reviews.text:
Outstanding service from Jorge!
I had an amazing experience at Founding Farmers thanks to Jorge. He was incredibly attentive, friendly, and professional from start to finish. His recommendations were spot-on, and he made sure we had everything we needed throughout the meal. It’s rare to find someone

Every staff member we encountered was pleasant and professional. The host was welcoming and our server was extremely attentive. The food was very fresh. The macaroni and cheese is the best I’ve ever tasted. The coconut cream pie made an excellent dessert. I’m sure I will be back again in the near fu

My ride-or-die restaurant when I’m in DC. Fresh ingredients and plenty of options to please every palate — salads, sandwiches, fish and meat plates, pastas, and more. My risotto was good, but I expected a bit more flavor considering all the ingredients. Next time, I’ll try the scallops. The French f

Food is great and fresh. I got the cheeseburger and fried okra.  My husband got the chicken fried steak meal with gravy, macaroni and cheese, green beans and a waffle.  No complaints.  All very good.  Andy was our waitress on both occasions and she was great. Ambience is very nice and bright. I woul

OMG every bite was absolutely delicious! My Straw & Hay pasta was perfect. I always get nervous with meals that have bacon because it makes it too salty but that was not the case with this dish. My husband loved his chicken noodle soup. The chicken was so tender and flavorful. I’m so glad someone re

The whole experience was stellar. Pablo was our server, and it was truly the best service we’ve had in Washington. He was knowledgeable about the menu, offered fantastic recommendations, and made our dining experience feel really special. He was attentive and quick to take care of anything we needed

Le Diplomate is an incredible spot for date night. It’s right on 14th Street and perfectly captures that classic European brasserie atmosphere. It’s definitely on the pricier side, but absolutely worth it for a special evening.

I highly recommend the steak frites, escargot, and duck. The duck, in p

My experience at this restaurant was excellent with the food and the service. The decor of the place was very pretty. The food was delicious. The coffee was super delicious, with an intense and tasty flavor. I loved it. The waiter who served us, I have to say this. We had a small incident with the c

My lunch at Le Diplomate in D.C. was truly exquisite. The atmosphere is authentically French and wonderfully charming. It is full of energy, conversation, and a fun vibe.

Since it was a gorgeous day in the 70s, I was especially grateful to sit outside on the covered patio and enjoy the afternoon.

Midnight in Paris, but Make It D.C.

There’s something about Le Diplomate that makes you believe in romance again — even if it’s just between you and your glass of Bordeaux. The lights shimmer like a Parisian dream, the chatter hums like a love song, and every bite feels like it’s flirting with you.

The atmosphere and vibe were great—very spacious, open, clean, and filled with natural light from the large windows. There were plenty of seats available as well. However, the food quality was disappointing. Maybe we expected too much, but aside from the French fries, which were good, the rest of th

Food was great - we went in a group of 5 so we ordered loads of food including the tasting menu. The food was delicious and some dishes were creative - we were impressed by the bone marrow. The beefsteak was delicious and the salad selection was great. I’d recommend coming in a group so you get to t

Atmosphere is beautiful, food was totally good, but not spectacular. I think the overall score of 4.5 is fair. The Brussels sprouts were delicious, the babaganoush was just okay. The pita looks cool, but I wish it was a bit thicker. The crunchy vegetables was just raw veggies. If you wanna save 20%,

Zaytinya, one of José Andrés’s long-standing DC restaurants, has been a favorite in the city for years. It had been quite a while since I last dined there, but I recently attended a reception and was reminded why it’s still such a Washington hotspot.

The restaurant is beautiful and inviting. There’

Very nice place to hang out and have healthy food.
The Tabboule needed more lemon juice and more olive oil.
The bone marrow kibbeh bas really good although i wished there was more sauce.
The Shish Taouk was good, it's just a small portion of 4 pieces. It was chicken thighs not breast, which makes we

First time here and wow—what a great experience! I was kind of bummed about missing the first UT game while in D.C., but to my surprise, they had it playing on the only TV in the back bar, right where I was sitting. Pretty sure my UT shirt had something to do with that. 😉

The longer I stayed, the m

Absolutely incredible. This place was recommended to me, and I recommend it to everyone. I had the swordfish, and it was tasty. But that was nothing compared to the oysters that we got, as well as the scallops. Absolutely divine; it was clear that the food was fresh. I also cannot recommend the brea

Stopped for a few beers and an appetizer after a day of exploring. We got the Hollander Maine Mussels. Absolutely wonderful..be sure to get extra bread so you can soak up all the delicious broth. Sorry my photo with the lid off didn't come out

Old Ebbitt Grill in Washington, DC, is a classic dining spot that lives up to its reputation. The atmosphere is historic and charming, making it a perfect place to enjoy a memorable meal in the capital. I tried the crab dip and the fried calamari, and both were absolutely outstanding—the crab dip wa

Old Ebbitt Grill is a must-visit if you’re in DC!
The pasta was amazing and the food looked gorgeous too 😎
Make a reservation- wait time can be 1-2hours without one.
Definitely try the signature crab cake!
One is big enough to share 🙌
The fries 🍟 were also super tasty!

My boyfriend and I went to Fiola Mare to celebrate our two-year anniversary, and it was honestly perfect. The service was on another level, everyone was super attentive, friendly, and made us feel really special the whole night. You can tell the chef cares about every little detail, because the food

The food was delicious and the restaurant was nice and clean, and the servants were well trained and very nice. The oysters and the sauce were absolutely delicious. But the only bad part was that the pasta and the shrimp. The pasta was sort of uncooked and the shrimp was too salty. Overall I still r

Try the Sunday night prix fixe menu: four courses for $85.  With the exception of the dessert, one of the very best meals I’ve had in DC and a bargain for the price, with excellent service and surprisingly robust portion sizes. We supplemented with a half dozen oysters (exceptional, $27) and a spina

Despite someone booking my birthday reservation for 12 well in advance, our private room was given to another party. We were split into two tables — not too far apart, but definitely a bit of a walk to mingle with everyone.

That said, the food was amazing! Towards the end of the night, once most ta

This is the best seafood place in DC. I eat seafood every day and fly to Spain/portugal at least twice a year just to eat. (I consider 99% of seafood dishes trash in the U.S.)

And the service is always excellent. I will go back often. At the end, they give free ice cream to kids — and we certainly

Loved the atmosphere of the Dabney and the open fire/ambiance is great! However, the whole experience was consistently lacking that my “wow, yum!” factor. First off, I reserved seats at the bar because we love sitting at the bar - but we were instead seated at a high top table away from the bar whic

Absolutely the coolest dining experience and best meal of my life. 5 course tasting menu was phenomenal. The atmosphere of the kitchen and being able to watch their craft with the open flame grill leaves you staring at the kitchen drooling over each plate as it comes out

Phenomenal dinner for my husband with friends. We went a little crazy and spent way too much, but the food was so fantastic we’ll treasure the memory. Some standouts for us were the scallops and pork belly. Sugar toads and beef cheeks were delicious and unique, don’t skip the sweet potato rolls

My husband and I had a wonderful anniversary experience at Dabney DC on 10/24. Our wait staff was amazing, especially Lucy! She walked us through the menu and chef’s specials.  My husband and I chose a beautiful 32oz ribeye. I adore eating at restaurants where the chef and staff remain committed to

Shew.. Lots could be said. But ill keep it short in the long list of long-winded reviews.
Phenomenal, The food, the service, the vibe...

Wanted to keep it short but I NEED TO ADD...
Exceptional service from The Dabney team! My buddy Pratt joked about a dish with the server, saying it would have bee

Service was a little slow until we told the waiter he needed to do better, which he did. It should not take 20min to get water brought to the table. It did not look that crowded, but maybe they are lacking staff. The hostess did not sit us until our time, we were about 15min early. The other thing I

Stopped in on an early weekday morning and was blown away. As expected, we had no wait and our choice of seats. The ambiance offers a chic and almost elegant feel and the layout is genius (great for crowds). Also, it’s conveniently connected to a hotel and great for those visiting out of town. The s

The patio bar is like an escape from the city. You are transformed from Washington to some chic place. Lots of area for a friend group gathering. I think they have a happy hour. The restaurant decor is very modern. Dim, black finishes, warm and inviting. Not a huge place but plenty of room. Service

Went to Dirty Habit DC and honestly, it was a disappointment from start to finish. The hostess greeted us with a stank face and zero professionalism felt like we were inconveniencing her just by showing up. Then, instead of being offered normal water, we were given hot water at the table. No menu fo

All about the food, service and entertainment!

Our server Ruben was a star: friendly, attentive, and kept those bottomless mimosas flowing. Many in our group ordered the “Waffle It Up,” “The Monaco,” and Breakfast Potatoes, and they were big crowd-pleasers. The food was delicious — satisfying, beau

reviews.text: After 8 days in DC and a bunch of restaurants, Amazônia was the best by far. It offers creative Peruvian dishes, bursting with flavors and colors. There wasn't anything we tried that was not delicious. But the ceviche amazonico and the pulpo al olivo were top. Great service, nice decor, plenty of ch

Service is an afterthought here and a lot of improvements are needed. It's so dark in the evening that guests use their phone flashlights. I get the intimate setting vibe but one should be able to see whoever is seated across from them and maybe the venue. Tables are so tightly set together that a s

My second visit to Amazonia - the staff operate as a high-end, well-oiled machine here. Greeted as I walked in, sent upstairs. Greeted again by eager, smiling staff, and shown to my table. Our server DaVinci was divine, very knowledgeable, kind and helpful. I loved the cocktails, especially their fe

Food was delicious! Mike was a great server and very helpful and polite. We tried the skewers, scallops, pasta and hot octopus. It was a fun place for a date night. The ambiance was nice, easy to talk and the decor was cute.

The food was very good, but the prices and portions are completely out of touch with reality, especially with what is going on with the affordability crisis.

A $55 martini, half ice. A single piece of sashimi for $50. A 2 lb yellowtail for $260, BEFORE they debone it. $5 extra for a couple of peppe

We had an amazing experience. Everything was perfect — the food, the atmosphere, and the service.
Mariana was our server, she was professional with a beautiful smile. She took care of us carefully.

We ordered the French onion soup, Caesar salad, and a ribeye au poivre served with a delicious pepper

We experienced the perfect dinner! The food was outstanding; delicious, presentable, and cooked to perfection. The service was  extraordinary thanks to our server, Angel. He was phenomenal, attentive, patient, and offered excellent recommendations. If every restaurant had Angel serving their custome

Yesterday we decided to finally try la grand boucherie for our 7th year anniversary. From the beginning they greeted us and coat checked us. The front staff was very friendly and welcoming. They immediately sat us down. And our server, Reilly was so knowledgeable and friendly and it totally made the

Amine Was amazing and serving and recommending great drinks and entrée! We started out with mussels and awesome salad! He recommended a drink that tasted like rose and also another drink that has a spice to it as well called Phoenix. I will recommend the rose drink, and also the Phoenix on the side.

Had the loveliest lunch. The mocktail was fabulous - light and fresh, subtle flavors. The soupe l’oignon was wonderful, the croque Madame had a perfectly fried egg on top, and I had never had a Mont-Blanc before but it was fantastic. My server Francesco was the best part - knowledgeable, attentive,

This place is so great! We ate there four times in four days. No joke. Our favorite meal was our last day there and they had a Saturday brunch that was off the chain! For a buffet brunch that had such a wide variety and such high-quality food, the price was excellent. Only 35 bucks!  Great cocktails

We did brunch buffet this past weekend and to he honest it was alright. We went there 11:30sh and most of the food are not getting refilled or they take long to refill.

Location: It is located along Massachusetts Avenue. There is a lot of seatings inside and the main buffet spot is in the middle.

My husband and I stopped here for an early lunch on a Sunday. There were a few groups waiting to be seated at a table when we walked in, but we were able to find some open seats at the bar. It was very lively with the breakfast/brunch bar, but we decided to order coffees and sandwiches.

I got a hot

Founding Farmers

Nice place to gather after a busy day viewing museums. The location was easy to find. The Labor Day holiday allowed free and easy access to street parking.
The restaurant is spacious and inviting with a nice outdoor patio area. Service was prompt and friendly.
Their lunch/ dinner m

The spicy chicken sandwich was delicious.  Had the right amount of heat and flavor.  The beignets where a miss. They tasted like a fried donut, very heavy and doughy. Verus a light and fluffy beignet. Service is fast and staff is nice and helpful.

Food was absolutely great …full of flavour and really well prepared. The atmosphere was electric, with a lively energy that made the whole experience even better. Our server was fantastic: friendly, attentive, and genuinely helpful throughout the meal, making sure we were topped up with water.

The

First time here and I really enjoyed it! I got the Caesar salad, calamari, and the Drunken Love pizza, everything was delicious. The pizza was definitely my favorite, especially paired with the garlic sauce that came with the calamari. The vibe was great and everything tasted super fresh. My only sm

Cozy Italian Vibes at Grazie Nonna in DC
I recently dined at Grazie Nonna in Washington, DC, and it was a charming spot for Italian-American comfort food. Nestled at 1100 15th St. NW, the restaurant boasts a lively, welcoming atmosphere with a fun breezeway setting—perfect for a casual meal with fri

I absolutely love this place! I came here recently for my best friend’s last meal in DC before moving out of state. Grazie Nonna was our top choice and it did not disappoint. Our server was incredibly kind, personable, and attentive from start to finish.

We started with the Caesar salad for the tab

A true taste of Italy! All of the appetizers, entrées, and drinks were excellent—flavorful, fresh, and well-prepared. The service was friendly and attentive, which made the evening even better. The only downside was the dessert; the brownie fell short for us as it was a bit dry and lacked the cannol

Still the gold standard for tapas in the DC area. I've been to his Vegas location and several Bazaar locations and Zaytinya, but this one is still my favorite restaurant in his restaurant empire. Make sure you make a reservation as this place is always packed. I've noticed the menu has shrunk compar

Food was amazing, you should always go in groups here so that you can taste a bunch of different things, my favourite was the garlic squid with squid in dips however the I rolled pasta was just as good. Service was amazing however it can get busy so I do recommend that you book a table beforehand so

Stopped into Jaleo for their generous offer during these furlough times. Jaleo is one of many and one of owner Jose Andres' restaurants offering deals for those impacted by the government shutdown.

The place was busy at 12pm. The service was quick and polite. Two of the tables are also glass topped

I ordered a five course tasting menu with wine pairing. The food and wines were wonderful. My only complaint was the small pour. A typical pour is anywhere from 2-4 ounces.  It's enough to have a few sips and truly taste how the wine complements the food. Fernanda gave me two ounces at the most. Two

Had a wonderful dinner at Jaleo tonight with the wifey! I started with a red sangria. We ordered the croquetas and fried calamari. For our main entree we ordered the seafood paella! I will have to admit we were blown away by this dish. We would even be fair in saying this even beat out the paella we

Filomena is truly my favorite restaurant! Their homemade pastas are out of this world incredibly fresh, rich, and full of authentic flavor. You can really taste the love and tradition in every bite.

The atmosphere is super classy and very high elegant, yet warm and welcoming at the same time. It fe

Absolutely delicious meatballs.  The staff were very polite and their service was truly top notch. The bar seating was comfortable and overall atmosphere was relaxing. The free bread was quite nice. Food wise do yourselves a favor and get the meatball, they were absolutely amazing. Overall if you wa

Filomena is a popular Georgetown Italian spot with big portions but average flavor. The Linguini Cardinale and meatballs were fine, just not worth the $69 before tip. Desserts look pretty but seemed overly sweet. Overall, decent but overpriced — good if you’re already in the area, but not a must-vis

We happen to stay in Georgetown DC and on the way to the hotel the name caught my eye, because one of our family members has the same name Filomena. We have to go eat there I told my husband. Shortly after we walked in, the restaurant is downstairs so it’s a flight down. We were greeted and seated i

We celebrated my husband's 35th birthday here on Oct 3rd! The staff was so kind and welcoming. Had looked forward to coming here as my husband is of Italian roots and this reminded him of his childhood. I deeply enjoyed everything and everyone at Filomena and you can tell how proud they are of this

Amazing food, great and attentive service, with a lively atmosphere! Stick to the Mediterranean fare when you can if you do the all-you-can-eat brunch, to avoid filling up on unnecessary carbs, but everything was delicious! Our server, Vedat, was all smiles and made sure we were always topped up on

Very delicious Turkish food and a great atmosphere! I had the Adana and Lahmacun—both were truly top-notch. My wife ordered the octopus and shrimp, which were also outstanding. A big thank-you to Ferdi for his warm hospitality; he was incredibly kind to us throughout our visit. We even hoped to take

The spread sampler is a good way to start, hummus was very thick which I didn’t like too much but all the other spreads were nice- I appreciated the diversity (Codroe, a version of tzatziki, roasted bell pepper, baba ganoush type thing). The lamb was quite underwhelming- the onions were raw and coul

Love these small plate experiences as you can order a lot and taste more. We had five and sampled dips, the always available warm pita, salad, fish, bass, chicken kabob, lamb, and wonderfully textured desserts with lovely flavors. Great ambience, too. Must go in this cute neighborhood of DC.

$50/person brunch with unlimited food + 2 drinks was absolutely amazing! Everything was so delicious, fresh,and the overall experience was 10/10.
Would definitely recommend!

Decided to check this spot out on a hangry whim after a concert. Coming from a town where anything sit down decent is closed at 9-10 this was a very welcome change of pace.

Caleb was our main bartender, and quite the vibe. Really made my wife and I feel welcome, without needing to order 4 drinks to

Took my European family here for lunch after walking the mall for a few hours. The lobster roll was stuffed filled with lobsters in a delicious brioche bun. Accompanied by crunchy fries, and homemade coleslaw. This was a perfect pick me up. My dad had the lobster pasta. The crustaceans were juicy, a

Delicious, AMAZINGLY DELICIOUS!!  A little more pricey than some other local places, but the food and drinks are incredible, The Long Island ice tea had top shelf liquor, tasted great and so strong. The octopus was so tender; people cheese cake was subtle and extremely smooth. Mmmmmm. Crabcake  Sand

September 12, 2024 - First time experience at The Hamilton was beyond our greatest expectations. We were gifted tickets to see Keep Flying, Ballyhoo, and The Mad Caddies. The music was phenomenal as well as our seating area. It was nice to dine and see a concert. We were shocked at how fancy & upsca

We came here expecting a long wait time given the reviews and being a Friday night, but we were quickly seated and with some amazing service. It was surprisingly very child friendly and the food and atmosphere was amazing. This was out first time in DC and definitely a must try place. We would highl

I came in with my family for a birthday dinner. Our server, Gregory, was very knowledgeable about the menu and very friendly. We ordered everything from appetizers all the way to dessert and the food was amazing and very fresh. The smooth jazz and warm lighting was so welcoming and cozy. We told our

Very attentive staff and they were very accommodating. Quick service by the chef as well. Food was really good. On par with other DC well known Italian restaurants. Medium noise level for the size. It was lively when we went. The only problem was the bathrooms. Only two of six were not working. They

Food and service was great.  We did encounter some issues about tables and chairs being too tight for us but Christian and Nikki went above and beyond to accommodate us even though the restaurant was fully booked. Nikki & Christian were awesome and welcoming. Would recommend - don’t miss out on the

We had such a great time! Everyone was very friendly, we didn’t have reservation and they were able to find us a table! We had the calamari, carbonara pasta, gnocchi and the tiramisu… all these with a great Barolo wine! Paola was great! the gnocchi were  regular but the rest was great

I love Italian, but this was a bit lower than my expectations. The server, Gabriella, was so excellent, but my favorite Italian cuisine was too juicy for me. All the same it's a good spot for Italian dinning. Wouldn't be my first choice but would go there again. The steak was excellent but squid ink

Chose to come to Succotash for an early dinner on a Saturday night. Got a reservation but it likely wasn’t needed between 4-5pm.

Service was great and the food was amazing!

Chicken and waffles very good. The fried chicken alone was likely the best fried chicken I’ve ever had. It was super crisp ye

We had an amazing experience at Succotash Prime from the minute we entered the beautiful restaurant.   The long and beautiful bar and tasteful decor drew us right in.  They have a great wine list and superb craft cocktails.  We had their Taste of the South tasting menu and it was off the charts.  Ou

As a Korean-Canadian who enjoyed watching Chef Edward Lee on the Netflix show named Culinary Class Wars last year, I was excited to visit Edward Lee’s restaurant in Washington, DC! Our server, Benjamin, was incredibly kind and attentive, always quick to help with anything we needed.
The food was ama

My wife and I had an incredible dining experience at Succotash. We were on a bit of a time crunch, but our server Benjamin went above and beyond to make everything seamless. His service was genuinely exceptional, he was attentive and accommodating. He anticipated what we needed, kept everything movi

This feels like the place to go for business dinners and celebration occasions, yet it's comfortable enough for friends to meet or a nice date night.

The food is really good.   It's not a huge menu, but what is served is really good.

We had two vegetarians in our group and each person had somethin

After a day at the Mall, we went to The Smith for lunch. We were seated immediately, and our server greeted us as we sat down although it was busy. The sourdough bread was very good. I opted to get the veggie burger which was moist and flavorful. The fries were crisp. My friend had the Vanilla Bean

We enjoyed dinner here the other night, overall great experience! We ordered the Mac & cheese (5/5), braised short rib fusilli (4/5, not much short rib in the dish but taste was great), NY strip (3/5, fries were lacking but the steak was good), apple crumb pie (2/5, wasn't a favorite), and hot fudge

The food is amazing. We tried brunch, lunch and diner on differrnt days and kept returning to this place not because it was conveniently across the street from our hotel but because the food was deserving, atmosphere was very nice and service was attentive and fast. Everything we tried from their me

I was highly dissatisfied with my food and the description of my menu item was misleading. I was visiting DC for the day from out of town and had it not been for the occasion I was there for, I would have sent this back and made a complaint to the chef. The manager or whomever is in charge of the me

Amazing Cinnamon Roll. We just stumbled upon this amazing restaurant and ended up coming here 3 days in a row. Their breakfast is great all around. If you’re lucky enough to visit when cinnamon rolls are being served order two ;) they are huge and packed full of flavor, the amount of icing could be

It was a pleasant experience, the atmosphere was nice and welcoming. I really recommend making a reservation.

The host and waiters were super friendly, super nice. Thank you Mr. Mabi (Sorry I'm winging the spelling).

The restaurant was tidy and clean, unfortunately there was some sticky parts on o

Very pleasant spot! Crashed here twice for a brunch during my short trip to DC. Plenty of options for a meal and drinks, cozy atmosphere to settle in. Zack’s service was pleasant and friendly, really enjoyed his advices. Portions were extremely huge, but I guess it is normal in the US (in Europe is

We enjoyed our food a lot. Ordered some tarts to go, they are amazing!! Flaky texture and fruit stuffing are so good togethe

This restaurant has such an elegant and antique atmosphere that immediately makes you feel like you’ve stepped into a classic European dining room. The portions are absolutely massive – we were four women and each of us ordered one dish, but every single plate could easily serve three people. The pa

Family-style Italian restaurant with a nice selection of seafood, pastas, and meat dishes.  Service is very good.  Limited wine list.  The rigatoni and broccoli was a hot our table.  The linguine and shrimp was a bland dish. The fried calamari was also a hit.  The focaccia was dried out and old. The

The service is always quick and sweet, love the low lit atmosphere of this environment. They have relatively clean restrooms and a good amount of seating within the restaurant. My school has group dinners at this restaurant and we always enjoy it!! They even let us take home the leftovers from the d

We came to this place to enjoy a nice pasta. We ordered the pasta pomodoro and they gave us boiled pasta with what it seemed full tomatoes out of a can. Servers said this is South Italian style. We have been to Italy and we can say this is not true. We ate half and we returned it. I think there are

Then our bartender/slash waiter was so attentive and gave us exceptional advice or how we should get certain things on the menu prepared to accommodate the whole gro

We came to Iron Gate to celebrate my partner’s birthday, and it was a lovely experience. The indoor dining area is charming and intimate, perfect for a special occasion.

We tried several dishes. The standout was the fava bean salad. It’s savory yet refreshing with a well-seasoned dressing. The bean

Great place! My wife and I were there for a Friday night dinner. It was the first time trying Mediterranean food. I just came to the US. Back in my country I used to eat food with spices like indian and Middle Eastern food. I used to think Mediterranean food was not that good but this place complete

Would I recommend? Yes
Super cool interior layout

Did the market table ($95) with wine pairing (75, 4 pours)
Pairings were right up my alley (pun intended). Standouts were the beet ravioli and oyster, Branzino

Omg! What a night it was!! I felt so cozy as well as my husband! We both felt so honored and loved with all the experience! We couldn’t have the 4 course meal since it’s family stuff but tried the focaccia, crudo, beetroot ravioli, branzino and ribeye followed by the chocolate mousse dessert. The ravioli was pro

We started with the Arancini and Caesar salad. Both were good but neither was unbelievable. I did like ho

Our server said he was going to have something special for us at the end of our meal. There was nothing! There is a 20% service fee a

This place does have 1700 reviews so I won't call it a hidden gem, but I did find it randomly on the map. But let me tell you this place is amazing on all levels. From host, to service, to food, they simply deliver on all fronts. We started the night with the risotto and the buratta. Let me tell you

Food was excellent, the 40 layer lasagna has an amazing sauce. The desert was also very good, with fresh fruit. The service is next level, they keep your table clean and fresh silverware between courses. It cost abit but is definitely worth it if you want a good meal and a nice experience.

Its not often that spots that are splayed all across social media are able to live up to the quality and expectations that come with that notoriety but I was really blown away by the food here. Got to enjoy their restaurant week menu and everything was really meticulously made and beautifully presen

Great experience, most of the food was absolutely delicious but the portions aren’t huge (as expected). The Kinship name on the door is almost undetectable, speak-easy vibes to the entrance. The service was impeccable, the decor is minimalist and not too cozy (very subjective of course). The beef to

Their signature lobster toast is an absolute must-try. They even surprised me with a handwritten birthday note, whic

Overpriced and disappointing taste. Paid $160 per person for the Kinship menu and most dishes were barely edible. Only the bread and tuna appetizer were decent. Guapo's Restaurant: A VIBRANT Dining Experience in D.C.

We had such a wonderful experience thanks to our server, Brianna! She was extremely pleasant, attentive, and took the time to explain the amazing menu in detail. I really appreciated her thoughtful recommendations—she clearly knows her stuff and made the whole dining experience even better. To top i

Stopped here for a light lunch. There's patio and indoor seating. We were seated immediately and the place was less than half full. We both ordered the Sage chicken brochette salad. One skewer of chicken next to a small salad.  Flavor was very nice on the chicken, but some pieces were dry. Perfect s

Last night at R&B Wednesdays was amazing as far as the music & food. Especially the beginning half until like 9:45. The lady DJ was great!! I will say some of the staff need better hospitality skills. You cannot talk to customers any type of way just because the entire staff doesn’t have clear commu

Susheria was amazing! We went on Juneteenth and the DJ kept the vibe going with great music. The food was good, the service was excellent, and the drinks were definitely hitting. I’ll absolutely be back. The only downside is the parking - street parking is tough to find, and the garage nearby can be

Had a 7PM reservation to celebrate a birthday. The decor is nice and ambiance is ok until the DJ and hookah start. I can appreciate any restaurant that offers a DJ but the restaurant is not a dance club. When two tables just steps away ordered hookah. I knew it was time to go. We preferred not to ea

I had such an amazing experience here. The drinks, the food, the music, and the lovey bartender, Andreas were all just top notch!!! I’m from Texas visiting DC for the weekend but I’m making it my mission to come back as soon as I can to this establishment. Thank you Andreas for making my trip that m

The best service, Nassim was a wonderful waiter and server. He was so friendly and added so much value to our experience. The atmosphere is amazing, great music and warm lighting. The food was fantastic and we left with full stomachs and happy feelings!!

Incredible food, service, and atmosphere at oki bowl in Georgetown. There is very delicious and customizable ramen. The miso ramen was rich, and slightly sweet, when paired with the beef. Highly recommend with a side of chili oil!! The Tom Yum ramen was very spicy - with enormous shrimp - very yummy

We got the mushroom rice bowl and the Oki curry bowl. It was delicious. The servers were very nice. They have lots of anime decorations on the walls that are pretty cool. I definitely want to go again. What a lovely time!

came in with an intense hangover and their ramen brought me to life. also ordered crispy octopus tentacles yummmssss. and finished my meal with Orion beer (Japanese beer) 🍺

Love the atmosphere too, very nostalgic esp the 90s anime’s wall decor/mural.

Run, don’t walk! Had my first ramen experience in the US, and it might have already set the bar. We ordered the Galanga Ramen (vegetarian) — it looked incredible, and that first bite of crispy kale? Next level. The portion was generous, easily enough for two people. We also tried their Thai Boba, wh

We ordered the unagi bowl and the spider tom yum.
We hope the unagi bowl could come with a bit more side dishes.
Overall, the food was decent, but not quite impressive enough to make us want to come back.
The interior decor is very cute.

Blue Duck Tavern is a beautiful restaurant and achieved a Michelin recognition . I've been here a few times now, and each visit has been a solid experience.

Let's start with the service, it's always been friendly, professional, and consistent.

Now, about the food. The pork sausage wasn't my favori

For a memorable birthday brunch, we chose Blue Duck Tavern at the Hyatt in Washington, DC, and it was a fantastic decision. We walked from our hotel, so I'm unsure about parking, but l'd suggest allowing extra time to find a spot in this busy area.
Pro tip: make reservations to secure your table, as

Blue Duck Tavern offers a refined dining experience with well-prepared dishes and a stylish atmosphere. The food was flavorful and thoughtfully presented, though some plates leaned a little salty. The burger was juicy and rich, the dessert was creative, and the sides were comforting, making the whol

Visited Blue Duck Tavern during my stay at the Park Hyatt and had the chance to enjoy both late-night drinks and dessert, as well as breakfast the following morning. Everything was excellent. The desserts and cocktails in the evening were top-notch, elegantly presented and flavorful, perfect for a r

We made a reservation in advance, and every dish was a wonderful surprise!
We ordered all our favorites — lamb, beef, duck, seafood — and every dish was packed with rich flavors and amazing textures.
The crab meat in the crab cakes was super fresh, like it had just been hand-packed — so delicious! 🤤

info.name: Bozzelli's Italian Deli in Georgetown
info.address: 3000 K St NW Unit 115, Washington, DC 20007

reviews.text:
This was some kid the best pizza I’ve ever had!! As soon as I walked in the door the vibe was set! The pizza came out fresh and hot, exactly how we asked for it!

Ordering was easy, on a tablet right at the entrance.

The staff greeted us and provided us with anything we needed.

The highlight was t

Best pizza and sandwich we had in whole Washington area very friendly service and food is unbelievably delicious. Highly recommend to everyone who wants to have a good memory from their trip to DC and Georgetown neighborhood.

Great, friendly service!  Great food at a great price for the area!
I think they could use a few 2 person tables if they could make room to keep 1 person from sitting at their limited 4-6 person tables. This was the case when we first walked in and kept us from having a table, we almost left because

The pizza was what you’d expect at a kids restaurant vs an Italian deli.  The wings have flavor and the breading is thick and amazing, but they’re over fried and all you can taste is the oil.

The Italian sandwich had a little kick from the peppers which I loved, but it is very small and the meat ha

Absolutely LOVED my Metro Sub from Bozzelli's Georgetown!

What an awesome experience! I stopped by Bozzelli's in Georgetown today and ordered their Metro Sub, and wow – it was absolutely loaded! Every bite was packed with fresh, high-quality ingredients, perfectly balanced and incredibly flavorful.

Loved everything about Alara - the service, ambiance and food! Our waiter, Sasha, was very attentive! They serve freshly baked bread with yum olive oil and balsamic or pomegranate vinegar which was divine!! We Ordered the yogurt drink - a good probiotic boost. For food, got the muhmarrra, chicken Sh

We had such a wonderful experience at this Mediterranean restaurant! The food was absolutely amazing and so delicious. We only ordered appetizers, but they were more than enough and every bite was full of flavor.

Our server, Mia, made the experience even better, she was amazing! So respectful, atte

The only reason it gets a 3.5 is because they charge a 20% service fee and it's not explicitly stated at the top of the menu. It's almost like a disclaimer at the bottom of the menu which is somewhat of a bait and switch. There is also an implied dress code of fine dining business professional attir

Turkish Alara offers an amazing brunch experience! The food was fresh, flavorful, and beautifully prepared. Every dish was delicious and authentic, with plenty of variety. The atmosphere is warm and welcoming, making it the perfect place to enjoy a relaxing meal. Service was excellent as well—friend

I usually try to give every restaurant an honest review.
So with the plus, there was also a pretty big negative, that influenced the decision not to return.

We were very hungry and decided on Alara as it was close by.
As you enter the decor is extremely impressive.
We were seated fast, ordered fast

Food and drinks were good but the prices were a bit steep for the portion sizes. Predominantly the calamari. We got maybe 10 pieces for $18. The flatbread $18 with just chunks of tomato and cheese. My lemon martini was great. Overall the food is good but the prices are a bit high in my opinion.

Came for Sunday brunch for my daughters birthday and it was fabulous. The parking is atrocious, but that’s Georgetown for you! There is a nearby garage with a two minute walk for $23 or another one further down with a 6 minute walk for $12. We set a reservation and were sat expeditiously in this cut

Went here to celebrate after work and it was a lovely space in the heart of Georgetown. The outdoor area has pretty views and is tucked away from the street/sidewalk bustle.

Happy hour was great. We had wings and drinks for a reasonable price.
The servers switched and it threw us off when it came t

This little place is incredible. The tenderloin sliders are the best I have ever had in my life. The focaccia was incredible. The cheese curds were to die for. The drinks were delicious. Everything was perfect. Highly recommend.

Myself and five Marine corps veterans decided to have dinner at this establishment on veterans Day. The restaurant advertised free meals for veterans. The restaurant offered all meals on the menu for free. We each chose a different entree from the menu. The server arranged for us to receive happy ho

Absolutely the BEST crab cakes we have ever had in our entire lives!!!! No fillers just wonderful, moist, delicious crab!!!! You do not need any sauce or even lemon it was that amazing!! We are so grateful for our uber driver Jose for recommending this restaurant!!! The clam chowder was also excelle

If you’re craving a variety of seafood options, Tony & Joe’s is sure to satisfy—especially with the added bonus of outdoor seating and a beautiful waterfront view. The hospitality was top-notch; the staff greeted us with warm smiles and were very accommodating when we arrived early for our reservati

It’s a nice place overall. It was pretty empty when we got there but everything was pretty normal. I think we right in between the lunch and dinner crowd. Food was excellent!

The view is nice as well- definitely going back when there is better and it’s not too hot. They are able to host quite a few

We have a wonderful experience here! We started out with the meatballs and oysters, and moved on to the crab cod and fillet strips. Absolutely delicious food all around! And of course, the view of the water was beautiful.

We settled on Tony and Joe’s. I ordered the 16-ounce ribeye steak. Let me just say, the meal itself was outstanding. The steak was cooked to perfection, tender and flavorful at medium, with just the right amount of seasoning to let the quality of the meat shine. The fries that came with it were cris

I am blown away by the total experience I had here. Almost felt like a dream walking into such a chic sexy environment being greeted by the nicest staff. Everyone was dressed well and the place looked tip top, clean, and unique. Everyone from the hostess to the server was exceptionally friendly and

The service and food were superior. It's a beautiful setting with amazing food. We enjoyed the prix fixe menu which highlighted lobster, and the flavors were unbelievably delicious. I cannot recommend L'Avant-Garde enough!
Wonderful restaurant. The Lobster Prix Fix was sublime. The ambience and service were great as well. This was really special.

Unreal experience. Chef Sebastian is in a league of his own. Some standouts weee the foie gras, lobster entree, truffle Brie, and baguette with butter (the last was simple yet perfect). But truly every dish we tried was outstanding. For cocktails, we had the last word & tequila bouquet, all great. C

I’ve been there twice and tried several dishes, each one was really good and full of flavor. I also love the quiet and romantic atmosphere; it makes the whole experience even more enjoyable. Definitely a place worth revisiting.
Been coming here for a couple years now and love stopping in with the PEV crew!  Food and service are always top notch.  Check them out if you already haven't, Best wings in Georgetown

The wings here are just okay. They're fried but they didn't come out crispy. I tried wings with the hot honey sauce which wasn't very spicy and I couldn't really taste the honey. I also tried the mango habanero which tasted like regular buffalo sauce to me and definitely couldn't taste any mango. Th

Stopped for wings, ended up ordering beignets .... because who wouldn't end up ordering beignets instead of wings right?  The beignets here are not actually beignets but better.  It's fried croissant nuggets bathed in sugar honey syrup and it's my new addiction which I cannot find anywhere else.

Wi

I love chicken wings. Found this place on a recommendation from a local. I walked well over a mile in the sweltering heat and ate outside. What an experience that was. Sweating not only from the weather but the delicious chicken wings is about as close to a spiritual experience as I’ve gotten.

Pict

Can't say enough great things.
Wingos had the best wings I've eaten in over 25 years.  Perfectly cooked.  Extra crisp on outside yet still juicy.
Would give anything to have one here.  The owner and employees were very nice.
They even gave us some free desert.  Wow wow wow.  Soooo delicious 😋..

First time in DC ,and tried Ethiopian food for the first time — .  This place is amazing, the food was so good . Best food I believe I’ve ever had ! Im not sure why I never tried it , maybe because the closest one to my home town is a 2 hour drive !
The Injera was a pretty cool, Im an immigrant myse

We visited DAS Ethiopian Restaurant in DC for the second time with our family, and it was excellent again. The food is authentic Ethiopian and truly delicious. I especially loved the spicy beef dish the staff recommended—super flavorful and very spicy, just how I like it!

Service was outstanding an

We had dinner there, and it was amazing. The host was super-accommodating, and the waitress and staff were excellent. Everything is done family style, so the menu choices come on a single large plate while everyone gets their own injera bread. The waitress was great in pointing out what combos and s
We had Chicken doro Kay wat  and shrimp tibs were fantastic. Sadly we were so full and couldn’t try the dessert.

We had an incredible Ethiopian lunch experience, post a morning of walking through the Tidal basin, watching cherry blossoms.

We got a few vegetarian entrees to share and one chicken entree among the non-vegetarians.

The injira was soft, supple and delicious.

Nick’s Riverside Grill boasts a great location right on the Georgetown waterfront, offering beautiful views of the Potomac River. The atmosphere is relaxed and pleasant—perfect for a casual lunch or evening out. Prices are reasonable, and the staff is exceptionally friendly and attentive, especially

Food: I had the jerk chicken bowl. The food tasted good, but the chicken was obviously frozen chicken breast that was microwaved/reheated and barely any cooking went into the making of my food.

Drinks: outside bar on a hot summer day beers were not ICE cold. They were okay temperature. Not the way

Stopped in to get a drink and kill some time, and ended up having a great experience! The bartender was absolutely wonderful! She was attentive, prompt, super friendly, knowledgeable, and made the experience what it was! Her recommendations were spot on and delicious. The mini-corn dogs will forever

This was a highlight of Georgetown.  Service for a group of 54 was fast and efficient.  My beer by Great Lakes brewery was very amazing.  Did a untapped brewery review.  The glazed salmon, garlic roasted potatoes, and perfectly made brocoli seasoned.  What a fun exciting place.  Must come here again
Our server, Valentina, was so pleasant. The food was EXCELLENT!!! The shrimp 🍤 was fresh. Nachos was abundant and good, could have had a little more meat.

We've looked for dinner options around 12:00am and this spot was open until 4:00am.
The pita was made right in front of us in a deck/Brick oven, Fresh and soft. Their hot sauce was good. The only reason i gave a 4 is bcoz i got a tiny meat piece in my vegetarian Zaatar wrap.

We wanted to come see Historic Georgetown area of DC.  With no idea of where to eat some lunch, looking at Google maps, the name Muncheez caught my attention. Read about it and compare prices with other eateries and decided to give it a try.  Excellent choice, no regrets.  We both ordered the Build

used to love this place, but the quality has really gone downhill. The food has become dry and lacks flavor, almost like no effort is being put into seasoning or freshness anymore. It used to be delicious and something I looked forward to, but now it’s disappointing. I hope they make some changes be

Ordered uber eats and I got stale rice & vermicelli, the rice was dry and crunchy and the noodles were also crispy.
The chicken… I got chicken jerky.
Very flavorless, very stale, very not great.
Munchies is a great reliable place for good food and good vibes, I’ve been here a few times, and now they’ve expedited their process with iPads, I love munchies! The chicken is unbeatable

I recently dined at Villa Yara in Washington, DC, and it was a delightful experience that left a lasting impression. The ambiance is warm and inviting, with a charming blend of modern and rustic decor that creates a cozy yet vibrant atmosphere. The staff were incredibly attentive, offering friendly

My visit to Villa Yara today was excellent! We ordered several Middle Eastern dishes to share, and everything was fresh and flavorful. The undisputed highlight of the meal was the chicken; it was simply the best. I highly recommend ordering a chicken dish for your table! Fantastic food and a great s

I stopped in after walking around Georgetown on a beautiful Autumn day.  The staff were warm and welcoming.  One thing I learned by stopping in at 2:45pm is their kitchen closes so they can prepare to re-open for dinner service.  Learning this I had to place my order all at one time.  Also, the food

Enjoyed my experience dining here. The service was great. Everything Iordered was delicious. My favorite is Yara's tabouli salad. The mixed grill was all tender, juice and flavorful. The hummus was so good and the baklava is perfect. Can't wait to come back to try other dishes

Great restaurant on M street that offers a tasteful and well balanced Lebanese menu. The food is full of flavor and the staff is quick and eager to help bridge the cultural barrier (if that’s the case with your party). Highly recommend!

I cannot believe I was served my food the way it was. The rice tasted like box rice & the cheese wasn’t even melted in the burrito bowl nor the burrito when I requested for the change. My food was very dry. Where is the love and the sauce? Maybe i’m spoiled with Mexican food elsewhere but this food

I have always loved Los Cuates in large part for its good service and decent food. The food has declined so much though, it’s really not good. And the service too.
I walked in at 8:45 for dinner. The nachos which are $16 and consist a 10 chips were completely burnt to a crisp. After waiting 20 minut
Favourite Mexican restaurant in DC. The atmosphere is simple, meals are good, plate are plenty!

Definitely a neat little spot with friendly staff and Touch Tunes so you can jam a little. The tacos were disappointing though. For $5 each taco, you expect more than a tablespoon of filling. You can see from the picture that the shells are only 1/3rd full. The Sangria is good though and it's a nice

Horrible customer service! we ordered a Coronarita and the server asked what flavor and what size and pointed at the menu, and she still asked what type so we ordered Mango. When our friends got their drinks, we realized the Corona on top was missing so another server came and we told her we didn’t

I made the mistake of going here on a busy Friday and naturally could not get my preferred seat. But the staff and the food made up for this in hospitality and flavour. The onion soup was the perfect blend of cheesy savoury goodness, and the pain au chocolat left me with no regrets!
I do recommend g

Boulangerie Christophe is a charming little gem conveniently tucked just off Wisconsin Ave NW in Georgetown. This cozy French pastry shop consistently delivers some of the most delicious and authentic French pastries in the area.
There can be a short wait at times, especially during peak hours, but

The best thing about this restaurant is the delicious food. The atmosphere is cozy, but it’s not very laptop-friendly. The chairs inside aren’t comfortable, and while the outdoor seating is nicer, you can’t use your laptop if you need to charge since there are no outlets available.
The service is fa

We got a beautiful medium sized fruit tart for my mom's birthday brunch. She loved it!  We got several other pastries. I especially loved the spinach ricotta croissant. My dad had am iced coffe that swayed him away from the sugar bomb iced coffee at McDonald's.  They have a charming outdoor seating

This bakery is outstanding. The croissants are buttery and perfectly flaky, the sandwiches are fresh and full of flavor, and the pastries are some of the best I’ve ever had. Everything tastes high-quality and made with care. A must-visit

info.name: George's King of Falafel and Cheesesteak

reviews.text: The restaurant came recommended by locals for best Shwarma in town and it did not disappoint. They have both meat based as well as vegetarian menu options available. Tried the Chicken & Beef Shwarma as well as the Lamb Gyro. All Shwarma had an authentic taste with balanced seasoning. The Beef and La

First time there, and we loved it! Friendly service, great options, nice environment and the food was delicious. I had the falafel and fries. Love how they cut it up to make it easier to eat. Comes with a side of hummus and pickled veggies. My guest got a lamb sandwich and said it was great. They st

One of the best Arabic/Middle-Eastern Restaurant. As a tourist from dubai i was craving and looking for a good place for shawarma & hummus so my friend took me to this place and it was worth it. We ordered shawarma platter with fries and pickles. And every bite was delicious. It was really soft and

After a lovely Habibi night adventure, schwarma was not something that I thought I needed, but alas, I ended up in Georgie’s, eating a delectable thing that I still don’t know what exactly is. Value is immaculate here, and while busy, it is worth the wait in line. If I ever find myself in Georgetown

Hands down the best Shawarma I’ve ever had! Let me tell you their fries, Tabbouleh, and falafel were also some of the best I’ve tried. We even got to sample both meats chicken and beef and they were both delicious. We ended up choosing the beef because it had a bit more kick to it, and the spices we

Delicious food and excellent service! Even though I had slightly higher expectations for the food, it still satisfied our cravings for mashawi. The overall experience was lovely, and the staff were so welcoming and kind.

Here are my ratings:
•	Beef sambosa 3/10
•	Hummus 9/10
•	Manto 7/10
•	Beef kab

I was in town for 6 days and ended up eating here 4 times. Excellent value and flavor. I had the: 1) $10 daily special, which was a chicken bowl. 2) $15 gyro and fries. 3) $30 lamb chops plate which is prolly enough to feed 2 people.

I was impressed with how fresh the food was and the quality and q

On 08/21, via uber eats I ordered a beef kebab which arrived in an unacceptable condition. The kebab had visible mold and an unpleasant smell, which made it look and feel unsafe to consume.

For health and safety reasons, I decided not to eat the food. I strongly don’t recommend this place, had only

Everything was really nice and the food was amazing and really tasty. I really enjoyed having the lamb kabobs and specially the eggplant was so delicious. I really recommend here if you’re Afghan food lovers. We had different meals and everything was delicious!

I’m in DC for work a lot and have had this place saved for a while. The spicy chicken kabob is delicious, the service was delightful, and whatever is in their sauces should be bottled! So much food for the price, too. Hope local Washingtonians can keep this place around for a long time!

info.name: Say Cheese!
info.address: 1071 Thomas Jefferson St NW, Washington, DC 20007

reviews.text: Eggs Benedict and the Turkish coffee were excellent. The seasoning in the sauce for the eggs and the poaching done perfectly! The service was good and so was the ambience. The rest of the orders were very average - the “better” bagel with packaged cream, not sure what was better about it; the omelet

Fell in love with this charming shop. In the heart of Georgetown; it’s quiet, welcoming and unassuming. I love a cleverly named business, so when I saw it was walking distance from the office, I was sold. I had never been and was so disappointed I got my lunch to go🥺. I called my order in while walk

Say Cheese, say yum! As a gluten free girlie, I can’t usually enjoy grilled cheese but that was an option here and I was thrilled. I got the Dipper and it was the perfect amount of soup and sammie for a Saturday afternoon. The lemonade was also refreshing. Inside the vibes are quaint and there’s a f

Stayed in the Graham Hotel right next door for 4 days and we literally had breakfast here every single day. Their avocado toast was incredibly delicious because it was so flavorful with goat cheese, a balsamic glaze and a hint of spice. Their coffee was great too and the lady who served us every mor

Talk about a place with potential. Very cute cafe/restaurant vibe, loved the decor and was very hopeful when I walked in. Unfortunately that’s where it ended. The service was fine, but the food wasn’t good. Ordered the grilled cheese combo with a small tomato soup, and a grilled cheese with bacon an

info.name: Mai Thai of Georgetown
info.address: 3251 Prospect St NW C-1, Washington, DC 20007

reviews.text: Fantastic place for really good Thai food. This was a stop on a good tour of DC. The atmosphere is friendly and lively. The staff is fantastic. The food is amazing, with a sushi chef where you can see him creating his art. I had a delicious sushi roll that unfortunately I don't remember the name and

Best Thai food I’ve had in a while. So flavourful and yummy. Had a filling meal with noodles, tofu, sushi, veggies and of course the mango sticky rice was the cherry on top. The server was so nice and attentive. Really loved the ambiance and the food. One of my favourite finds in DMV for sure!

Nice atmosphere,  friendly staff and delicious food. Prices were great, especially for a city restaurant.  My family of four enjoyed each of our meals which was delivered to our table very quickly.  Especially tasty was the Honey Chicken,  Peanut Chicken and Sushi.  All meals were presented creative

Disappointing Birthday Lunch Experience

Took my wife here for her birthday lunch, but unfortunately, it was not a pleasant experience for several reasons:
1.	Cold Food: The food arrived lukewarm, which made it taste stale. For me, if a dish isn’t served hot, it loses its appeal.
2.	Poor Hygiene: Th

Although the food doesn't satisfy my appetite, the service is great!

Green curry doesn't really blend in the ingredients and Fried calamari is not impressed.
Pad Thai tastes a bit too heavy for me but still fine. It is basically a safe choice in all Thai restaurants.
Would recommend trying other di

Reliability: 100

This place is an absolute must if you love pizza. I have eaten here so many times and it's always good, always ready in 90s (or what feels like 90 seconds) and always tastes like you want it to taste. It's open so late too. Listen, if you and I are hungry and out in DC, I'm probabl
Loved this place! The pizza was done super quick and it was delish. They have a good amount of seating upstairs. We would definitely come back.

I recently tried 90 Second Pizza, and overall, the experience was great! The pizza itself was excellent—a perfectly crispy yet airy crust, flavorful sauce, and fresh ingredients that really stood out. The speed of service was also impressive, making it a great spot for a quick, high-quality meal.

M
Great Napoleon pizza at a fair price. Dough is delicious. Owner is very nice and there is ample seating upstairs. Parking in that area is tough.
It's not the best pizza in the world, but you absolutely get it fast and you get it cheap. So it's a 5 star place in my books.

Such a cute little French patisserie! I will add that though I, too, am a Poupon, I’m not aware of any connection, so this is an unbiased review. I only went because the patisserie shares my last name (how could I not), but I was pleasantly surprised by the authenticity of the French pastry, and par
Been coming to Georgetown for years and never knew this place existed until the Georgetown Fall Market. I’m so glad I stopped by the pastries are really good! I’ll definitely be coming back!

Pâtisserie Poupon is one of the best bakeries I’ve been to in the US. The pastries are top-quality, and their chocolate eclair is the best eclair I’ve ever had. Their selection of coffee and pastries is wide and very authentic to France. The coffee is well-priced, and the prices of the pastries well

The best service over the phone, and the cake was absolutely beautiful and delicious!   I highly recommend Patisserie Poupon for your special events.  You will be taken care of with utmost care, and  professionalism.

I ordered cassis cake and it exceeded all expectations - it tasted and looked absolutely stunning.  Everyone was complimenting how amazing it tasted and it was all gone before I took any more pics..

Thank you Pattisserie Poupon for absolute deliciousness.

I LOVED THIS RESTAURANT! We went there on Halloween night, and oh my goodness, SO YUMMY. Our appetizer was so delicious I almost ordered another, but everyone told me to save room for the main courses. The service was amazing, they kept refilling our water, and our waiter was super kind and attentiv
This is now my favorite Italian restaurant, lasagna is the best I had in years. Owner Jamal was an amazing host best service I had in a while. My good friend Crystal put me on ❤️❤️❤️🍝

It was a mid restaurant. The food was okay, the main platters we ordered were very rich and a little too heavy, but the bread and dipping oil were very good. The service was also not that good, one of our dishes was forgotten so we just took that off of our bill and the waiter came back to our table
Excellent service, delicious food and a wonderful experience all around - the pasta and garlic bread were incredible

The service at this place is appaling and this is being generous. The server was so terrible when we visited from New York on Saturday 3/29, it was shocking! The kids had to eat, so no choice. The only way he was going to get a tip was to include in the receipt, which, he did. When we arrived, they

I hadn’t been to Shanghai Lounge in years and back then it didn’t leave much of an impression. I was surprised to see the menu now focused on Sichuan cuisine—turns out they have a new chef from Sichuan!

We ordered a mix of dishes, and the Sichuan flavors really delivered:

5/5 Sweet and Sour Crispy
The facility is old and the taste is average below , we pick the fish for $48 plus , it is smell and fire sure dead fish and not worth the value , this restaurant not recommended . Server is fine

Shanghai lounge rocks because it's not trying to prove anything this is freshly prepared Chinese food the traditional way and the ingredients are pretty good love their eggplant love their shrimp love their soup buns and love their service oriented owners and servers that want to make you happy. I a
