By far the best Chinese place in the area. I grew up nearby, and it was a staple for my best friend and me on our Sunday afternoons after having scoured the flea market for anything reasonably priced. The food is consistently rich and flavorful, the staff is always friendly, and the location itself

I had an online order for their crispy chicken, in which I opened it up to parts of the inside being pink. I immediately called them once I saw that, and they offered me a refund. Told me the refund would take a few days, however they ended up lying and saying in my refund receipt that “customer sai
Literally the perfect meal. Healthy. Fulfilling. DELICIOUS. plus the team that works here makes you feel so welcome… I found my spot for this summer, thanks Marco!

Update: Dig Inn customer service reached out and handled the situation professionally and with empathy. I visited the restaurant today and the service was absolutely amazing. They fixed it, the  server was friendly and I’m glad I’m able to enjoy Dig’s healthy food again! I changed my review to 5 sta
DIG restaurant was my first time, and I loved it! The Salmon Bowl was fresh, healthy, full of green energy, and affordable. I’ll definitely be back!

Food was SO YUMMY! HEALTHY! And AFFORDABLE!
Service was EXCELLENT!
Atmosphere was clean and cute and fresh!
It was my first time and I will be recommending

If you think about your health and love yourself, I DO NOT RECOMMEND, definetely. I ordered 1 burger and it came in 20 minutes and it was wrong. Then I changed the wrong burger with 2 slices of pizza. It took exactly 42 minutes for the pizzas to arrive. Pizza was like everything except pizza, it was

For a college campus, it's GREAT!
But, if you're family of or a patient, Epicurean leaves LOTS to be desired.
From empty condiments containers (think salsa, etc) to a confusing online ordering system, there's HUGE room for improvement.
The staff is EXCELLENT, and they'll always make sure you've rece

I’m very disappointed ☹️ they gave me a donut glazed” without glaze, cold brew very regular, the last and oldest fries they have, waiting I ad pickled to my burger I barely see them. The service is pretty bad. I’m just a visitor. I don’t recommend I wouldn’t eat here if I was a student. And on top o

This place is kind of like a food court. There is a grill, a noodle bar and a ‘all-you-can-eat’ like place. The ramen wasn’t that bad. The noodles were great, but the soup was a bit lacking in taste. We also had a meat lovers pizza with fries. They were mid, the pizza was ok and the fries were crisp
Food is not good, not even for the convenience of working next door. This is what i found in my chicken tenders 🤮 absolutely disgusting

I feel like the Fountain Inn might be known more for its cocktails, but the food menu makes it one of the best (and currently underrated) spots to eat in D.C. I’ve visited a few times in the past several months and every time the menu has been new and exciting. Every dish is creative, elevated, perf

The Fountain Inn Restaurant was absolutely incredible! From start to finish, everything felt high-end and thoughtfully done. The menu was impressive — every dish was delicious and beautifully presented. The atmosphere was elegant yet comfortable, and the service was exceptional. You can tell there’s

Did the zero proof flight and was not disappointed. Zach and team made the whole experience. I met almost everyone on the staff as the presented and rotated through. My total purchase was higher than anticipated because of me. Trust me when I say it’s worth every penny. Will go back before I depart

The Fountain Inn delivers an exceptional tasting menu experience: refined, seasonal, and beautifully balanced. Each course feels intentional and pairs perfectly with their incredible spirits program. The atmosphere is elegant but inviting, and the service is warm and attentive. A standout dining exp

Had a great experience at the Fountain for a date night. We did the mocktail tasting and every single drink had a neat history that we learned. We also got back ground in the history of the bar and it's strong ties to DC. I would highly recommend the drinks, food, and the atmosphere!

info.name: KYOJIN Sushi
info.address: 3315 Cady's Alley NW Suite B, Washington, DC 20007

reviews.text: Really enjoyed everything about my experience here. The staff was friendly. The food came out quickly. Everything tasted delicious. The vibe was great; it was a little loud but you could still have a conversation. Great date night or friends night out spot. Not for kids. Paid parking garages are in

What a fun, delicious dinner experience! We had the summer 5 course set menu, and everything was so delicious and well crafted. From the appetizer to the dessert, everything hit the mark on flavor, freshness and composition.

Their special menu item “The Winner” does its namesake justice. It was a d

Harrison was a phenomenal server. He was incredibly attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable about the menu. His recommendations were spot-on, and he made the entire dining experience seamless and enjoyable. The food was amazing, but Harrison’s service truly made our night. We’ll definitely be coming

Went here for an anniversary dinner and had a great time. Food was delicious and beautifully plated. Came really hungry so the small / delicate portions felt even smaller with the big price tag but that’s just the name of the game. Interior is also a vibe. Reminds me of Miami without all the ruckus.

I absolutely love Kyojin. If you want good food, good drinks and good vibes head here immediately.

Kyojin's space is beautiful, modern and upscale. You walk into what feels like a dimly lit lair that opens up into a vibrant bar area along with different rooms that have plenty of seating for dining.

Amazing Indian food! I will say I ate here cause I wanted to cool down from sweating all day from walking. I didn’t realize that medium spice for the lamb biryani meant still meant painfully spicy for a parched person LOL. Amazing food regardless would love to try the mango lassi if I ever do visit

Being vegetarian, we ordered veg Momo's and veg biryani, and they both were super delicious. Veg options aren't significant, however, the available veg options are sufficient. If you are around this area, you should definitely try this small restaurant. Self service.
We are onsite and ordered to-go
The food was really good, I forgot to take a pic at first so ignore the little nibble I took. Overall flavorful, fresh, and satisfying.

My favorite Indian restaurant in DC! Staff is always friendly and welcoming. Food is exceptional! Please try the chicken Tikka masala with the garlic naan! Perfect combo! I'll keep coming back until I try the entire menu! 😅🙏🏼

Red doored Indian food in the middle of Georgetown. Tables are a bit dated. Service: Prompt and friendly who understand the menu. Vegetable Biryani: Well spiced, tasty, veggies were fresh, crunchy fried onions on top gives it more texture. Tikka masala paneer is well spiced, savoury, filling. $16 Bi

A bit of a mixed bag. Love the dimly lit, but warm and cozy atmosphere with the spacious corner booths. Liked the food overall though nothing spectacular. Definitely did not like the service which entailed a waitress that clearly had better things to do than wait on customers, and we felt that vibe

Fitzgerald’s has incredible service. From the moment you enter until the time you leave, you’re treated with great hospitality. The food is also quite good & reasonably priced. The tuna tartar is a personal favorite of mine. The decor is very cozy, & they also have two mocktail options worth checkin

If you're looking for a sophisticated spot to unwind after a long day, look no further than Fitzgerald's. From the moment you walk in you're greeted by a sleek and wholesome interior that sets the tone for a refined and relaxing experience.

But it's not just the atmosphere that makes this place spe

Simply magnificent. We were visiting from Canada and were elated to find Best Lobster Rolls in town; here. We were welcomed by the pleasant staff and the gastronomic options really elevated the entire experience. Thank you for your hospitality and service; we can't wait to come back!

Was here with a couple of friends for drinks and dinner. Service was great. The cocktails were good, too. I had the happy hour Manhattan ($10). We shared some appetizers. The truffle fries is a must.  I also enjoyed the steak tartare.  Overall, a great time.

Absolutely amazing experience! I stopped in on Halloween and ordered a few different baked goods — every single one was fresh, fluffy, and so tasty. They had a fun spin-the-wheel event for Halloween prizes, and I actually won a free baguette! Since I’m not from DC, I passed it along to the lady behi

I was walking on Wisconsin Avenue and saw Fresh Baguette. I went inside just to look at the pastries. Everything looked so tempting that I could not resist having a lemon meringue tart.

All I can say is that it was pricey, but it was worth every penny.

This is a smaller fresh baguette but the pastries  are still delicious. I ordered a mini croissant which is a great size for a sweet craving. It’s probably the first coffeeshop I’ve been at that offered mini sizes! My son can only have alternative milk so the barista made him a chocolate oat milk wh

They have a very nice selection of pastries in a small shop with a couple tables. On top of that, I've had an experience with them ordering two raspberry tarts with no sugar. After the order, they called me to warn and ask if it was fine for me to wait another day, because they didn't have delivery

The raspberry croissant was superb! Flaky, buttery, just the right amount of sweet.
Service was quick and the employees were attentive.
Laila was helpful and had great recommendations!

I took my mom here for her birthday and she loved it!! Mohammed provided excellent service and hospitality. His warm personality, genuine kindness and attention to detail made the entire experience feel effortless and special.

Had a great time! My wife took me here for their Sunday brunch buffet as a birthday treat. Upon walking downstairs, you are right in the middle of it. The staff are friendly, personable, and welcoming. I don't remember his name, but the man behind the taco bar was gregarious and kind. It's always a

What a great experience! A wonderful place to have brunch with friends. There's a TV on one side so you don't miss any sports. There's a nice patio. The food is amazing. This is a perfect place for a very nice brunch. I would suggest making reservations for big holidays and events as I'm sure it fil

Delicious food and wonderful service. All the employees are very professional and fast! Special thanks to the reception lady Lyndz and the waiter Mohammed, you always give your guests a special experience! Many good choices Sunday’s for brunch and during the weekdays

I am a repeat customer of Four Seasons Washington DC. My server/waitress Maricris is the best waitress I have ever seen. Maracis is exceptional at her job. If I am unable to get her probably I will make reservations on another day she is working. The food was first class but the service was 5 stars.

The atmosphere was great, and everything we had - the curry, naan, and lassi - was absolutely delicious. Above all, the staff was incredibly friendly, which made the whole dining experience even better. I'll definitely be coming back!

Very impressed! Great classic Indian fusion and Nepalese. They even have pizza with a Indian twist. It's an informal sit down, where they take your order at your table, but you get your own water, and then pack the food you didn't finish at the end.

The pizza was excellent as was the butter chicken

Fantastic fusion food!!  Honestly the best Indian Asian food I have had traveling the World.  Service is okay.  Not knocking it because we may have gone there during a severe off season (late July in Georgetown).  If you are traveling, must stop here.  Small, quaint, and the food again is beautifull
I ordered the chicken tikka masala pizza. For some reason I never got the tikka masala taste in the pizza. Not sure if the cheese overshadowed the masala taste. I did share the feedback with them.

Overall, this place was pretty good. We had originally wanted to go to yellow, but the line was too long. The restaurant itself is a little awkward because the dining area is on the second floor and it’s a little cramped. The bathroom was a little bit small and did not have air conditioning. We orde

info.name: The Rooftop at the Graham
info.address: 1075 Thomas Jefferson St NW, Washington, DC 20007

reviews.text: The views are gorgeous, the crowd felt fun and welcoming, and the whole place just had that energy that makes you want to stay longer than you planned. Some cocktails hit the mark, but a few felt like they needed a little more love and attention. With a space this amazing, I expected the drinks to s

Great rooftop spot in Georgetown with beautiful views over the city. The drinks are solid and the atmosphere is fun but still laid-back enough to relax. Perfect place to bring friends, catch the sunset, or just enjoy cocktails with a view. It can get busy, so coming a little early is a good idea. So

Beautiful skyline view.
Comfy couch and hightop table seating. Nice decor.
Quick service.
Ok cocktails. Kinda pricey for what we got.
Disappointing hummus. Carrots were not super fresh. Pita was definitely old. They toasted them to make them seem fresh. They were crunchy and not fresh.

We visited this bar twice. Our first visit was in late November 2024, and the cocktails were very good. (We had a  Summer, Evening, and Upper, a Rooftop Express, and a Moscow Mule; all of them were solid.) We returned on a Monday about ten days ago, and the cocktails were, well, simply atrocious. I

Quick service and really great cocktails - although I don’t often drink so don’t have much experience to compare.  I enjoyed the food too but there are only a few choices. Just one bathroom which seems lame given the number of tables. Had to wait awhile to use it. Happy to say I’ve been here overall

info.name: The Lobby Lounge | Cocktail & Wine Bar

reviews.text:
I had such an incredible experience at this cocktail bar! From the moment I walked in, the hospitality and attention to detail made the evening unforgettable.
Danny is truly a master behind the bar—his cocktail making skills are unmatched and every drink he crafted was both creative and perfectly ba

Such a great intimate space to wine down but also have so much fun! The aesthetic is luxurious. As soon as you walk in you’ll be ready to try everything this place has to offer.  The outside patio is like an oasis. You’re going to take so many selfies in the mirrors outside and literally not want to

Cool bar with dedicated employees. We walked into a true speakeasy. What looked like a Georgetown townhouse on the outside, was truly a charming bar with beautiful arched mirrors. The servers were attentive and made sure to personally address each of their guests. When I did not see a drink that app

Awesome experience! A lowkey spot that is worth the trip. The bartenders Brandon and Mike served top tier drinks and service. Mikes knowledge of the different rums showed his love for the craft. I would definitely recommend to anyone to stop by in the Georgetown area!

Such a classy and cozy spot in Georgetown. The vibe is warm and relaxed, perfect for a date night or a quiet drink with friends. Cocktails are beautifully made, and the wine list is on point. The staff are super friendly and make you feel right at home. Definitely one of my favorite lounges in DC

Thank god for this new addition to Georgetown. This is absolutely my favorite spot for fast casual food. It’s clean healthy food at generous portions for a great price. Especially for what you get, it’s such a good value. My favorite is the Korean BBQ beef mixed with black rice, kale, broccoli, eggs

Bibibap has quickly become one of our family’s favorite fast-casual restaurants — and that’s saying a lot, since our daughter has celiac disease and eating out can be stressful. Their kitchen is a validated gluten-free facility through GFFS.org, which gave us instant peace of mind. Safety here isn’t
Pretty good. The Service was great and it was clean in there. My only complaint is the quality of the protein could be improved IMO.

One of my favorites! Bibibop is always fresh and delicious. The staff don’t disappoint they are always kind and helpful. I have been to both locations in DuPont and Georgetown. I wouldn’t compare them to Cava it’s clear they are Asian inspired dishes not Mediterranean. In my opinion, I would choose

Bibibop is consistently one of my favorite spots for a quick, healthy, and customizable meal. The ingredients are always fresh, the portions are generous, and the flavors are balanced without feeling heavy. I especially love how easy it is to build a bowl exactly the way you want—plenty of protein o

info.name: sweetgreen - Healthy Salads, Bowls and Plates

reviews.text:
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ 5/5

Saturday Morning Team – You’re Absolutely Outstanding!”

Food is good. Healthy. Tasty too. You can make your own rice bowls here. The food is locally sourced, clean, green and environmentally friendly stuff. That’s all great. I would recommend this chain. Only issue is it’s damn expensive. I mean a normal person can’t afford this daily. My Whole point abo

The Harvest ball was about half empty.
We order from th

I had an unpleasant experience at Sweetgreen today because of one of the staff members, Cam. He was rude and unfriendly throughout the interaction, with an irritated, almost poker-faced expression that made me feel like I was bothering him just by being there.

What was even more concerning was that
No longer sweet or green :( Do not order in line. I went in person hoping for a change. Once again the lettuce and some of the veggies are inedible beyond wilted and yellow. I picked quinoa instead.

info.name: Taj of India Cuisine
info.address: 2809 M St NW Suite 2, Washington, DC 20007

reviews.text: Went on the day after Thanksgiving with a friend for lunch. The restaurant was empty for the most part. Ordered butter chicken and okra. The food was good. However, the service wasn’t the greatest because the server was quite rigid and rude. That made the overall experience quite unpleasant. Won’t g

Great atmosphere and energy! The staff is very personable and shared their recommendations. I’m excited to try lamb korma!

Update! - The lamb korma (green) was AMAZING, savory seasoning with a little kick! The other dish was chicken curry. It was good, traditional but not as spicy. Lastly, the dess

After a long time I am satisfied after visiting an Indian restaurant. We ordered fried calamari, paneer tikka masala, palak chaat, papri chaat, mango lassi, samosa. Everything was good but the calamari is 100/10.
Excellent service, staff and Atmosphere. Thank you team at Taj of India. Enjoyed the quiet atmosphere, background music and friendly input. The papadum and goat vindaloo were on point!

Great food and service.
Nice menu selection.
It was easy to have a conversation.

For a good bagel sandwich, head to this small cafe along Wisconsin Avenue NW in Georgetown. Walking in on a Friday in June around 10:30am, I ordered right away. Within five minutes, I was downstairs eating the "Georgetown Breakfast," one of five house specials.

The bagel sandwich itself was tasty a

With a window into meow maison and seating outside, downstairs, and a small bar upstairs you should bring a friend to try out Cafe con Bagel. I got the Veggie summer sandwich and the cream-cheese veggie combo was peak. I went outside to watch some kitties sleep and sip my dirty chai and bagel.

A hidden gem to stop by when strolling thru the Georgetown area. Family oriented feel with some delicious delightful treats to offer. The option I picked was a build your own bagel. Which was amazing and delicious 🤤.,

Loved it!!! One of the best salmon bagels I have ever had.

There are some more seats to sit underground.

I got the MELT on everything and egg and ham district on blueberry. They both were GOOD. the melt bagel was greasy so it was pretty messy. I also got a black coffee and it was better than most coffee shops. I get my coffee black. My total was $30
Atmosphere was a 4 star just because it was pretty cr

I enjoyed everything about this bar, the bartenders and wait staff were really kind and welcoming. Providing us with great food/drink recommendations. This is a great spot to go to if you’re in Georgetown, I personally can’t wait to go back!

Visited on a Sunday afternoon to try the craft cocktails and small bites. We were seated in the front bar area near the window which was open and nice with lots of table space for a group. The service was great - Connor was great and was very knowledgeable about the menu providing us with drink reco

Easily one of the best additions to the DC cocktail scene in years. I can usually recreate at home most of the cocktails I try at the majority of cocktail bars, but this spot has some very unique, very complex creations. And most importantly beyond the inventive menu, the drinks are delicious. Well

We came pretty early and didn't need a reservation, but it filled up quickly after so I do recommend making a reservation. We had such a fantastic time at this spot on a Friday night! I really appreciated the hospitality, care and knowledge of the staff. Our bartender was Dylan and he really went ab

Awesome place for cocktail hour!  Sophisticated vibe, relatively quiet.  We absolutely loved our drinks (Queen of the South and Mule's P.O.V)  My husband said it was the best mule he's ever had.  And the mushroom sliders were to die for.  Service was flawless.  We'll be back!

Service was really great. Quiet evening in the restaurant on a Saturday evening. It's located in the beautiful Fairmont Hotel. Their cornbread is a popular item on the menu. I found it to be okay. Nothing I would rave about or recommend. We have the crab cakes and chicken which were very good with t

Had a great meal, served family style, with a group of friends at Juniper and everything was delicious - corn bread skillet, sides, striped bass, herb roasted chicken, NY strip, scallops, crab cakes, steak tartar, and the snickers dessert! Planning a return visit. Tip: meet for cocktails in the cour

The Juniper Restaurant located in the luxurious Fairmont Hotel in Georgetown is a restaurant that you will want to try. I especially enjoyed having lunch there and tasting the seasonal menu while dining in a lovely courtyard setting. Be sure and order the cast iron skillet bread. Tip: As soon as it

If you're looking for a place to satisfy your brunch cravings, then this joint is worth a visit. But listen, if you're not planning on indulging in their bottomless mimosas, you're missing out on life. You better come thirsty and ready to guzzle down at least three of those babies. Note: the price i

My husband and I went for brunch even though we didn't stay at the hotel. It is located inside the Fairmont Hotel, and when you enter the hotel go toward the left of the lobby to get to the restaurant. You may be able to find street parking but if not, you can valet in the hotel garage for $20. The

We were walking around #Georgetown tonight and stopped by and took a look at the menu.  The manager greeted us and asked us if we have eaten here before.  We replied with a big ole Midwestern 'nope'. Then mentioned we did not have reservations.  He said for you.  You do not have to worry.  He sat us

I went with a girlfriend of mine for a leisurely splurge day about Georgetown. Decided on Ristorante Piccolo for dinner on a Friday, walk-in was available as it was just before the dinner rush, and had our pick of the free table in the nook by the window, underneath the stairs. Very cute and intimat

I'll start with the bottom line - most of the food we had wasn't that good unfortunately :/
The ravioli was great. The calamari was made from frozen calamari based on the texture of it, the pizza is just average, the desserts were just below average.
From a place that has been around for so long and

Saw a review that talked about the food not having any flavor, not sure if the chef at the time had a bad day or what, but I can't agree with any of the statements‼️

Some of the best Italian food I've ever had in the United States 👌

Everything is made from scratch, the pasta, sauces, salad dressin

Seriously the best Italian food I’ve had in ages. I got the rigatoni Gorgonzola, and it had the most incredible rich flavor. The blood orange Italian soda was great, too. One member of my party didn’t get his order, and our server was so apologetic. He gave us a fresh pasta dish to take home, two de

Call your mother has got to have the best bagels I have ever had! I ordered the no meat sun city and it was absolutely amazing. It was so warm, it was steaming when I opened it! The inside of the cafe is so chic and cozy. I would definitely recommend checking out Call Your Mother if you are in the D

We got two sandwiches and a coffee, and we liked what we had , everything was okay. However, there are no tables to sit and eat inside; it's take-out only. There are a few benches where you can wait for your order. The colorful and lively decor was nice, but the interior felt a bit old and cluttered

This was one of, if not the best sandwich I’ve ever had. It had fresh ingredients, amazing meat, high quality mayo that had to be in house made, it wow’ed me on all corners. I got the spicy pastrami, the wife got the (I forget the name) it had like pastrami / sofrito and brisket in it … oh my goodne

I got a BEC and a cinnamon latte and both were amazing! If you see a line when you go (which you probably will) trust me it is worth the wait. They are also super efficient and help the line move quickly so it really doesn’t take too long. The only downside is that there is no seating.

Amazing bagel place with a few shops in and around DC, it’s a small business and there is no seating available except outside.
I personally recommend the sun city bagel and latte. Prices are OK and never had any problems in regards with food safety. Must try

I’m usually really picky about where I eat sushi, but this place BLEW MY MIND!!! It’s the best sushi place in all of DC. My bf and I stumbled upon this place one day in Georgetown, and it quickly became our favorite spot during our time in DC!! The owners and staff members are so sweet and kind, the

This is the freshest sushi I've had in the DC area. Portion size seemed just right to me. Wish they had vegetable tempura on the menu, but they didn't so I got shrimp tempura. It was perfectly cooked. I ordered the volcano roll, & it was delicious.

The restaurant has seating upstairs. It's a small

Food: 5 out of 5
Service: 4.5 out of 5
Atmosphere: 4 out of 5
Price/Value: 4.5 out of 5
Overall: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ 4.5 out of 5

Recommendations: Sushi Gold

It’s a very small place, but their sushi are some of the freshest and best sushi I’ve ever had, even better than some of the sushi in Japan. Price is on t

I loved the sushi here. It is an unassuming restaurant.  When you get in, you’ll order and pay first then either take your food to go or get your table assignment and be sent upstairs.   Green tea and hot Sake were great.  Perfect balance for the cold night.  We ordered the baked scallop, baked salm

We have to start off every visit with a Sapporo. This is one of Georgetowns best Sushi. This place was recently renovated but has always given me the feeling of home. The staff is amazing, super friendly and helpful when it comes to making your selection. I find that even on the busiest days you wil

A group os us (all family members) came in on a busy Saturday night for small plates, lots of fun drinks, and plenty of chit chat.  The staff was great!  Very attentive and friendly.  The plates we ordered would be made and come out in relatively quick time and were all piping hot and fresh too.

We

We got 6 things for 2 people and we’re stuffed, the Brussels sprouts and the shrimps were our favorite. The carrots and croquettes were also very good (were sweet tooth’s). The Mac and cheese wasn’t the best but still decent, and for dinner we had tea the olive oil cake which was so good!

We came in for brunch and had a great experience. Our server was informative and attentive. We enjoyed the brunch feast, it was fun sampling many different plates. Everything was delicious. For 30$ each we left with leftovers and were stuffed. I’d love to come back again and try the regular chefs ta

This restaurant offers an exceptional dining Our experience at the restaurant was truly exceptional. Our server, Mauricio, skillfully guided us through a culinary journey that showcased delicate and layered flavors, diverse textures, and freshly prepared dishes. The tapas were a delightful surprise,

There’s a vibe here for SURE! We came on a Tuesday night (before the government shutdown of 2025) and it was PACKED! The music was awesome & the service was excellent! The food was hood to us but I can see some people maybe not liking some of it because it’s not your usual serving sizes. It’s Tapas,

Food is always top notch and the last time I went was maybe in 2010-2011. We went back in November 2025.Nothing has changed which is why it is so charming. The wait can be a bit long so make a reservation. I recommend the Steak Fritas with delicious French fries 🍟, escargo and bread pudding desert.

Someone recommended Bistrot Du Coin and I have to say we were not disappointed. Best meal we had in DC. The menu is both extensive and classic French bistro fare. We had escargots, mussels, and pate to start. My friends had the bouef bourguinon and steaks frites, while I had the cassoulet. They were

The food was out of this world. The escargot and pate was superb. The drinks were good. The place was packed. We asked to sit upstairs. My boyfriend enjoyed the mussels. The service was good but slow because it was so crowded.

Very much was a welcoming place. Lots of seating and decorations. There was a ton of noise though that really made the mood lower since me and my plugs couldn't hear each other. Food was extremely good and I highly recommend it even if the price is really high. It almost made me excuse their fake Fr

French food finally impressed. Fantastic lamb stew. Do not expect much if you don’t eat meat or even if you don’t eat beef / pork. Ambiance is rather gray. Pricing is high. Good wine okay service (also cute little wine glasses!!)

I had a great time at Ala. Harrison, our server, was amazing and made the experience even better 😊
I also had the chance to talk to the chef and was so impressed with his Turkish and international background. You can really feel the creativity in the food 👨‍🍳✨

I tried the happy hour hummus, batata

My wife and I went for our anniversary based off a recommendation from friends. The atmosphere was great both outside and in. The staff went above and beyond. If I could offer any advice, listen to their recommendations for food and drink. We had amazing cocktails, small plates, entrees and desserts

We have been wanting to try this new Mediterranean place. We had an early dinner around 5 o’clock on a Sunday night.The food was delicious especially loved the beef kebab. Pita bread is hands down the best in the area. Everything is fresh and tasty. Service was great too. Outdoor seating is lovely.

We came for restaurant week and had a great time. It was four courses and we added the four drinks to go with it. It was especially nice that they did regular menu items + regular sizes so you could get a sense of what it is usually like. The bread and dips were great, we really liked the potatoes a

I liked the place. Food was good, staff - friendly and knowledgeable.  Plenty of vegetarian options and a good selection of regional wines. While the restaurant tries to position itself as Eastern Mediterranean, it smells Turkish. And one of the managers indeed was from Turkey. Against this backgrou

info.name: Lyle's
info.address: 1731 New Hampshire Ave NW, Washington, DC 20009

reviews.text:
Great for photos/instagram and for young people who do not know class, quality food or good service. Music was inappropriate for the atmosphere. I got the salmon, drenched in salt, and it came with rice that looked and tasted microwaved.

The wait staff need to go through training on etiquette, comm

The place is wonderful however the servers are always hurrying you to order and eat, they want to take the plates and bring the bill asap and is so annoying. Nothing professional from any of the three people who took care of my service. Bad costumer service by also interrupting me in a phone call an

Dishes you wish it would never end - and when it’s up you wish you had room to try all the rest of the menue.
I have been here several times before the menu changed and Chef Jan and his team keep me enchanted and surprise all anew with beautifully displayed flavour combinations.

Meanwhile the servi

The ambiance of Lyle's restaurant was so nice! It was upscale and nicely decorated however, it was also comfortable and casual at the same time. However, the tables were placed INCREDIBLY close to one another. It felt like I was a part of the party that was seated next to us because our tables were

We had such a wonderful dinner at this restaurant. First the service..amazing. Food was tasty, on time and fresh. Ny strip was wonderful.Oysters delicious. Pairing with a great Chianti. The only thing we didn't enjoy so much were the Brussels sprouts. Charred but raw inside. Overall a wonderful dinn

info.name: The Pembroke
info.address: 1500 New Hampshire Ave NW, Washington, DC 20036

reviews.text:
This place is one I can finally check off my list and it did not disappoint! The restaurant was spacious and a great place to meet and catch up with friends. Service was attentive and on point.

We came for brunch. They really good options on their menu.
Chicken and waffles- amazing!! The chicken wa

Had a best dinner on the best restaurant in DC!
Every dish was thoughtfully prepared, beautifully plated, and bursting with flavor. You can really tell the chefs put care into both the ingredients and the presentation. I had Octopus and Green Circle Chicken and it was truly unforgettable.

Service w

The salmon Benedict was sublime. The hollandaise sauce was a slight reinterpretation with brown butter and a viscous consistency that emulated a fine melted cheese. The English muffin was soft and spongy and easy to cut, the poached egg was cooked to perfection. Apart from that, the fresh squeezed o

Me and my husband decided to have brunch here, we were excited to get to eat something savory and delicious, but sadly it wasn’t it. The coffee was great, I had a smoked salmon beagle with cream cheese and confit tomatoes. It was very hard to digest and overall bitter. My husband got a shot of Monte

Exceptional dining experience — a true gem
The Pembroke is an outstanding restaurant that delivers a top-tier experience on every level. From the moment we walked in, everything — from the atmosphere to the service — felt refined and thoughtful.
The dishes served here could easily compete with Miche

My friend and I came here because we were craving a Caesar salad. Wednesday evening wasn’t too crowded. We sat upstairs. There was a weird smell but only in some areas, we sat clear of it. The Caesar salad was out of this world! It was perfectly dressed. We also got a side of the prosciutto board wh

Hard to describe how much we enjoyed our meals here during our visit to DC. Atmosphere is great, people at very welcoming, and the food is off the charts good. Everything we tried was perfection, from appetizers to desserts! The meals turned into hours and the experience was excellent. In today’s wo

Stunning meal! The starter of scallops was one of the best things I’ve ever eaten- we wanted to lick the plate. The pasta was phenomenal, the drinks were great, and the dessert was unique but so well done. I will definitely be back!

Must say we sat outside and it felt as if i was in Europe!! Great service, food was delicious, very fresh and very authentic!  Would definitely recommend this place to anyone visiting DC or living nearby!! DC Gem!!

I was actually walking to another restaurant when I passed La Tomate. The host smiled at me through the window, and it just felt inviting. I decided to check it out. I sat at the bar and the bartender was just as nice. He recommended a great dish, catered to what I explained I was craving. I got the

info.name: Firefly
info.address: 1310 New Hampshire Ave NW, Washington, DC 20036

reviews.text: All of the staff were super friendly. We definitely felt under dressed. I got the eggs Benedict with Smoked Salmon. There wasn't much hollandaise sauce, so it was a bit dry and the Smoked Salmon was strong. Their potatoes and veggies needed seasoning. My daughter enjoyed her french toast. For basic

This was a good brunch spot. The food was wonderfully made. Their club sandwich was the best. The French toast was my favorite. The Mimosa was the finishing touch for my breakfast. The waitress was friendly and attentive.

This place made our short trip to DC amazing!! The service was absolutely outstanding, thanks Andy!!! Every drink we tried was excellent and always had something fun like smoke bubbles or edible butterflies. The ribs were cooked perfectly, juicy and fell right off the bone, definitely try the mambo

Firefly is a cozy little spot that I found on Google and decided to try because it was close to another spot that we were planning on visiting. Firefly is situated in the beautiful neighborhood of DuPont circle ( I think 👀). It's small but inviting. The customer service is great. The food is decent.

I recently had the pleasure of dining at this restaurant, and I can't say enough about how fantastic Chef Red is! From the start, he was genuinely engaging and offered great suggestions from his new dinner menu. Every dish was a 10/10! The shrimp appetizer, which I usually wouldn't go for, had the p

info.name: Compliments Only
info.address: 2029 P St NW Front 1, Washington, DC 20036

reviews.text: My husband was in DC and picked up two sandwiches from Compliments Only and let me tell you… THEY WERE AMAZING! Being Philly-bred and having high expectations, this place did not disappoint. He brought home The Frex and a Crunchy Boi, and both were absolutely delicious — and the prices were super re

My friend and I stopped off for a quick lunch on a busy day.  The Tuna Salad ($10) and Sicky Wicky Club ($15) sandwiches were huge and really good.  Next time we'll just get one and share it with a side.

Service on a Friday afternoon is quick and simple! I got the farmers market after dark - would consider adding the fresh mozzarella or chips next time. The sandwich was great, as was the bread, but oh my god so much shredduce. Packed to the brim and the peppers bring some really great flavor. It’s t

Ordered them at random because my normal sandwich shop was closed and OMG, absolutely worth it.  I had the Vesuvius two first which is in the photo.  The meatballs melt in your mouth and the baked cheese is fresh and has tons of flavor.  Get a buck for the pickle because the juice explodes.  I can’t

Located in the LGBTQ+ community, this sandwich shop is fire. We Bay Area natives love family owned deli sandwiches. No questions about it. Would go back again and again. This store does open face sandwich. I do the Sticky Wicky with no Ham. but that's just me. I prefer the pork belly(bacon), not the

This place was suggested by a delightful local person who goes there every Thursday. From outside it looks like a small place but once you enter you see the high ceilings and the white walls with beautiful Greek photography and historical photos. It’s not cramped and feels airy.  The way you order f

Great location and superior service in a multi-story restaurant with open seating and a quiet atmosphere. Delicious meal. The only reason for not getting 5 stars is that that food was a little more processed than homemade. Unless I can be corrected, in which case I will bump this up to 5 stars.

This restaurant is in such a lovely place.
Two facts:
The food was fantastic, and the service was impressively quick.
However, they played some sad Greek music, which made the atmosphere feel a bit down.
Back to the food, it was absolutely delicious. The portions were small, that make you order more

A great little spot for Greek food. Friendly counter service with all the classics. Food was freshly prepared and the restaurant was clean throughout. The baklava was delicious. They offer a small selection of wine and beer to pair with your food too. Prices fair. Parking may be challenging.

Loved this spot! The food was super fresh and delicious, and the wine and beer selection was on point. The staff was so friendly and attentive—it made the whole vibe even better. Definitely coming back next time I’m in DC!

Such a great experience! The vibe was amazing — the perfect spot for a fresh morning start. The setup and atmosphere were so nice, and the customer service was friendly and welcoming. The toast was delicious and beautifully made — definitely worth coming back for again and again. Toastique really ha

I tried the "OG Acai" bowl and I liked it very much because it was prepared with fresh fruits and arranged appetizing. The place was clean and the order was prepared fast. I got the chance to meet Ferozan, very kind and lovely - she also recommended me to visit the store in California if I have the

I love this place! I’ve been coming here for a while now and the staff at this point feel like they’re my friends. I always order a cortado and it’s delish but I’ve never had the food. Ferozan one of their investors came up and offered to have me try the smoked salmon toast and give my honest feedba

Toasts - YES, Boosters - Nahhh
Smoked salmon toast was on point — fresh and flavorful, the perfect way to start the day without anything greasy or fried.

The pear juice was delicious and refreshing. 🍐 The booster and detox shots, however, were much too sour for both me and my husband. I appreciate
Fantastic service and amazing food. We recommend the smoothies and latte. Rafi was a great server. ❤️ Nice place to come hang out with friends.

I went to Rakuya for happy hour, and it was honestly one of the best sushi experiences I’ve had in DC. Everything was so fresh and beautifully prepared — the salmon roe nigiri and red sea bream nigiri were absolute standouts, but I also loved the Seoul Train roll, branzini, and a few other nigiri pi

Cute restaurant in Dupont Circle. The food was good, but relatively expensive for the overall experience. For reference, we had the Tonkotsu soup and the Yakisoba. As an appetizer, we tried the dumpling soup, which was excellent.

wow! My first time here and I’m DEFINITELY COMING BACK!!! Sit at the sushi bar, it’s a dope experience.
The food is WORTH IT.
Also request Evan as your server. He was dope and attentive. Green Book Approved.

Nothing stood out to me here. The miso ramen was bland, chasu too oily, chicken karaage was fine but the aioli sauce is too mayo-y rather than light to try to take away some of the heaviness from it being deep fried, and maki were only slightly above grocery store standards..

I came in for a quick roll and beer for happy hour and sat at the bar. I got the spicy crunchy tuna roll and it was very good. Quick service and a nice place. There’s indoor and outdoor seating and a pretty large menu. I still want to go back for ramen at some point too.

Jesus was our server, and he went above and beyond! Excellent service!! The food was great the quesadillas and salads tasted great especially the Caesar salad!! The places atmosphere was beautiful very aesthetically pleasing

Jesus was amazing! The best server. We really enjoyed the happy hour & cannot recommend Jesus enough. He’s such a kind person. And the rest of the alero team was great! Really appreciate the atmosphere.

Sep 2025: Almost there if you try harder. Seated myself at the bar around 5:30 on a Saturday. There were 1-2 employees floating in and out of the bar. Wasn’t greeted. After 5 minutes had to speak up to order a drink and ask for a menu. Had to flag someone down to place the food order. I asked for th

Two friends and I went to Alero at around noon on a Tuesday afternoon. The atmosphere is pleasant and we were greeted promptly by our friendly server, Jesús. He attended to ask of our needs and was attentive. One friend has a cilantro allergy and he clearly understood that we shouldn’t have any at t

This restaurant is truly amazing! The food is delicious, and the service is absolutely excellent. Jesús, our waiter, was super kind and attentive, always making sure we had everything we needed. Joel, the bartender, was also incredibly friendly and welcoming — they both made us feel right at home. I

We ordered the Margherita pizza and the Alfredo pasta. The food, portion sizes, and service were all excellent. I highly recommend this restaurant. The only downside was that our table was a bit too close to the kitchen area, so we often had servers passing by with plates.

From appetizers to desserts, an authentic experience. We loved the warm bread basket. The Ceasar Salad was light, crisp and well portioned. The pasta was fresh and the sauce was perfectly seasoned, the chicken was plenty. The potatoe fingerlings were seasoned well also. The desserts were fresh sweet

We’re down in Washington DC visiting for a few days and this is one of the restaurants that I chose for dinner. It was only about a half a mile walk from our Airbnb and the weather is very warm down here so it was a nice night for a walk. As soon as we walked into the restaurant it was very warm in

Food was good. The bolognese was nothing special. I rate this place a 3 star because of the service. The menu states that the risotto with the braised short rib was $38 but they charged us $42. When I confronted them, they said the price was $42. At first, they would not compensate us until I said i
A great choice for Washington Restaurant Week lunch or any time.  A short walk to the Phillips and other art galleries and the Metro.

Absolutely awesome spot. Went during happy hour and it was awesome. The specials were great. The oysters were absolutely amazing. So so so tasty. The atmosphere is very nice and the bartenders were excellent.

We stopped in for dinner on a Friday night and were surprised at how quiet the restaurant was for prime dining time. The space is very clean, modern, and spacious, with a large bar/lounge area and patio out front. Lighting in the dining room is on the brighter side, while the bar area feels warmer a

This restaurant is absolutely top-tier! I've been here four times now, and it never disappoints. In fact, I even had my engagement party here in 2023. The new GM, Mahalia, was fantastic—she answered all our questions with ease. Our waiter, Richard, provided outstanding service, making our experience

This place was amazing! The service was fantastic. We were with a large party and the drinks and food were served quickly. The crab cakes are a must try, but my girlfriends chicken dish was also quite tasty. The menu has a lot of other great options which can make ordering a bit of a challenge, but

Teddy and The Bully Bar is a great happy hour spot.  The drinks are awesome...barrel aged cocktails are a must.  Their variety of beverage options at reasonable happy hour prices was definitely a draw for me.  The oysters are a great price as well for half or a full dozen.  The rest of the happy hou

My father took my wife and I out to Astoria for a late birthday dinner. It is difficult getting a reservation to this place mainly because they only allow you to book one week out. Luckily we were able to get a reservation. We ordered a bunch of items and share them all which is probably the best wa

Went here for a girls night and it did not disappoint

I arrived as a walk in at 5 pm and was promptly seated upon opening for my party of 3 with no issues. If you don’t have a reservation I’d recommend arriving early and walking in

For drinks, we had a gimlet, and 1 of their specialty gin drinks.

This is truly one of the best restaurants in DC, every time I go it is a banger. You must try their salt and pepper eggplant and Dan Dan noodles. The vegan noodles are delicious as well. Not only are their food and drinks phenomenal the staff is a delight! From the hostess, bartenders, and waiters,

Make a reservation! It's very popular and I know why. This was my second visit here. I went many years ago and the high quality is still there. Very flavorful food. Some spicy, be careful. Cozy atmosphere. We sat in the window counter. Service was good and the staff were nice.

Love the rustic railroad style of the restaurant.
I had a reservation and was sat right away.
Service was great , every staff member that walked by checked on me .
I ordered from the vegan options . Noodles were delicious and slightly spicy the impossible beef and tofu was ok and not my favorite.
I

Thai Chef Street Food in DC is a fantastic spot with bold flavors and a lively vibe. I had a great experience from start to finish. The papaya salad was incredibly fresh, crisp, and perfectly balanced with tangy spice. The glazed tofu was another standout—rich, savory, and full of flavor. The servic

Thai Chef Street Food is a decent, casual spot in Dupont Circle. Two people ate for a little over $60 (before tip) and left very full. The crabmeat fried rice was excellent and the only dish I’d strongly recommend. The kapaw was disappointing, and both the chicken satay and tom yum were just average

Tried this place on a whim with my wife and I'm glad we did. Mostly great food - the veggie curry puffs are akin to samosas but the dipping sauce makes it 10x better. The fried rice was refreshingly delicious.

The BKK wings are marked as spicy on the menu but they were very sweet. This is the only

Summer was our Server; what a delight! Their specialty cocktails; Crazy Thai Lady and Elderberry Old Fashion were well made and delicious. The Bikini Shrimp Rolls and the Thai Chef Dumplings are very appetizing. We also shared a Poh Tak Seafood platter; Wow! So tasty.
The decor is cozy and the servi
Came in on a Friday night and got seats within 10 minutes! Everything was delicious - really big portions. Definitely enough to share / have for left overs.

The food was good. We ordered the Birria tacos, a shrimp taco and a carnitas taco. I like the mango salsa on the shrimp taco.

We sat on the patio with our pup. Service was decent, but it would have been nice to get some water for the dog, other places with patio seating are good about offering wate

We hosted a rehearsal dinner for our November wedding at Mission Dupont after seeing their "no venue fees" advertisement in the spring. After inquiring online, Reed met with us personally to tour the loft space and discuss our needs. The F&B minimum was extremely competitive for 20 people, and all o
10/10 Mexican Restaurant. Try the Chipotle Chicken Rollups for the starters. The Spicy Chicken Sandwich was delicious. Also, you cant go wrong with the dinner burrito bowl as well.

A great place to hangout with friends and family. You come for the Margaritas and stay for them. Well made, not watered down. Had a few pitchers. Good Taco’s. Loved the Mango Shrimp. Service was 5 ⭐️. Jake the manager was very hospitable and took extra care of us. Jack our server was awesome. Great

Fun place for happy hour. I'm unsure if it's a good happy hour (comparatively), but I do know one thing---their $5/taco deal on Taco Tuesday paired with a pitcher of margarita for much cheaper than usual is not half bad!

I had "squirrel "fish once at a private Shanghainese restaurant.  I was excited to know this restaurant also provides this special dish. I made an appointment online. I was able to find a nearby paid street parking. The staff were friendly.  I decided to order Mandarin Branzino "squirrel fish" and S

Honestly deserves 4.5 but since we can't give half stars here it is. Food was absolutely delicious especially for someone who is a pescatarian. Plenty of options although would be careful with the traditional choices as the tofu wrapped items are stuffed with meat! My favorite was the steamed shrimp

Incredibly overrated.. didn’t take many pictures but the dumplings were neither traditional nor fusion enough, fried rice had hardly any shrimp and didn’t even taste fried, portion sizes are not for sharing, dong pao pork was the only good dish there. The xiao long bao was good but the dough kept st

What an incredible All-You-Can-Eat dim sum brunch experience! We were a party of 10, which allowed us to sample a large amount of the menu—and it was all fantastic.

A special shout-out to Scott, our "Dim Sum Master," whose service was truly on point. He guided us through the two sided menu and orde

Service: We were a party of four with a reservation. We were seated in a booth and sat for about 8 minutes before I asked if we had a server. Then the server stated I was in my phone that's why he didn't approach the table. While I made a quick call, the same server walked by our table several times

Went for dumpling happy hour on a whim when I was in the area. It was great! Decent prices ($5 for 3 medium sized dumplings), but the real benefit was the taste. I recommend trying each type of dumpling. Very saucy and crispy but perfectly cooked inside. There was only one other person there when I

Ordered takeout from here. Got the chicken fried rice which was really good! It had lovely chunks of bacon in there. I also tried the soup which was flavorful and a good amount of spicy. I’d probably go back and sit in the store. Portion sizes are worth the price!

Do not sleep on this place, amazing! But come with a bunch of people so you can order a bunch of the menu to share. The spring roll was one of the best, killer brussel sprouts. The wings just play compared to it all. Get the chicken main, bulgogi was delicious. The cold noodles was good but not grea

Dumpling happy hour from 3-6pm and plenty of additional delicious options. Loved having locally brewed beverage options and the blood orange gose was perfect on a steamy day. I am delighted to have a new go-to option in DuPont. It’s only two blocks from the Q St Metro stop, too.

One thing that never disappoints is the Chiko dumpling hour. Their sauces are always to die for, dumplings are fresh, and drinks are delicious. Their spiked asian pear cooler is so delicious and super refreshing and combined with the chilled peanut noodles it is really the perfect summer meal. Also

I really wanted to like this place, but the experience was a letdown. They enforce a strict 2-hour dining limit, and when your time is up, the staff doesn’t hesitate to rush you out — it felt very disrespectful. The ambiance is great and the concept is trendy, but the service and hospitality are now

I had such a fantastic experience at Residents Bar & Café! The vibe and ambiance are exactly what I love — cozy, stylish, and welcoming, with a lively energy that makes you want to linger. The staff were attentive, and friendly.

I started with the Watermelon & Heirloom Tomato salad with Persian cuc

Residents has done the impossible! For years my wife has tried to introduce various octopus based dishes and I’ve never been into it, until now. The charred octopus was delightful; perfectly cooked and thoughtfully executed with the chermoula, croquettes and aioli. 10/10. The mini gyros were also de

Had a very cute vibe-y Sunday morning brunch here with my family. We sat outside on the patio and loved all the decorations on the ceiling. Definitely stuffy in the summer though! Most importantly, all the food was delicious! We had the avocado toast, merguez and sweet potato hash, salmon toast, and

Chic Breakfast Spot With a Healthy Kick 🍉🥑

The watermelon & heirloom tomato salad was the standout — fresh, bright, and so addictive I’d order it again on its own. The Turkish eggs were creamy (a little spicy🥵 , so ask for less chili if you prefer mild), and the salmon toast with avocado and eggs w

DC Vegan is a beautiful spot with a pleasant atmosphere and genuinely good service; the staff is friendly. However, I probably made a mistake ordering the meatless meatball sandwich, which tasted quite bland—almost flavorless, possibly made with a commercial brand rather than house-made. Because of

Super delicious food!! We explored lots of fancy restaurants in DC but this place the restaurant where we enjoyed the most. All the items in the menu are exquisite and so delicious. Different from other vegan place, the food is very authentic and can feel the care and love. There are also great sele

The food in this restaurant was absolutely amazing. The seating space is comfortable and perfect for a date or a nice meal with friends. They also have a huge variety of pastries and coffee, making it an ideal spot if you’re looking for a great place to work. Previously, I had this restaurant cater

As someone who’s always been a devoted meat eater and a total veggie newbie, this meal completely blew me away. Every bite was a revelation and a journey of flavors I didn’t think vegetables were capable of. I was also lucky enough to share it with beautiful company, which, paired with the incredibl

Great little vegan italian restaurant. I visited here on a Sunday evening.

If you're visiting on the weekend, seating is generally available and you can even find street parking nearby.

Starter

Mushroom calamari had a nice crunch and it went well with the almond parmesan topping and rich marinara

New favorite study spot in DuPont! I love that the music is chill and not distracting (a mistake that a lot of cafes make), so it’s great to get some work done. They give reusable glasses if you’re getting stuff “for here,” which is always commendable. The lighting is ideal and the inside is very sp

Best Egg, Bacon and Cheese sandwich ever!  Soft poppy seed bun, freshly cooked egg and bacon.  AND the yoke slightly runny...YUM.  coffee and Latte was brewed to perfection.  Great experience here at DuPont Circle

Great tasting food with ample portion sizes! 😋 Truly impressed by the quality! Fun atmosphere and friendly staff. 🌞 Bonus: All Day Breakfast! 🤤🍳 Also, 50% off for furloughed govt workers with Govt ID during the shutdown! 🙏🏻😊

First time stopping by was great! They were out of the cold brew I wanted to try but offered some alternatives which I appreciated. The maple cruller was to die for, 100% melt-in-your-mouth deliciousness. The latte was pretty standard, not a huge fan of $1 up charge for oat milk but otherwise prices

Tried their latte. Egg and cheese sandwich. And lemon blueberry muffin. Was not super super tasty. But still ok.  Near DuPont circle. Good location. Close to metro. Street parking ok too if it is maybe Sunday.

Great Brunch Spot!
Tried this place for brunch and was pleasantly surprised. The French toast was delicious—crispy on the outside, soft on the inside, and not overly sweet. The avocado toast with eggs was fresh, flavorful, and satisfying. Friendly service and a cozy atmosphere. Only reason for 4 sta

We stayed at the St. Gregory over Memorial Day Weekend and was given a $25 voucher to the Ellington Park Bistro each night of our stay. We choose to use our vouchers for breakfast. We thought the food was good - especially the thick cut bacon - as well as our lattes and macchiatos. We also were impr
Outstanding food and service.... the pancakes were unbelievable. The paris omelette is magnificent

Had a great experience at this restaurant ❤️ Such a hidden gem 💎 Made reservation via Resy, when we arrived the hostess greeted us and was very nice, the server was very professional, food, wine and drinks - everything tasted great! We also got a complimentary champagne toast at the end 🥂
Stopped in for Happy Hour.  Enjoyed the baked oysters appetizer and the Old Fashioned's.

info.name: City Tap House Dupont
info.address: 1250 Connecticut Ave NW suite 105, Washington, DC 20036

reviews.text:
I was looking for a place with a large beer list and they delivered. They had 4 porter/stouts, one which I recognized as superb! Overall, they had over 30 beers on tap.

I had appetizers- clam chowder, Brussels sprouts, and nachos. It was a lot of food even for how hungry I was. It was all very good

We had such a fantastic experience at City Tap Bar, all thanks to our amazing server, Alvaro! From the moment we sat down, he was friendly, attentive, and made sure everything was perfect throughout our visit.
What really stood out was how thoughtful he was — we were celebrating my boss's birthday,
In DC for a few days. Stopped in to grab a beer, wings and watch the game. 4.5 stars for this place. Very clean, very nice atmosphere. Highly recommend.

Meal: Dinner
Day Visited: Saturday
Budget: $35
Closest Station: DuPont Circle
Reservation Needed?: No
Payment: Cash; Credit
Kid Friendly?: No
English Menu?: Yes

Solid 4 stars! We really enjoyed the jambalaya! The 10-Spice Wings … a bit less so.

Friendly service. Vibrant atmosphere.

Me and hubby stopped by this place to grab a quick bite. The hummus was good. The wings tasted a bit “old”, but the bbq pulled pork nachos were delicious as well as the elite corn dip. J (our waiter) had to make our drink 3x and once he did bring it back the  drinks were mediocre.

It’s a nice quiet restaurant with great service but that’s it. I had high hopes for this restaurant till I had my food. The food is on par with restaurants like Outback. I personally think even long horn has better steaks for the price. There are much better restaurants in DC for the prices Palm cha

From the valet, to being greeted, to being seated; everyone was absolutely amazing! I didn’t get the valets name, but Angela (our host) and Sayeed (waiter) were absolutely amazing! Very kind and attentive to every need, we didn’t have to request a single thing. And the food was absolutely divine! We

I had high hopes for this restaurant especially since the steak was excellent, the service was fast and friendly, and the ambience was really enjoyable. Unfortunately, finding a hair in my Caesar salad completely ruined the experience. I understand that accidents happen and I don’t believe it reflec

The Palm in DC is a fantastic spot for a top-notch steakhouse experience. The steaks are perfectly cooked, the seafood is fresh, and the portions are generous. The service is professional and welcoming, and the old-school atmosphere , with the famous caricatures on the walls , gives the place a lot

I dined at The Palm on Monday, November 24th, and the experience was exceptional from start to finish. Upon arrival, Angela greeted us warmly with a cheerful and courteous demeanor, setting a positive tone for the evening. Our server, Siad, provided outstanding service—attentive, professional, and c

Absolutely Delicious Burger and Top notch Mac n Cheese!!!!  Staff were super friendly and their service was attentive. The reviews for this place were spot on as all the food was tasty. Definitely get the burger & Mac n cheese they will not disappoint. The patio was very peaceful and inside was cozy

I went here for dinner with a friend and it was really good. I walk by it all the time and I’m glad I finally tried it. You would never know that it is a local chain.

I got the Golden Grain Salad with Chicken, which was apparently a mistake because their burgers are so good. The salad was really go

I’ve gone for bottomless mimosas & happy hour, and both experiences were phenomenal! The prices are reasonable, quality of food and drinks is great, and more importantly, the staff is fantastic. You can tell that they want you to come back and become regulars, which I always appreciate it.
Fun, delicious, and great service.  We come to DC often and this place is one of the best.   They made my burger into a lettuce wrap - yum - and with an egg and bacon. Keto heaven.

My first time at Duke’s grocery and it did not disappoint. Coincidentally went here on national cheeseburger day and their highly acclaimed Proper Burger did not disappoint! They offer it either medium rare or well done I chose the former and loved it! When in DC I will definitely be back at Duke‘s

Starting off with the plantain empanadas really set the tone for the rest of the meal because wow!!! Mind you, I’m not even the biggest fan on plantains (which sounds crazy because I’m Nigerian) but they were so good we almost got another order.

We also got the camarones a la plancha (grilled head-

We visited Amparo Fondita during their special collaboration with 2fifty Smokehouse, and the food was incredibly delicious! It was so interesting the way how version… pupusas were full of amazing flavor and richness.

The restaurant itself has such a delicate and warm atmosphere really beautiful and

Visiting Washington DC for a conference, stumbled upon this place and it did not disappoint! The fish tacos were sensational, we ate some of the best guacamole I’ve ever had and the desserts were out of this world! Delicious cocktails and great value for money. If I could leave more than 5 🌟 I would

First dining here and as a Mexican, this place is amazing. The food was delicious from the drinks all the way to desert. Our server Jerson was very nice and attentive, he explained they have a new menu each seasson, which has be excited. I can't wait to see what's next. I cannot recommend Amparo eno

I absolutely loved having dinner at Amparo Fondita! Our server Jerson was so amazing and the food was absolutely phenomenal. He recommended the best dishes!! Definitely get the barbacoa and the first option for the salad (the one with anchovy dressing- so so good). Will be back!

Lovely restaurant in downtown DC with an elevated sports bar type feel. The food and service was amazing 🤩 The menu wasn’t too big but offered some great selections to choose from. The guacamole was on point!!!  The overall feel of the restaurant was cozy and chill so we really enjoyed our visit.

T

Excellent place to bring a group of friends. Staff is friendly and the space has a great vibe. It was happy hour when my group finished our rounds at a few art galleries nearby. Katie and Kat were great at serving us. I 100% would recommend you have an event or enjoy happy hour at The Admiral as soo

Their events team is great and they're responsive and helpful, making planning super easy. It's easy to reserve the spaces for no fees/minimums and there's very minimal paperwork. Highly r

Food and drinks were outstanding and well-priced, and the atmosphere was excellent also. I and my organization certainly have The Admiral in mind f

The Commodore DC is a great spot for good food and a chill vibe. The comfort food hits the spot, the drinks are solid, and the atmosphere is cozy and welcoming. The staff are friendly and make the experience easy and enjoyable. Definitely a place I’d come back to for a relaxed night out.

The Commodore became our nightly spot while visiting the amazing DC - the bartenders and staff are so very fun and were welcoming to us each time. First time at this location & enjoyed my food. Will definitely be back :) hope to try their other brunch options soon

The service is very good — the staff taking orders are friendly, attentive, and empathetic. The atmosphere is nice, and the food looks very appealing. However, in my experience, the flavor didn’t quite live up to the expectations.

As a Cuban, I went hoping to enjoy a good Cuban sandwich, but honest

Food was amazing the last 2 days we came here. Breakfast sandwich with pork and add avocado was delicious. The plantain chips and dip almost made me cry. Jorge made the customer service rememberable. Good job
The Cuban sandwich is the best we've ever had! So savory, down to the last bite. The empanadas were small, but delightful. And our virgin daiquiri and pina colada were the perfect dessert!

The real star of the show, however, was the food. I ordered the Osso

The is an informal counter service fast food and very small place to eat. The lobster was surprisingly good and plenty of lobster meat that was big pieces. The ladies running the shift during my visit was amazing and had the store running well.
We are from miami. The food is absolutely amazing and delicious! We had two lobster combo. The lobster meat was super fresh and well cooked.

I ordered from a different location here a couple nights ago. It was good enough that I was inclined to order again, and I'm on a special diet right now and lobster is one of the most agreeable things for me,

Most Delicious Lobster Rolls Ever!
Great Friendly Service!!  First time visiting.. would love to have one of these near Orlando, FL..
Organic Maine root soda was added treat!
Loved the Bar Harbor version of the classic lobster roll with 50% more meat which I feel like was a whole tail.  Hit the spot for me after craving one for a while.

My wife and I got the chance to go to All Day Restaurant after church recently. The weather was great so we sat outside. This is one of my favorite restaurants! I love breakfast and brunch food, and Kramers' prices are pretty reasonable. They also take inKind for 20% cashback. It's a bit cramped, though, and the service could use some more training/organization.

Drinks...

Chai latte: Good, though the chai was a litt

My party and I visited your restaurant on Sunday, June 8th at 3:30 PM. We found the cheesesteak sandwich to be a satisfying choice. Honestly the food was mediocre, both pastas needed a lot more seasoning and were quite plain. Same with the pizza. The French toast was nice, and we really enjoyed the homemade soda, even ordered extras of that. I'm assuming the brunch is much better than the dinner options.

It was my first time at Surfside and I was not disappointed! Gracie, Carlos, and the whole team were so friendly and welcoming. Surfside Taco Stand is my go-to spot in DC for tacos. Always fresh, super flavorful, and quick service. The fish and shrimp tacos are amazing, and the chips + guac never disappoint. Chill vibe, friendly staff, and great for a quick bite or late-night snack.

I have a soft spot for any place with a walk-up window, and Surfside nails it. The restaurant is in the hotel and there isn’t any sign outside that tells you where it is. The ambience is pretty nice and it wasn’t crowded on a week night. I really wanted to love the food but thought it was just alright. I am a poke fan and thought the rare tuna wasn’t as tasty as it cooks have

Giving this place a solid 5 stars for unique food offerings, paired with excellent service!!

The Peruvian dish, Polish appetizer, and squash soup were very tasty. Match that with the chef personally serving me while I enjoyed the evening fresh air as I dined on the balcony, simply amazing!  The bar

I had a very enjoyable lunch at Fred & Stilla. Every meal I ordered was absolutely yum!!!
Highly recommend

Food is pretty basic: I had a decent plate of fries (crunchy and perfectly cocked) and a vegan thing that tasted like air, my friends had meat and they liked it….we shared a bottle of wine

Happy to see that there is still a Taim in the DMV. Stopped off after a cruise through the farmers market and a stop at Un Je Ne Sais Quoi. The staff were friendly and service was relatively quick. The sabich sandwich was delicious and the lemon mint ginger lemonade was refreshing on a hot summer da

Very fresh and flavorful Mediterranean fast casual spot. Same concept as Chipotle or Bibimbop next door but with falafel, harissa, lemon mint dressing, kebobs,pita, humus, baklava, and more!
I made my own pita with a side of fries. The fries were mid. But the wrap with the vegetables was so fresh. I
Overall a good place to go and grab a quick bite. I tried the chicken shawarma bowl and picked my own toppings. There’s only indoor seating and it’s open pretty late for the area.

I stumbled across this place. Its in a nice neighborhood. Its super cute and authentic. They have a lot of variety of teas, pastries, and hot food which looked delicious. I decided to get a black Boba tea and the vegan ginger  scones. They were baked fresh straight out of the oven and very amazing!

Such a gem of a spot. Love how cozy the upstairs area is. The croissant I got around lunch was sort of stale, maybe pastries are better in the morning. The ginger limeade was so so good though! A refreshing drink for when it’s hot outside.

This was a unique restaurant we found by accident whilst exploring embassy row in downtown D.C. It was awesome. It had a great selection of teas (as its name suggests) and a fantastic menu of Japanese inspired cuisine. The energy was also great and the staff were friendly and accommodating. My partn

Was gifted the Matcha Sweet Green Tea, Rosy Cacao Rooibos, and Steeping Mushroom Chai from this location -- all three were beyond expectations, especially the Steeping Mushroom Chai (easily my new fav) which is perfectly balanced between peppery/floral.

I love that I can add the Matcha Sweet Green

This restaurant offers diverse cuisine, including Korean, Japanese, Indian, and Thai foods. All were great! I saw someone complained that salmon had no flavor. You should dip it in brown sauce together with kale under salmon.

Good food. Didnt like the menus on my phone but i am old school. Very loud but it is a bar on a Friday night. Lol. The reservoir dog was absolutelythe best.

Very nice inside. You order at a kiosk so you don't have to wait for the staff to help you. It is a little awkward if you ordered a drink to have to walk up to the bar to get it but not difficult to navigate ordering. The staff did disappear and my food sat in the window until it was cold so the ser

Good food and drinks, but the electronic ordering and payment system is a joke!

The food was superb. Great experience at Dog Haus Biergarten Dupont. The Cowboy All Beef Dog Amoroso Italian Roll was excellent, and the service was top-notch. Our server, Edwin, took great care of us. Highly recommend!
Invited to a luncheon here for a group of 12.  Great company and an even greater lunch! The servers were very attentive to our needs. Love the ceiling with the upside down dining table setting.

If you're looking for a low key kinda divey, nothing too fancy spot, then this is it.  We came in for happy hour and thought the $6 bites was a good value, however, the food want all that great.  The mac n cheese bites and chicken tenders were basically frozen meals. And the nachos were pretty basic

Excellent service! Great spot to watch football. The brunch food was soooooo good. I would definitely eat here again!

We really enjoyed our visit to The Mad Hatter. Great happy hour specials. My 9 year old really loves the Alice in Wonderland theme. Food was decent. The Texas style brisket was really good. Service was excellent. We sat in a booth at the back which wound up being somewhat of a mistake as the music i

5 stars for service alone. Food was also excellent. I was here for a group dinner, so we had a prixe fixe menu and I didn't get to choose from the larger menu, but the options were great anyway. The ginger squash soup was particularly good. I also had one of the best aviation cocktails I've ever had

Annabelle was one of the best dining experiences we've had in 2025. Annabelle provided one of thee BEST restaurant experiences I’ve ever had!

Delicious food, excellent quality, and such a warm ambience. A perfect spot for a date night or a birthday dinner with friends. The hospitality was wonderful — I’ll definitely be back!

The atmosphere has a great vibe to it and is great for private

The staff are so nice and welcoming. The French toast is so fluffy and delicious. Genuinely the best French toast I’ve ever had

info.name: Doyle
info.address: 1500 New Hampshire Ave NW, Washington, DC 20036

reviews.text: The espresso martini with the custom white chocolate foam on top is EVERYTHING! I went here for a ladies night and we were not disappointed. The ambiance is perfect for a date night, girls night out or even a dope study spot. The food was amazing, we will definitely be going back.

Liv is the absolute best. If you’ve forgotten what great customer service is, please come visit Doyle. I had forgotten how great it feels going out post Covid and the food is great. My fish sandwich was delicious.

Favorite bar in dc! Staff is great, especially Betty (who has worked here for 10 years)! I’ve been coming since 2018 and their drinks are consistent and really good. I get the old fashion, espresso martini and dirty martinis. My favorite food item is the kale Caesar with steak. Highly recommended.

Everyone was ordering drinks in outdoor patio. We opted to share a dessert. It was chocolate mouse with whipped cream and cherries. It lacked chocolate flavor. The cherries were good  presentation lacking. Would’ve preferred cherries on top.

It was absolutely beautiful with a warm and welcoming atmosphere. Everything from the decor to the ambiance was just perfect. I tried the trio— tofu, coconut shrimp, and fish — and each one was bursting with flavor. Honestly, I wasn’t expecting them to be that good, but they blew

I most enjoyed the oyster mushroom taco and tofu taco.

Friends recommend that I try this place for tacos, especially because they have diverse vegetarian options. I ordered the Chickpea, tofu, and oyster mushroom as a trio.

Initially, I most liked the tofu taco because it had a great variation of

Potato mac salad was as expected- pretty good. The pineapple upside down cake at the end was very good. Mos

Great portions and delicious tacos. The blackened salmon and pork belly are my favorites. The brisket taco was also delicious! The kalbi beef is good but a little one dimensional. The island fish is more mild but very good. The malasada donuts were great as well.

I have eaten here many times with friends. It is a great quick option that’s fairly affordable and has delicious Thai food.

This time I ordered the Chicken Nua Pad Pik, which is hard to find on the menu but tasted really good. My friend had the Panang Gai Curry - which also looked pretty good.

If

Golden Age is a fun old school DC restaurant with an almost speakeasy type vibe and fantastic cocktails.  Definitely take advantage of their happy hour.  I recommend having a reservation, but we arrived shortly after they opened at 5pm and were able to snag a table for two.  Their food menu is just

Had a wonderful time at this bar. The cocktails were expertly crafted and the food was delicious. The live music created a charming and inviting atmosphere and the service was outstanding. We truly felt like we were among friends and family

Fantastic spot! The drinks are to die for—try the spicy bees knees!— and the food is great. The atmosphere is perfectly moody and the music is good and played there perfect level so that it can be enjoyed but it is still easy to hear conversation with your party. So even though it was after 10pm when I arrived, I could get a full delicious double patty burger. Unfortunately, I ate it
