I have been going here since 1991. Hands down the best sushi in the DMV! I will not waste money on any other sushi! Always friendly and quick service! Has been run by the same very sweet woman since I have been going there and she has a great memory! Always fresh and tasty! I wish they would reopen
My favorite sushi spot. Great quality for the price. The spider roll is my favorite sushi ever. Perfect spot to come with a couple friends and hang out.

My favorite sushi restaurant in DC for their reasonable prices & high quality sushi. This is our monthly date spot. The interior is relaxed/casual (albeit can sometimes get a bit noisy during peak hours) & the service is always great. Will keep coming back!

As someone that grew up in Tokyo, this place serves great quality sushi that’s very authentic! This will be my go to spot from now. I don’t even mention the finger licking baked
Perfect place to go for breakfast. The chicken soup is chunky, the sandwiches are rich in toppings, and the cold brew coffee has a wonderful aroma. Slightly pricey but worth it.

Cute little cafe and easily accessible. Love the ambiance. It can get pretty cramped around the takeout area, though. The pastries are lovely, but I wish they had more options on savory pastries.

I visited this spot on Sunday to celebrate a friend’s birthday, and I’ve had it on my DC bucket list for a while. The vibe is very cool — beautiful décor, fun lighting, and an overall trendy atmosphere that makes it perfect for a night out.

A great spot for happy hour deals. I ordered the bok choy and sushi off of the $7 menu and both were simple yet tasty. I did not eat it all after the first 2 rolls!!! Chicken dumplings was plated beautifully and i feel like you can't screw that up. My

info.name: Station Kitchen & Cocktails at The Embassy Row Hotel

reviews.text:
We stayed at The Embassy Row Hotel a couple years ago and visited the Station Kitchen a couple times.

The restaurant seating area is well designed and attractive, with a trendy and slightly chic decor. You can purchase coffee and light bites to eat in the morning which can be eaten at the restauran
Superb nice bartender. We were doing a ‘pit stop’ from our exploration of walking around the area. Had draft beer and it was good. Nice place to rest and relax and helpful bartender.
Love everything.  Great coffee,,good food, nice service

My family and I came and were served by MJ. When I say we loved her, I mean it! That girl knows the menu, had great recommendations and was extremely fun. I had the shrimp and grits w/the lobster tail. I want to try something else next time but it was so good!

5 stars all around. This restaurant is black owned, food is delicious, service is A1 and fast. Inside of the restaurant is beautiful as well. Good vibes. No complaints at all!!! Perfect for birthdays, anniversaries, or just for fun. Forever will be a customer.

If you’re looking for a quiet spot to eat in Dupont, this is it. The food is solid, the sandwiches really hit different, and the service was even better. Prices are reasonable. They did make a small mistake on my order at first, but they fixed it quickly and handled it well. Great service overall.

We didn’t try the food here but the coffee was wonderful! The people who served us were friendly and helpful. The inside (where we sat until outside chairs became available) was clean and cool temperature wise. The outside was shaded, comfortable and clean.

Damn good sandwich joint in North east DC. Will be back, God willing. Expensive but worth it. Turkey avocado club no bacon extra turkey. And tuna Sammich bangs! Chip selection plenty! Tremendous taste.

I really liked their kimchi burrito the first time I went. However, the second time I took my friend and we both ordered the kimchi burrito. We took it to go and when we went to eat, we saw that they gave us the wrong order (2 breakfast sandwiches).

I contacted Prego Again via their form on their w

Prego Again is one of my favorite cafés in DC. It’s right in Dupont Circle and has such a warm, inviting ambiance. The kimchi burrito is absolutely incredible — technically big enough to share, but I always keep it to myself. It’s consistently made to perfection every time.

The staff are friendly a

Muncheez in DC is a great stop for fresh, flavorful bites. I had the falafel and it was crisp, tasty, and made to order. The ingredients felt super fresh, the seasoning was on point, and the vibe is casual.
A perfect spot for a quick, satisfying meal in the city.
They gave us some nasty old drinks, and wouldn't give us a new one or our money back. Plus, they don't even have a manager there, which is against the rules in DC. We're gonna...
The food was good and the service was even better. Shout out to Eric for making the experience enjoyable and being patient with us.

We have been coming to this restaurant for over a decade and the food is always spot on. Even when I had an issue, the owner Abbas went above and beyond to resolve it promptly. Much appreciated! My family loves this food as it reminds us a lot of the food we had in Lebanon when we visited a few year

I had a bad experience at this restaurant. I asked for spicy sauce, and the staff member responded in a very disrespectful way. After I ordered a chicken shawarma, I tried to add sodas to my order, but he refused to serve them. The attitude and lack of basic customer service were really disappointin

This little gem in Washington DC is another diamond in the rough that many have looked over. The food is authentic Chinese cuisine like your momma made it. It was hot fresh and tantalizing on my taste buds. If you live in DC what are you waiting on to drop by this small but quaint little gem. The se

Got a few items for carry out being hopeful that the current 4.3 stars was not that bad. Especially because it’s hard to find any halal Chinese restaurants in DC. But unfortunately in my kung pao chicken there was some sort of egg shell or plastic? Unacceptable. It’s like inside the breading of the

Just had lunch at New Dynasty Restaurant in D.C. last year (just remember to upload my documentation.lol) and honestly, it felt like a hidden gem—especially if you’re craving Asian flavors that hit close to home. As an Indonesian, I’m pretty picky with taste, but this place delivered!

One big plus:
The older man and I believe his wife were the sweetest and nicest. Food was great, service was pleasant, everyone that sat down or came to pick up was nice.
Great yummy food and many variety in menu. The owner is nice and offers  fresh spicy chili from his garden 😋  yummy! Love fortune cookies 🍪

I've been here a handful of times for dinner and although it's always been a great experience, somehow it keeps getting better and better each time I go.

Some of my favorites:

✅ Empanadas with a flakey crust and a delicious ground beef filling and dipping sauce.

✅ 🗣️ Ceviche Tropical 🔥🔥 Just do y

I had my Birthday party with VIP entrance and everything was reserved on time. In general we had a great time, started with bar at May flowers,  ending with Zabbie's separated place to dance for us. It was fun

Aesthetically this restaurant is spot on. It is decorative, fashionable, and detailed pleasing to the eye. Prepare to spend all your money here; the portions are small but pricey. Everything was great except they were filming a reality show during our visit so this came with restrictions and delays.

Me and my husband went to this club for the first time on Halloween and I will say at first we were not happy with the long line , we were at the point were we just wanted to go home but once we made it to the front we were nicely greeted by the bouncer with the glasses who complimented our costumes

I went for my birthday dinner. I was so excited after seeing all the tiktok  videos and I was honestly disappointed  because i think my expectations were too high. The food was just okay. I did enjoy the lamb chops but i didn't like the potatoes they paired then with also the portions  were on the s

My partner recommended this café. Let me just say that the atmosphere was wonderful and the café was absolutely stunning. They have menus in the front so you have time to choose what you want to eat in advance. Ordering is very quick, they ask if you want to dine in or out. We decided to dine in and

Great coffee spot—went back 4 times!
I tried their cappuccino, iced americano and lemon tart—all so good. The coffee was smooth and strong (in the best way), and the food was fresh and tasty every time. It became my go-to while in DC!

Great place for coffee and cake.
It looked fairly busy but didn't take long to get served and receive my order.
I had the cinnamon rose, which was really nice.
Plenty of seating inside.

Very popular place. It was slamming when I visited on a Tuesday morning. Outside seating was very available but that’s likely due to the fact the heat index was over 100F even at 9am. Good shade for outdoor seating, though. Overall a good experience.
Really good drinks and a great selection of pastries and cakes. Well worth the visit.

Positives are the staff here are amazing and friendly and super helpful and the vibes in here are dope.

The con? The portion sizes are small as hell and the prices just are not worth it.. I paid $26 for a small burger with no fries…. That’s just crazy…. $20.00 for 3 tacos ? That’s just ridiculous.

What a enjoyable dinning experience for restaraunt week. And although we did not chose the menu, we had a extent opportunity to experience some of the best dishes. Lamb gets 5 stars and the sides are eneough to share for a table of 4. Desserts were very good and service was attentive and timely. Oth

The duck carnitas were very delicious. The brunch menu seemed a bit limited and not many non-alcoholic options! The atmosphere in the restaurant was great, but the server may wish to speak less hastily … especially after we’ve asked her to repeat herself … at the end of the day we go for brunch to e

First off we had the best experience because of Emily! She's full of fun energy and very knowledgeable about the entire menu.

Their menu is designed for family style so we ordered a little of everything. Steak Tartar, crab risotto, brussel sprouts, lamb, pork, and scallops. Emily suggested a chenin

Super nice dinning area around the Eastern Market. The duck fat home fires were so good! Definitely recommended. We ordered the duck carnitas, the cinnamon roll, and the brunch burger!  It was all so delicious! Love all the style of the indoor and outdoor dining area.

I’m surprised I’ve been here and not left a review before because my experiences have always been DIVINE. This place is worth the drive every time from Virginia.

I highly recommend a reservation and keeping an eye on their system for the time you’d like. It’s easy to book through Resy!

Now the exp

I’ve never left a review before, but after the kindness and hospitality I experienced, paired with a menu full of flavor and personality, I knew I had to!

I was in town on a solo trip to celebrate my birthday — I’ve never had a fine dining experience before, but I decided to treat myself because th

Absolutely loved our experience at Rose’s Luxury! The food was outstanding — creative, flavorful, and beautifully presented. The staff were genuinely warm and made us feel so welcome from start to finish. Every detail, from the atmosphere to the service, made the evening unforgettable. Truly one of

Incredible experience here twice! Most recently went to celebrate my anniversary, did the "choose your own adventure" menu at the chef's counter. Delicious options (famous pork & lychee salad is a MUST), good portion sizes, and top notch service (big shout out to Lindsay S. for making our celebratio

I was gifted a dinner here and two of my adult children and I arrived for a Thursday evening service.

The setting is beautiful, like an outdoor courtyard, but inside! The staff was welcoming, energetic and friendly.   Throughout the evening, attention was showered upon us with each new course.

The

This place is the perfect spot to unwind after a long day of exploring Washington, D.C. We ordered two cheeseburgers with tater tots, and everything was absolutely delicious! The atmosphere is charming and nostalgic, with its vintage decor. They offer both indoor and outdoor seating, so you can choo

We came form SC and happened upon this gem while in DC. The food was delicious. Atmosphere super cozy. The wait staff was top notch. Friendly, knew their stuff and even suggested some places around town. All the staff have been there 10+ years which says volume about the way a restaurant treats thei

The food is amazing! I must say for my first time eating here that was the best patty melt and home cut potatoes everything was good the coleslaw was amazing as well! The staff is very friendly customer service was definitely giving and on point I highly recommend Mr Henry’s restaurant and will be b

A true gem of Capitol Hill. Mr. Henry's is such an iconic place in DC history. And on top of that, it's got great burgers. We come here pretty often and love the patio. A tad on the pricey side for the food you get, but the vibe totally makes up for it.
This is a great local bar and mecca for new jazz and music talent. Roberta Flack was a regular performer. The food and drinks fit into the breezy and friendly atmosphere.

info.name: Barrel
info.address: 613 Pennsylvania Ave. SE 2nd floor, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text: Went here for brunch. The food was so good! Got the honey butter chicken biscuit and that honey butter was delicious. Also did the brunch fried rice which was good and well seasoned. The bottomless deal is good where it is $28 per person and they leave a champagne bottle and juice at the table so yo

We hosted a private whiskey tasting at barrel this past weekend to celebrate a birthday and it was a phenomenal experience. Matt was so easy to work with in planning a great experience from start to finish - securing a date, planning the slate of whiskeys to taste, bringing in some special bottles f

If you love bourbon, this is the place to go!! I only drink bourbon and there were so many choices and I finally got found a Little Book that I've been wanting to try, I was the first person to try the bottle. If I lived in DC. I would go there again. The bartender was amazing and made my visit an e

Decided to try this after a work dinner. The bar has a great atmosphere for the bourbon scene.
Quite a selection with a menu almost too big to review it all.
The bartender was very knowledgeable and explained our options well.  We asked for suggestions and he didn’t lead us astray.
Seemed reasonably

This experience was great! While the food was below my expectations, our server was Connor and his aura made our experience that much better. He was very polite, professional and simply a great spirit to have during your dining experience. He suggested that we come back during a Sunday brunch and lo

We went for our 35th anniversary and I must admit that it was the best dining experience I’ve had ever. We sat at the chef’s counter. The dining experience feels like an episode of The Bear. Truly a remarkable time. The dishes were absolutely fantastic. The explanation of the foods being served and

Lively atmosphere, excellent and inventive menu gorgeously presented and plated, and friendly and engaged service combined to make P&P a unique and highly enjoyable experience.

My only issue was that I waited about 35 mins past my reservation time to be seated, and the foyer backed up quite a bit w

From the moment we walked in, Pineapple and Pearls made our anniversary feel truly magical. Every detail was thoughtful, every course a revelation. The team somehow manages to strike that rare balance of warmth, creativity, and polish—making you feel both completely at ease and utterly spoiled.

As

When I reserved dinner here, I was slightly apprehensive. After all, there's an upper limit (for us at least) where the quality of the food/service only reaches a certain point financially.

I am thoroughly pleased that we chose Pearl and Pineapple. In fact, I would eat there again. Not only was the

It’s an event from the greeting at the front door to getting home and realizing how amazing the gift is they give you at the end. We picked our dishes but also shared bites around the table and everything was a hit. Seems to be a lot of focus and intentionality coming out of the kitchen here and it

We had breakfast twice during our visit to DC, and we absolutely loved it! We tried the Mixed Berry Ricotta Pancakes, Chicken + Waffles, Big Mark Breakfast, and Thick-Cut French Toast. The hash-browns were crispy to perfection, and the Brown Sugar Cinnamon Ted’s Tart was an incredible homemade treat
Ambiance wise my favorite Ted’s the building has a lot of character. Their fried corn bread is a MUST. Absolutely delicious. Their mixed drinks and happy hour are awesome.

I ate there twice! The first time, I had the Chicken and Waffles for breakfast!! It's a classic American dish. It was sooo tasty, but the portions are huge!! The same goes for the milkshakes and the chocolate cake. Everything was very tasty!! And the service is also great.

Last night we sat outside for the beautiful breeze and perfect temps. We so enjoyed our cocktails and appetizers and our entrees were outstanding! Will is exemplary in his service with a warm friendly conversation and set the atmosphere for fun! You cannot go wrong here! Greek salad with shrimp adde

The best coffee in DC! The “Cinnamon Toast Crunch Latte” is a must-have if you visit Ted’s Bulletin. For breakfast, this place absolutely crushes it with those Crab Benedict eggs, super tasty! They could improve the sourdough bread, it’s a bit too dense and not as flavorful as expected. IG: @framini

Service was excellent! José took very good care of keeping our water filled and drinks coming at a great pace.

The starter chips and nacho appetizer were delicious.

The cocktails were very well mixed and balanced, with a wide variety of options.

The food was spectacular, well cooked and seasoned

Stopped by Los Caballeros in DC and really enjoyed it! I had the nachos and my coworker tried the enchiladas – both were flavorful and well-seasoned. The atmosphere makes it a great spot to grab happy hour drinks after work. Definitely worth checking out!

Best Mexican restaurant in DC and let me tell you about what I had to eat. The Gambas appetizer was great love it and then Mariscos Soteados was on point great flavor and the Margaritas the Crocodile Margarita that had me going for second and third. Great service and best experience and I highly rec

We had the best time at this restaurant. The food was incredible. The drinks were refreshing and delicious. The staff had the most wonderful and welcoming vibes and really added to the experience we had. The next time we are in DC we will definitely be coming back. Highly recommend!

I took my parents here for lunch after seeing the restaurant recommended on Reddit. My mom has been in pursuit of a good chicken quesadilla — she finally found it! My dad had the same and also enjoyed. I had the Pollo Encebollado. It’s amazing how delicious a simple dish can be if done right. Will d

Went here for brunch with a few friends on their recommendation and it was very delicious. It is a true Belgian cafe with a full waffle menu!

I got the Fresh and Simple waffle which was LOADED with fruit and absolutely delicious. I got a side of eggs as well. My friends got interesting items, inclu

Had a light brunch? We both only ordered one dish. And the total came out to be $50 quite high, but understandable for area.

The skillet I ordered was quite nice, with the meat, sauce, eggs and potatoes meshing quite well. However, the fruit waffle was not only quite small, but it felt a bit insult
Everything is great! The dishes and coffee were super delicious! Great atmosphere and great food here. We definitely will back and try more other dishes.

Great service, very friendly staff. Knew nothing about Belgium cuisine so I kept it safe by just getting mussels, which were delicious. Friend got salmon which she loved. Will be back to try other dishes
Yum!  The chocolate mousse was amazing.  The other food was great too.  The cod was cooked perfect and the sauces were much better than I thought they would be.

Any bar that hosts a Survivor premiere party is good in my book! It shows that they are committed to safe spaces for different communities.

Along Barracks Row, as you are is in a larger building with two floors. The top floor is where they have events.

The staff are friendly and often host regular
Such an awesome spot. Great music, great service, solid happy hour & good bar food. We played monopoly deal and just vibed. Will definitely be back.
Not the gay bar refusing to play Reneé Rapp. The DJ played music for themselves. Literally not a single person was dancing but the two people in the DJ booth. Food and drinks were good though.

I am so freaking happy that they finally opened! And the food! Is. So. Good! Real simple menu but my gosh, the portions! The small bites are entrees and the sandwiches, didn't have one but they looked and smelled amazing. These nachos are by far the yummiest I've had in a while. A good solid place t

One of the most fun bars I’ve been to in a long time! First floor is open table seating and serves food. We did not eat while we were there though. Music was fantastic, drinks were appropriately priced and had a good spirit to mixer ratio.

I recommend this bar to anyone who wants to go out for a ni

I visited here on a weekday and was surprised by how full and lively it was. This is a cool little bar with elaborate decorations and plenty of seating.

They had a huge menu and I believe they serve breakfast all day. Some of the items seemed a bit pricey, but there’s plenty of inexpensive items to

Really enjoyed our visit to this traditional American-style bar. The mozzarella sticks were absolutely amazing…highly recommend! The Philly cheesesteak sandwich was also a real treat. Service was great throughout. The only downside was the lack of a baby changing area. Would recommend
Very nice atmosphere, wonderful staff, incredible Mozzarella sticks. A nice place for a date or to hang out with friends. Lots of seating.

During our visit to Washington, our family had the pleasure of dining at this remarkable restaurant. From the moment we walked in, we were captivated by the atmosphere — the interior breathes history, with the establishment dating back to 1946. We spent quite some time admiring the vintage photograp

Unique, quirky, true hole in the wall with class. First of all, thank you to the amazing wait staff who handled a bust night amazingly.
This was a DDD stop and after eating the food I understand why. The mozzarella sticks are a MUST.
If you are nearby, this is worth a stop and you won't regret it.

info.name: Little Pearl
info.address: Carriage House, 921 Pennsylvania Ave. SE, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text:
Overall good experience but I do have some notes!
First course was the angel egg and asparagus tart. I absolutely loved the angel eggs, the white meringue like part had a sweet after taste that balanced the creamy yolk part perfectly. The asparagus tart may have been the star of the entire night, th

A charming gem set back from a main thoroughfare in the city. Everyone was friendly and the service exceptional. The food and wine pairings were amazing, and they easily accommodate dietary restrictions.  They change the menu every few weeks, so it's something to experience at least seasonally.

We’ve had an incredible and special experience at Little Pearl. It’s one of those places where every detail is thought of but it’s also very spontaneous, not pretentious and super relaxed. The food is awesome, what a menu ! The beef salad, the kind of egg flan and the medjhoul dattes dessert were in

We had an absolutely fantastic meal. We love Pineapple & Pearls and Rose’s Luxury, and Little Pearl didn’t disappoint — everything was delicious, beautifully prepared, and impressively inventive. The team went above and beyond to accommodate a pescatarian diet, and every dish was spot-on. The staff

This was from a year ago. 2-3/8 dishes were exceptional!! 1 terrible (okra) and rest were ok. I'd say the non-veg person had a wonderful time/ absolutely loved the food. Can't say the same for vegetarian versions. Great experience but will not go again.

If you eat meat- you'd love this place. See t

We had a good experience at Sonoma. The food was tasty and well-prepared, and the service was friendly. That said, the portion sizes felt a bit small for the price, so it did seem slightly overpriced. Still, it’s a nice spot if you’re looking for quality over quantity.

Stopped here for dinner. Not too busy, which was good. The waitress was very nice. She told us that pizzas were taking longer to cook that night. Lots of options to choose from on the menu. I had the angel hair pasta that was dressed in olive oil, grilled chicken, chili flakes, and crispy spiced zuc

Came with the family as a spring break trip from Florida. Were served super fast ! But the food - was delicious !! Every single thing I have tried was good. Cheers for the staff and the cook! Best food I’ve tried in Washington!! The staff , the food. Not sure how else to say thanks besides a tip. Th

Event Venue Review - Sonoma is a gem, and so is their event manager Hilary! I'd highly recommend Sonoma as an event venue, especially for nonprofits. We love the Avenue Lounge on the 2nd floor, as well as the meeting space behind it, and we will continue to book as often as the team will have us!

While the restaurant certainly strives to present a welcoming atmosphere, the overall dining experience fell short of expectations. The service, while not unfriendly, could be best described as perfunctory, lacking the warmness. As for the food, it regrettably did not live up to the promise of its d

I was promised it would be the best burger I've ever ate but I have to say it was so much more. The Smashburger was the best I've ever had. The fries were amazing. But the shake, the Chocolate shake was the best I've ever tasted. Holy cow. I wanted to stay and try all the flavors. We came in a large

Specialty burger shop with plenty if indoor seating and a few outdoor tables.   I ordered the patty melt and it was cheesy and tasty but was a but lacking in size for the price.  The hit dog looked like a better value for a filling meal the price as compared with the burgers.

This is a great spot for a quick bite to eat, and it has fantastic shakes! The burgers were stacked high, and you definitely feel like you are getting your money's worth. And I want to repeat just how good those shakes are! Don't stop by Good Stuff without getting a shake.
Lots of people eating here. Okay prices. But the burgers were a little small. The hot dogs were bigger and cheaper. Both tasted good though. I think the fries were the best part of the meal.

I had really high hopes walking past this place in the morning,  went by for lunch.   Fries were undergone and limp/soggy/soft.  Needed about 90 more seconds in the fryer.  Shake left a plastic film like aftertaste and I couldn't drink more than a 3rd of it.  Unfortunately no good stuff for lunch to

We are in DC for a vacation and a local told us about this restaurant. She said that the restaurant for some decent bar food. The wait staff where awesome and gave good recommendations. We actually came 2 days in a row.

Day 1, I got the wings wearing Buffalo and Old Bay with inside of fries and my

Been here a couple times and it’s always had a great little pub feel with food to match. Always order the fish n chips cuz they have been delicious and can count on a good thing but family has ordered burgers along with other items without disappointment.

We decided to stop by on a Saturday for brunch before visiting the Eastern Market vendors...the French toast and eggs Benedict were outstanding! Side dishes were delicious as well!  Will definitely return😊
A very high quality Guinness and maybe the best crab cake sandwich that I've ever had. Great for watching sports too.

Good atmosphere and location. Stopped in for breakfast with family. Cocktails were served within 10 minutes of ordering. The servings are plentiful and very tasty. Really enjoyed the French Toast. The smoked Gouda Mac & Cheese w/sweet cornbread reminds me of home. Price point is perfect.

We were walking past when they offered us free samples of delicious chocolate that we couldn’t pass up. We ended up buying ice cream, their hazelnut chocolate bar, and a free cookie for each kid. They were so kind to us, (shout out to chi-chi!!) Overall, a great experience.

The most sweet and loving people take care of this place.
Such a chill environment and the drinks and food is real good.
I super recommend come and chill over here
I will come back

I love this place, it’s right by my job and gym. They have really great coffee and breakfast sandwiches. But the real star is the chicken bacon ranch sandwich I had today after the gym. Lorenzo did a great job crafting it and was super friendly!
Got this huge salad for around $14 sooo happy and satisfied , love the selection in the store too

My tomato caprese was excellent however I paid for additional walnuts and I didn't get it on my sandwich. I'm willing to change my star rating to 5 Star if I can get what I ordered right the first time

One of my favourite places in DC - reminds me of home (england/europe).

Cushions with the union jack, pictures of the Queen, 1920s british posters, melted candles, and old fashioned seats make it a wonderful mix of a stately english home, a parisian smoking club/upscale restaurant, and a pub.

Alwa

Service here is phenomenal. Prices are great. Had their bacon and waffles. Bacon is thicker cut and yummy, the waffle was kind of dry however. Needed more butter, more syrup, and more fluffiness. Love the atmosphere! Espresso in my latte was pretty tasty.

Republican hangout/hotspot. Nuff said.

Why does that matter? Well generally because Republicans are anti working class - shifting more and more taxes from the rich to the working class. And the working class can't afford to uphold an entire govt - the rich can - but don't want to and now they don't

Had a delightful meal. Greeted by a super friendly host who graciously took my wife's coat. We then dined in the little window jet out. The atmosphere was calm and fun. The quirky furniture added to it all. The meal was absolutely delicious from start to finish with excellent wait staff.

Literally steps away from the U.S. Capitol, Butterworth's transports you far from the Nation's Capital to Paris. With an antler chandelier, old picture frames on the walls, and hanging plants on shelves, the decor is impressively French.

My friend and I sat at the bar for drinks only, but their foo

The food is mediocre at best, the prices do not reflect the mediocre food that’s for sure. The service was fast and friendly. They will nickel and dime you for everything while also charging top prices for the main meals. The location and atmosphere is good, often very crowded and loud but cheerful

This restaurant is amazing! The atmosphere is perfect, the people are super nice and pleasant,  and the food is out of this world delicious! We got excellent service from Luis...ordered the fettuccine Alfredo and tortellini with meat. Also, fried calamari as an appetizer and tried the pomegranate ma

Service was great; they let us customize the pasta order. Food was good! FYI, antipasto for two comes with pickled veggies (and lots of carrots) on top of the meat and cheese. Meat and cheese was really great, but if you don't like pickled or olives, then be cautioned.

I found Trattoria Alberto when I was on the Hill for meetings wanted to try their tortellini as it's my favorite pasta. Trattoria didn't disappoint and their tortellini was fantastic. The sauce was very tasty and went with the tortellini great. The creme brulee was a nice way to finish off lunch!

My wife and I love Italian food and wanted to try something new and this restaurant did not disappoint. We showed up on a Saturday night and was seated quickly. Our waiter Manuel was very attentive and food came out fast. The food and drinks were very good.  Definitely a great place for a date night

I went to Bistro Du Jour with my friend for dinner on Thanksgiving evening. This was one of the very few restaurants in DC that was open and offering g the full menu beside the set Thanksgiving menu. We were so glad we chose this place - we were greeted by the front door staff with so much pleasantr
Escargots were very tender but a little too salty. Set lunch of skirt steak is very value for money and tastes. Just a little overdone. Best to get medium rare! Excellent service!

My wife and I walked around the down town when sudden rain was about to start. So, we popped in the Bistro Du Jour to hide from the rain and have some snack. A guy who served us was very friendly, but, after bringing my burger, he suddenly disappeared. My wife kept patiently waiting for the soup. Af

I had an incredible vegetarian dinner at Bistro du Jour!  The appetizer salad with little gem lettuce, grapefruit, radishes and avocado was dressed with a perfectly balanced lemony dressing.  The braised leeks with lentils were to die for - simply fabulous!  I finished my meal with the mango and pas

The service was so warm, so welcoming and so above and beyond that I'm writing this review before even paying the bill. All the cuisine was delicious and quickly delivered by a smiling member of the kitchen staff. The best part of the experience was Michael and Aisha's dedicated and professional ser

I see why this spot has a Michelin Star!

Truly a great and intimate experience. With an attentive staff of four-ish, they were able to cultivate an experience where we can not only eat, but learn about the fish and food that we are eating - why they are prepared the way that they are and why they t

From the moment we stepped into the intimate omakase at Barracks Row, we knew we were in for something extraordinary — but Chef Ricky, Aaron and Gabrielle delivered an experience far beyond expectations.

Every course felt like a story — perfectly paced, beautifully presented, and bursting with crea

We chose Omakase @Barracks Row for our wedding anniversary, and it 100% worths it to every penny. The experience was astounding and memorable: each bite was super fresh and flavorful, we learned a lot more about the Edomae sushi style thanks to Gabriel; huge shout out to chef Ricky for creating such

My boyfriend and I came here for our anniversary last night and were blown away with the different tastes and the amazing experience. We both agreed that this was the best food we have ever had and one of the best experiences. The way that the different courses and beverages were described was amazi

The best omakase in DC. Ask any question here and you will get a full, riveting culinary history. The chef here is particularly intentional about sourcing - they source highly sustainable and seasonal fish/seafood, women-owned sake brands, and rare Japanese specialties. Masterful temperature control

My friend and I went to the Lobby Bar last night. There's parking out front and nearby, but the system wasn't working properly for most of the guests. The host was super friendly and kept an eye on our cars. I made a last-minute reservation, but when my friend arrived, he was able to grab a seat at

Saw Lobby Bar on IG and had to try. It didn’t disappoint! They were accommodating with my toddlers stroller. Extremely welcoming just walking inside. British was our server. She was so sweet and gave great recommendations. Chef brought us out deviled eggs and we ordered the girl dinner as well which

Had a great experience tonight at Lobby Bar! Like others, we had seen the bar on social media and decided to check it out!
The host and the manager were so kind, so welcoming and so accommodating that it gave off a hometown bar vibe!! The drinks and the food were a hit, as well! I got the fried chic
The olive dip was incredible and loved the espresso martinis, especially the pumpkin one! The atmosphere & vibe is very cozy. Best for parties of 2 but they have some larger tables.

Stopped by Lobby Bar to try their popular Girl Dinner for $80! It was such a good spread - it came out hot and you can tell they made it to order. Our waiter was also very attentive and made sure we enjoyed our meal!

Hoping to stop by again soon!

Very good food! One of the best Fettuccini Alfredo's I've had, very filling as well. The appetizer was fantastic. Quite expensive, but very tasty, and this is also D.C. so what can you do? Service was a bit slow in my opinion, it certainly was not busy while we were there, but we came not too long a
The best pasta restaurant in the DC area. The restaurant is relatively small and very intimate. Ita great for small groups. The food is as amazing as you can get.

Very small restaurant 10 min walking from the Capitol Hill.
Food was very good, waiter was very nice but I would not recommend this place. It took us 40 min for a bruschetta and 1:10h for the main dishes. This is not acceptable. If they were short on staff, which I don't think was the case, they sho

I went here a while ago. The food is authentic Italian. However the service could be better. Seems like it's a family run business. There was just one person in charge of several tables so there was a long wait whenever we needed something. But overall it was a good experience.

Amazing food and great service. The calamari were the best we’ve tried in the US, the eggplant parmigiana sandwich was to die for and the last surprise came with the desert which as a classing cannoli but with a cinnamon twist in the crust. They even accommodated my little sister who only eats plain

The cafe's location, next to Capitol and the Library of Congress, makes it unique. Prices and quality of food are good. My wife and I stepped in the cafe when it was full of people and there was a long line in front of us. I can say that professionalism, timing, and positive attitude that the person

Stopped by for a coffee break with a colleague.  Good espresso and pastries … congressional offices are near by.  It was quiet when we were there - but looks like this place can get busy.  Highly recommend.

From the moment I stepped through the door, the warm, inviting aroma of freshly brewed coffee and artisanal pastries enveloped me like a cozy hug. The decor is a perfect blend of rustic charm and modern minimalism, with exposed brick walls adorned with local artwork and plush seating that begs you t

Perfect place for brunch while out and about in Capitol Hill. Our omelets were unbelievably delicious. We picked the build your own omelet with four ingredients. This came with a lightly seasoned ( not overly salty) fair amount of red potatoes. We were able to  get a couple of fried eggs for our pup

If you have been to a cafe in Europe, you will appreciate the similarities between this place and cafes over seas. It definitely makes you feel like your in a cafe in France.

Service was great and the food and drinks came out in a good time. It is a bit tight in there for seating, so be on guard fo

My food and drinks were delicious. The bottomless brunch was a good price and they give you full portions. I am shocked. Our waitress Joyanna was so patient attentive and made sure we had everything we needed. I will definitely at this to my favorite brunch spot list.

We've been seeing the posts about the weekend brunch and finally made our way after 8am service 2 weeks ago to check it out. We didn't have a reservation, and the 4 of us arrived separately, probably 10 mins apart,  but as no one was there at 10 am Sunday morning, the first one to arrive was seated

I gave this spot a look see and it was okay. The calamari was not not plentiful, it was overcooked, and the sauce i didn't care for. The whiskey sour was pretty good though! Bartender did a great job as well
Tiffany was really great start to finish. She recommended some drinks. I got the pineapple paradise and also the shrimp and grits. Super amazing for super amazing service. also got the shrimp pizza

Server gave me my receipt for me and my guest which was inaccurate but it wasn't a big deal. All for him to charge my card the table beside me bill which was over 30 dollars more because they got bottomless. Which he tried to convince me I was wrong that even though my receipt was "wrong" he swiped

A friend told me to stop here when I moved to DC. I’m sad I didn’t make the trip sooner. The “G” Man is one of the best sandwiches I’ve ever had. I will absolutely be making a better effort to get over here frequently.

I just ordered a turkey and cheese sub on a hard roll! I am so disappointed of the sub I received! If you ever had a sub from Mangialardo's you know they are known for serving generous portions of meat on their subs! This was unlike any sub I had from there before! The meat was such a small amount y
This was by far the best sandwich Ive had in DC to date!  Everything was so fresh and the bread was perfect. The potato salad was good and the brownie was an excellent end. We will be back!

The best sandwich in DC, hands down. Absolutely consistent from one visit to the next, even years apart. Fast and always pleasant service. Amazing value. On a hard roll, the sandwich keeps quite well until dinner — we’ve taken them for an evening picnic before a show at Wolf Trap. I assume the hard

Today was one of my worse experiences here. I found the longest piece of hair in between my cheese. It absolutely turned my stomach. I usually love this place but I know sometimes the employees lack in their hygiene but THIS WAS COMPLETELY UNACCEPTABLE!!!  I’m still gagging from the thought of it!!

We were surprised by how big the portions were considering it was cheaper than some other chains we frequent. We ate in-house so I don’t know about their to-go portion sizes. Very tasty and looked up to see here are other locations more convenient for us when we need our next fix.
Top notch! I love Mezeh. It’s always delicious and fresh. The service at this location is fantastic. José was very professional, helpful and friendly with a catering order. Cannot recommend enough.

Loved Mezeh!!! Customizing my dish was fun. The lamb was perfectly cooked and the variety of sides was goood too. Friendly staff added to the experience. Portions could be bigger, but overall, a satisfying meal. Recommended for those who enjoy customizable plates.

They literally missed an entire entree (classic shawarma) and side of hummus on my order. It says it on the receipt but not in the bag. Then I had to pay 2 different delivery people a tip because of their screw up.
Wow! First time trying Mezeh and loved it! Friendly service, packed build my own bowl (hello lunch and dinner), and super tasty juices. Will be a frequent customer!

info.name: Jab We Met Indian Kitchen
info.address: 515 8th St SE First Floor, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text: Had a double date here last night and the food was delicious! Very flavorful with great consideration for spice level, overall taste and attention to detail. It felt like we were in a family owned spot, everyone was very nice and shared the responsibility for our table without making us feel shuffle

We came across this place on Google and the name seemed so attractive that we ended up visiting that restaurant for our next meal that day.
We reserved a table but there was no wait time. The restaurant ha multiple tables for variety of groups.

In appetizers we tried their palak chat after reading

Perfect Combination Lunch for Astounding $15!!!

Have you ever had a meal so delicious, so perfect that you were forced to your laptop to write a review, knowing your thumbs would give out if you tried to craft it on your phone? This happened to me today when I went for an Indian lunch at Jab We Met

Super good food and great service!
We ordered Saag and Chicken curry and it was absolutely delicious. The flavors are strong but well balanced. The garlic naan is buttery and garlicky. Highly recommend.

Went for lunch to try the new lunch menu and had the Tandoori Chicken Tikka special, which came with daal, rice, naan, and the vegetable of the day, which was saag. Both the quality and quantity of the food were exceptional; it was a great value for the price. I can’t recommend it enough! It is the

info.name: Art and Soul at YOTEL Washington DC
info.address: 415 New Jersey Ave NW, Washington, DC 20001

reviews.text: Went to this place for brunch & we had a great time! There was a live musician and that made the experience even better. We sat inside but the patio was super cute and spacious. The dining room was nice too! The drinks, food and service were really good! 😊

Great place for an outdoor meal with our pet. Large pet friendly dining area out front. The crew was so kind and catered to our Aussie Shepherd.They even have a Pup menu ! Fritz loved the 6oz sirloin. This was cooked to perfection as was the rest of our dinner. The Angus burger with cheddar and carm

Conveniently located near our hotel, Art & Soul was a pleasant surprise. We walked in with no expectations—just hungry and hoping for a good meal. From the moment we stepped inside, the hospitality stood out. We were seated immediately and offered water, which was especially thoughtful given the hea

Very expensive.  Dining area not open for dinner so has to join others on longer tables. Photos below of our order, which ended up costing approximately $300 Australian dollars. Definitely not worth that amount!! 2 share platters 2 meals and a medium priced wine!!

Literally stumbled on this gem lookig for a quick dinner  and it didn't disappoint. Food was really flavorful and delicious. Service was also good.  Good Happy Hour options as well, e.g., the crab dip is amazing (we forgot to get a pic before finishing it). Recommend highly because of tasty and dive

During a recent lunch break, we stumbled upon ZomTum, a vibrant new Laos-Thai bistro near Eastern Market, and decided to give it a try. We're so glad we did! The experience was marked by reasonable prices, delicious food, and warm, friendly service.
We ordered two dishes to start our exploration of

Was in DC for the weekend and this gem popped up on yelp when I set the filters to organize my search for lunch by the highest rating. This is a five star spot!!! The service was so friendly and quick. The food was so fresh and full of flavor. I ordered the som tum with sticky rice and it was bursti

We were staying in the capital hill area on our way back from walking to the Capital and stumbled across Zomtum Thai restaurant. The service was slow going at first but the appetizers and main dishes made up for it all. We enjoyed egg rolls and LI ice teas… my main was the shrimp pad Thai. Everythin

Probably one of the best Thai restaurants I’ve had in years, and definitely my new favorite in DC. The food was amazing. I had the calamari for an appetizer and the Siamese Kaprow (chicken) for an entree. Both were cooked to perfection. This will definitely be my new go to spot in DC. The service wa
Steve made our experience at ZomTums one for the record. We had the mixed veggies/tofu with drunken noodles. Superb flavor and the vegetables are perfectly cooked, crisp -fresh-hot. Thanks guys!

info.name: Jimmy T's Place
info.address: 501 East Capitol St SE, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text: I really don’t get the appeal. It’s like going to someone’s house and sitting at a super small table and getting cheap food that tastes pretty basic. I guess if you’re looking for a homey vibe and are a regular, maybe?? But no reservations, cash only, no menus (just up on the whiteboard, hard to rea

I went with my husband and we absolutely loved this place! It has a special vibe, you can tell it’s run by the owners with care and heart. Classic American breakfasts at super affordable prices.
The drip coffee was delicious and, incredibly, not burnt (a rare find!).
We’d go back without hesitation.

CASH ONLY! This is a no frills breakfast place, simple menu with breakfast basics. $10 to $20 a person.
Jimmy T's is on the SE corner of 5th and East Capitol Street a quiet part of Capitol Hill. Only Street parking is available. Was greeted by the server when I came in and he helped me immediately,

What a little hidden gem! Cute spot that’s cash only. I love all the random decor. They have a solid menu, no frills, exactly how I like it. The staff are all very friendly and the chef even made sure we were happy with our breakfast. I had the French toast, sausage, and egg combo. It was exactly wh

Our meal came out hot!! How wonderful!
Food was satisfying.  Will return.
Pancake bacon and egg. Hot 3
Grilled cheese with tomato and onion tasty and hot 4
Fried Jalapeño cheddar grits. Bland
Would try the cheddar bacon grits next time
Prices are reasonable especially in these times. Cash only.
Food

My wife and I enjoyed our dinner at Chiko. We took part in the kitchen counter experience. It was soooo much food. Well worth the $. We had enough leftovers for lunch the next day. My favorites were the beef & bone marrow fried rice, the double fried chicken wings, and all the offerings in the 3rd c

I wanted to like CHIKO but the food was just too sweet for me, and there was too wide a gap between what I read on the menu and what I got.

For example, the sichuan cucumbers were a little earthy/musky which I didn’t dislike but wasn’t exactly what I expected. Tasted more like something from xinjia

I ordered the duck confit fried rice, orange chicken, and kimchi. The food was great, and not your run-of-the-mill Asian food. The fried rice was basically Peking duck with the pancakes replaced with fried rice. There was a very generous portion of duck.

The orange chicken was such an interesting t

Really great food and a great overall experience at Chiko. I definitely recommend checking out the kitchen counter experience - it's well worth it!

Chiko is a cozy space with a few tables up front and a counter that gives you a great view of the kitchen.

We stopped by for dinner and did the kitche

SOOOO good! The food is incredibly flavorful and the portions are very generous. Perfect for take out or a causal dine in experience with a glass of wine or their new cocktail menu. It’s small so don’t expect anything fancy but the food makes up for the casual experience on Barracks row. It’s been a

I normally avoid eating Mexican but here I loved nachos preparation. Too good it was and then some two more dishes. One was wrap kind of a thing n other was rice and black beans n avocado   But it was good. Wrap was ok but nachos were really GOOD my friends enjoyed their meal too

Updated review: still and always an amazing spot for good food and drinks! Brought family from out of town that have varying food preferences and allergies and they always have something for everyone!

Love this place so much!! They have an amazing margarita menu, and I got their seasonal pomegranat

Great service, atmosphere and delicious food. Got the Skinny Margarita Pitcher, pork belly taco, with the perfect amount of fat, large chips with guacamole which was perfectly seasoned The tortilla chips were hot  out of the fryer, and the quesadilla was just right with a side of salsa, sour cream a

The food was good. The Combo is a little pricey for just 2 small tacos and nachos. But the tacos had a lot of toppings on top. (Can be positive or negative depending on preferences) The atmosphere was great.

A quiet area. Even though we were sitting outside next to a busy road it was easy to talk a

What an incredible dining experience. I found this place while en route to another destination. I saw the patio, and the margaritas looked great, so I stopped. Everything was perfect from the hello, and welcome greeting all the way until I left. This fine establishment is managed very well. You can

I had a great time at this wine bar. The vibe was super relaxed, making it easy to unwind.

I wanted to try the charred Brussels sprouts, but they were out. Our waiter apologized and brought us Arancini instead, which I hadn't planned on ordering but ended up really enjoying. This was a super nice g

The cocktail selection is very good, and the atmosphere is very pleasant. I happened in on a night when the kitchen was having a problem, so I can't comment on most of the food. What was available was still quite good. The staff working were very accommodating and understanding and overall seem grea

I went to a special Galentine’s wine tasting event at the Eastern, and it was such a great time! The staff was so knowledgeable about the wines they served us. They were happy to answer any questions we had. We ordered the Beastern Board. It was exquisite.🍷

Yesterday, I had a pretty underwhelming experience at The Eastern. I understand the bar can get busy, but the service didn't feel very welcoming. When I sat down, I wasn't greeted right away. I was probably there for about 3 to 4 minutes before anyone acknowledged me. Eventually, I was handed a drin

The Eastern is a wine bar so let's start with the wine list. The list is varied, playful, interesting, and approachable for the novice and engaging to the very knowledgeable. Yeah, the wine part is lovely, one of the best wine bars in the city.

The food is delightful. The Eastern Burger is my curre

Damn good ramen!! Blink and you’ll miss it though.

Their space is small and hidden, it’s attached to what looked like a different restaurant but Toki is to the left up the stairs. Also note, they only have bar seating. But go for their food, service and vibe!!

The server/bartender were super cool

I want to start by saying the food was fantastic! The Bao Buns, Curry Ramen, and Dan Dan Noodles were all packed with flavor and I would happily order again. This being said, the service was shockingly snarky and rude. The host wasn’t friendly at all. It’s really a shame, because the food was so gre

The steam bun with fried chicken and the root beer chicken wings are both delicious. The fried chicken curry ramen and the numbing garlic ramen are both okay. The pork insides the numbing garlic ramen is delicious tho. The vibe is great. There are not many seats, and there are also no tables, so it’

We really enjoyed the vibe there. It does feel “underground “ theme even it’s at the second floor. It’s like bar seating style. Their Ramen noodles soup was very creative and the fired chicken was absolutely delicious and impressive. Love all the Japanese beer options and we will definitely back aga

I have been to toki underground twice now. I have to say that I am extremely disappointed in the food and service. I ordered dan dan noodles and my noodles were not cooked. I am not the kind of person to send back food, so I waited to write this review. The ramen was so bland too. I spent close to 2

This cafe was a cute spot with some decent food. Ordering at the bar and finding seating was a bit difficult. The food was well overpriced but seemed fine due to it being in DC. I enjoyed eating here but would not rush to go back.

Junction has become an absolute staple of the neighborhood. The food is always good, the drinks are continually solid, and you can’t beat the location. It’s one of the last great happy hour spots in the area. Whenever we’re walking around and we feel like stopping somewhere, our default is the junct

Came to Junction Bistro & Bar since I was in the neighborhood in search of a coffee shop/bakery of the sort with food because I was really hungry. The menu was pretty extensive for such a place, which was a relief.

They did not have pour coffee when I arrived, but I was able to get some mocha. It w
such a lovely lunch experience. light fare + neighborhood style atmosphere. a little expensive, but still delightful.

Junction used to be my absolute go to spot for a slightly elevated drink after work. They make great cocktails and had rotating nights like mule Monday, taco Tuesday, etc. Their happy hour was unbeatable with a wide selection of drinks for everyone, but now it’s been changed to a very run of the mil

Sexiest bar in dc. I don’t drink anymore but they have solid food and killer decor. Heard Renee is running it now, he’s a dope dude. Definitely check it out, they have pool, food, cocktails, beer and party. Recommend 10/10.

I am a regular at this establishment. However, on Friday night, I experienced the worst customer service ever from the bartender, Shay! She was rude and simply unpleasant. My guest and I sat at the bar, and she constantly walked by us without speaking or taking our order. The other bartender, Christ

I’ve rarely had a burger with no taste/flavor but that’s what I had tonight and it was over cooked. Incredibly disappointed as its sister restaurant Hawk n Dove has great burgers. Also, I think there were like 12 fries on my plate. Really????  Also, the new bartender didn’t know the answers to any q

Awesome ambiance and a big industry hang out. Great happy hour and lots of small plates including flat breads, tandoori chicken kebab, chicken & pork sliders, chili, Mac & cheese, chicken wings, anti pasta, chicken & pork sliders, mezza plates and decent desserts too. Mike always takes care of my bu
Visiting DC and had the best drink of our entire visit here! I'm not a Gin fan but the bartender switched it up and it was incredible. She definitely knows what she's doing!!

Absolutely great food! Meat we got was stunning, soft and delicious, all the other menu positions were great as well, however it took an hour for the desert we placed at the very beginning and even though my husband ordered espresso, we never got it(even though it appeared in the receipt at the end)

A very comfortable and unique small restaurant situated in a refitted townhome, making for a great atmosphere! The food was excellent and had a healthy variety of choices for the size of the restaurant, including the drink and dessert menu, though we only saw it for lunch. There was a good and inter
We come to this place during events like Oktoberfest fest and around Christmas. The food is amazing each time! We recently got an Oktoberfest fest combo that was totally worth the money!

While we were on a walk with our dogs. We decided to check to see if this place was dog friendly, and it was. The outdoor patio was perfect! The host gave us a section in the back that allowed us to have more space with our 3 dogs. They have really nice fire heaters and tons of lighting creating a n

Like taking a few hour holiday to Europe.  Authentic German food and drink (great fresh German beer on tap).

We went at 3pm for a late lunch and it was perfect.  Dog friendly outside so our pointer could join too.

The sauerbraten was on point, with savory gravy and delicious semolina dumpling.  Th

info.name: Akeno Sushi Bar and Thai at Capitol Hill

reviews.text: We just moved back to the US after living in Asia for 25 years and this place checks the box for good Japanese which is tasty and not overpriced. We loved their innovation serving trays. This is now our local, go to place when we want simple tastes of Japan.

Great all around. We went for the brunch, unfortunately someone in our party didn't want to pay for bottomless so the rest of us missed out. We ended up ordering a mix of sushi and entrees, everything was top notch. Not a massive crowd, we had reservations bit probably didn't need them. The double h

I LOVE this place! I have been coming (often) for the past couple of years, and have celebrated birthdays and other special occasions here. The staff are superb and welcoming, the food is well prepared, and the drinks are delicious (love that they have mocktail versions of their cocktails too)! I me

The sushi was amazing. They have different options and flavors. Servers were polite and helped us pick from the menu - which is always a support I like and need :).  Restaurant is on the second floor and you’ll have to go through a short alley. Parking can be hard to find.

Very good sushi and great vibes. It’s a bit tough to find but walking up the stairs transports you to a sushi fairytale land. Lots of bright colors. Great sushi. Crab rangoons were so good.  Not your typically carry out rangoons with cream cheese and fake crab. These were made in house and had aweso

Do NOT order take out from this restaurant. I ordered drunken noodles in-person for take out, and the amount of food I received was shockingly sparse. Even with the scant amount of beef and noodles, the order was bulked mostly with bell peppers and onions. I sent the photo to the manager who respond

If you want Flavorful with any level of Spicy you need look no further then this restaurant. The meal and drinks were excellent. Service was fast, friendly and patient with us.
Footprint isn't very big and explaining directions to the bathroom is hilarious 🤣.
Overall, I'll be back

I looooove Sanphan. I dine in and do take out all the time. They are always so sweet and the food is so yummy. I recommend a chicken pad thai or a panang curry. This time they offered me a free drink and it was soooo delicious. 💗

I would definitely come back here. Delicious food, great drinks, and the best sticky rice Ive had in a while, my experience here was great. I decided to dine in, this restaurant seems big on take out but I was in the area and wanted to watch the Olympic games, they had it playing so this place was a

Ordered plenty of food and wanted to give it a 5/5 but the Steak Pad Thai was ranscent and we weren’t able to finish it.

Overall I would come back and just avoid that dish, otherwise awesome customer service and efficient delivery service!

The food was actually good, especially the chicken and broccoli noodles; both the starters we got, the dumplings and the spring rolls were homemade and solid.
I reccomend this place if you have in plan to take a walk for the capital!

Top tier customer service and delicious food!  I will certainly return to this spot to try the other food. The General Tso Chicken was well seasoned and excellent crispy outside and tender chicken inside. I loved how the servers treated a family with a child. They made the child feel welcomed and ap

Not one but TWO food items had hair cooked into them. I genuinely enjoyed my first order from this place, and I wasn’t going to leave a review for the crab Rangoon. But the second hair I found was the tipping point because it really feels careless and unsanitary. I’m pregnant and have to take food s

I eat here literally every day for lunch. The best Chinese cuisine ever ! The staff is very friendly and provide great service. My fav part is that the food is to your table in less than 10 minutes so I never have to worry about being late for work. You gotta try the shrimp spring rolls, they are to

They have quite a mix of cuisines here and that's not necessarily a good thing. The ambiance is dated, though relatively clean.

I generally wouldn't recommend sushi at a place where there isn't regular fish flowing out/being ordered as this is usually an indication of long-frozen/unfresh fish but t

Always an amazing place to visit, best salsa in DC and phenomenal service. Carlos and José, Christian are always the best servers and make you feel super welcome! The food is also 10/10, so much flavor that just blends perfectly. Vast menu and options for everyone, also very family friendly. I highl

I recently visited this restaurant and had a disappointing experience. The food didn't taste great, and to make matters worse, I saw mice running on the floor while I was checking out. Given the condition of the restaurant, I'm concerned about the potential for contamination. However, I did want to

I’m so sad to give this place a bad review because it was SO yummy and so cute, but they poisoned me with a known food allergy that I disclosed ahead of time… and I had a very serious reaction and it ruined my night out. They need to take food allergies more seriously and be more careful…if they do

A DC gem hidden in Capitol Hill.
Family owned, no fuss just outstanding food, kindest people, BEST spicy margaritas (they make them with actual fresh jalapeños). This place continues to be our absolute favorite. We have thoroughly enjoyed every dish we have tried here.
If you’re looking for fancy, k

La Plaza is a vibe. They pack the tables inside and there's a popping sidewalk patio with more tables. It's decorated with bright colors and the staff are friendly. It's a fun spot to get queso and frozen margaritas.

We popped in after Santa Rosa was too busy. The menu at La Plaza is large with tac

info.name: U.S. Capitol Cafe
info.address: First Street and East Capitol Street NE, Washington, DC 20002

reviews.text:
For being a museum cafe it's really good and has a good amount of options for lunch.
Good options for treats as well.
Best plan is to tour the Capitol around 10:30-11, eat lunch here, and then go through the tunnel to the library Congress around 1-1:30pm. That way you only need to go through the sec

It’s a cafeteria full of 8th grade tours! It was packed full, it felt amazingly clean. Had a wide variety of food, pizza, hot dogs, salad bar, shrimp; even Indian food. Wide choices of food, desserts and drinks.
Shrimp was $19. You take and clear your own plates. The utensils are found at a counter

Yo?! This food SUCKS! Mac and cheese? I could make a cheaper Kraft when I get home! Straight up cafeteria food. Don’t get the cupcakes. The red velvet tastes like paint. Pizza is cardboard with sauce. Potato salad has WAY too much mustard. Don’t go.

A cafeteria in every meaning of the word to accommodate the menu desires of all variety of visitors to the Capital. It may not be just legislative staf enjoying that pizza slice but also the high school class of students. And to prove there is something special about that place, search and enjoy the

Continental-style restaurant situated in the heart of the U.S. Capitol. With limited food options on the National Mall, it's a place worth stopping by.

Food is served akin to a school cafeteria. You pick up a plate, load it with whatever you want, and pay the cashier prior to heading over to the di

info.name: The Betsy
info.address: 514 8th St SE Back Alley, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text: We love the Betsy. It is an Eastern Market gem. Best cocktails in DC. Made with love. We tried the gin and tonic and a beautiful cocktail. I can’t remember the name. Oh so delicious. The chicken wings and waffle bites were delightful. Can’t wait to return.
I’ve been a few times and always wonder why I don’t come more! Cocktail selection is amazing and bartenders know what they are doing. Not a huge food selection but still super good.

What a fun and great discovery. Up the stairs in a back alley is this fun and authentic cocktailbar (and quite extensive bites menu as well. Their selection of gin & tonic is quite impressive. The bar tender Arslan was a gem and made sure everybody in the group what they were expecting. Lovely lovel

The drinks here are very nice and the setting is lovely. However, I had issues with the service - I wasn't big on the first cocktail I ordered so I asked which of the bourbon/whiskey cocktails were the most bourbon/whiskey-forward. The server took this opportunity to mansplain the difference between

I have mixed feelings. It’s got that blind tiger / speakeasy feel with a tightly packed room and dim lights. I felt like I’d officially entered my mob-wife era (complete with my well-timed faux fur coat and chipping nails)
The cocktails were great. And it was a nice stop over with friends on a night

The food here was delicious! We got crab ragoons, Panang Curry, Basil Chicken, and Peanut Sauce Chicken.  Everything tasted great and despite it being very busy the service was good and we got our food very quick!

This beloved Thai restaurant on Capitol Hill serves up tasty dishes with quick, friendly service-perfect for a speedy lunch break. Don't miss the spicy papaya salad and the flavorful Pad Thai noodles!"

Great Thai food, had one of my fav is the papaya salad, so far one of the best within the DMV.  Perfect spice!!!! The basil rice was a little spicy for me (even tho I asked for level 3) if you don’t like it hot ask for level -0 - to be honest everything we order was good.  Will definitely visit them

The perfect ending to a wonderful day.  My friend and I shared Red Curry Delight with Chicken and Spicy Eggplant with Tofu (each $13.95).  Hot tea was $4  and Thai Iced Tea $5.  Delicious food at very reasonable prices.  Attentive service.  Located a block away from the Capitol South Metro, so the p
We ordered the tofo drunken noodles and chicken panang curry. The service was quite good, and we had our food quickly. It was awesome! Perfect heat level.

We had time between scheduled tours in DC and decided to grab lunch nearby. Very happy to have found this place. We would definitely return. My wife got the ham and pineapple, which was probably the best I’ve ever tasted. I got the Butcher Block and liked it a lot. There seemed to be plenty of seati

This has become my go-to, laid-back pizza joint, and I'm here at least once a week to hang out with friends on the hill. While the floors and furniture have seen better days, I really enjoy the music murals on the walls. The pizza is consistently good, and I'm a big fan of the non-alcoholic soda jer
This was some of the best pizza I have ever had! Super convenient location near the capital and library of congress. Enjoyed this a lot! Would 100% go again. Fast service as well!

Great option for families with kids! Close to the Capitol. Seating is upstairs so it looks vacant at first, but it's a hive of seating and people upstairs. After a Capitol tour with our state rep's office, the kids and I took a short Lyft ride to this pizza-by-the-slice restaurant. So. Many. Options

This pizza was fantastic! The staff was friendly, but most importantly, the pizza was one of the best I’ve ever had. We were very impressed and wish we had a We The Pizza near where we live. It’s a must try in DC!

info.name: Call Your Mother Deli – Barracks Row / Capitol Hill D.C.

reviews.text:
One of the best bagel spots in DC! We had a great experience, and luckily we found a table that fit all of us even though we were a big group. I loved the variety of options on the menu and really appreciated the ability to customize our own bagels.

Here are my ratings:
•	Big Turkey 8/10
•	The Sun

Call Your Mother is hands down one of the best bagel spots in DC!

From the moment you walk up to the colorful storefront, the energy is warm and welcoming. The bagels are next level — perfectly chewy with a creative range of flavors. I got the Royal Palm bagel and it blew me away. The Thunderbird s

I can imagine that this place gets packed with long lines on the weekend, especially considering the location. I went on a Monday, late morning which worked well for me. Ordered a bagel with tons of veggies and it was incredibly good. This is the kind of place where you continue to come back and wor
Order 2 jetski and 1 thunderbird . All taste nice , portion of the filling quite small tho for the jetski
Highly recommend stopping here for coffee and a bagel. Worth the (very long) line and wait. Service was joyful and the atmosphere and decor was fun and playful!

Almost feel guilty for writing this.

The staff is so nice and friendly . Was really exceptional service . I even saw the owner talking to a fellow that randomly came in and tried to sell beer to add to the stores beer tap. He was so nice in the encounter.

At the end of the day the sushi and sashim

Sushi Hachi is the best sushi restaurant I have ever been to; it was so good that my boyfriend and I went back two nights in a row. Their cocktails are great, and my personal favourite was the 8th street specialty sushi. The atmosphere and mood is calm and pleasant, and the staff and service is top
Good spot! Service was good. Sushi was yummy. Would like to see more variety in their menu. I’d go back!
This was the perfect way to end my day! Go for the sushi special (running until August) fantastic service and an exceptional dining experience. Looking forward to my next visit !

Sushi Hachi has a nice ambiance, but the experience was a bit underwhelming. The sushi was decent—fresh, but not extraordinary. While the food was enjoyable, it didn’t quite live up to the hype.

The service, unfortunately, left something to be desired. It felt a bit slow and inattentive, which detr

Absolutely incredible dining experience! The flavors were out of this world, and every dish we ordered was unique and exceptionally delicious. Each bite was a flavor explosion that left us wanting more. The creativity and quality of the food were top-notch, and the service was fantastic. We'll defin

Let me say that I absolutely love Indian food, North Indian especially.

Well, well, well where do I start. This review is basically based on atmosphere as I did not eat anything in this restaurant.

When I walked in a strong odor hit me and immediately I noticed the carpet was old, dingy and maybe

Overall I was not satisfied with my experience and will not return. The pictures of the full table show everything that was ordered. All together $80 for two. Butter chicken, extra rice, samosa, 2 naan and the chicken dish. The breads were $5+ each and the rice came out to like $10. None of the menu

I ordered a dish that is vegetarian at every other restaurant I’ve ever ordered from, off of the veggie section of their menu, and and confirmed it didn’t list meat as an ingredient.

Food arrived and contained Chicken.

Delivery was handled by the restaurant directly, so I can’t even blame a third

My husband and I want to like this place because we love Indian food, it's near our home, and it has been around for a long time. However, it is an awkward experience every time we go.

The decor is confusing (white tablecloths and stemmed glasses paired with outdated china, old chairs too low for t

Their poke bowl was so good!! I had the salmon and it was incredibly fresh. Staff was friendly and even chatted with another customer next to us. Their sushi also looked amazing. Couple behind us didn’t finish the boat they ordered and I almost asked if they could bring the rest over to me and my fr

Solid spot! You order and then sit… there’s limited seating - little hole in the wall, but yummy! The sweet potato tempura was my fav! Wish they had a full bar… they were the only sushi place open late in that area on a Friday night. Would def go back! Also, their bathroom has a bidet!

This small, neighborhood sushi spot offers a pleasant, if somewhat cozy, dining experience.  The sushi is generally good, satisfying that craving for classic rolls, and they also offer a few more creative options that are worth exploring.  The intimate size of the restaurant contributes to a more ex

A great deal for the money - cozy, family run. We enjoyed our rolls; my husband fell in love with the vegetarian miso ramen but the hands down deal was the bento box with tempura, CA roll, seaweed salad and even a little kimchi. We left full and very happy!

Excellent sushi 🍣😋👌. I wish I found this spot when I first got into Washington DC. We had lunch specials that were impressive in size, quality, taste, and the price was relatively inexpensive for what you got. It's a small spot seating only available for a handful of people (we sat at the bar due to

This is an old school diner. Inside a bit cramped but not complaining and they have outside seating. Service is very quick, they bring entire order at once. We had grilled cheese, fries, and cheeseburger. First was fries, then, GC, and then burger. All were good but burger could have used a bit of s

Great, non-fancy diner, and lovely cat.

In the midst of lots of more swanky places in the heart of the political centre of DC, this diner is a breath of fresh air.

Oh, and they have a lovely cat too!

Reminds me of home a bit too ☺️

I went to D.C. for my graduation and My husband and I decided to stop at a diner for Mother's Day. As soon as we walked through the door, we were greeted. The service was just amazing from the second we walked in to the second we walked out the door. The food was amazing. If you are ever in the area

We recently visited Pete's Diner in Washington, DC, and unfortunately, our experience left much to be desired. Despite its prime location near the Capitol Building and the charm of being a quaint little diner, the food and service fell well below expectations.

To start, the food was disappointing.

We stopped by Pete’s for a late breakfast before heading to the Library of Congress, and overall, it was a solid choice, though not without its quirks.

The eggs, pancakes, and sausage hit the spot, but the waffle had a little too much time to contemplate its existence on the griddle.

The decor is

¡aDios míooooo!
I absolutely loved it here.

Gabby & María were incredibly kind to me and my lady friend, even though she was acting a little rarita. Lol.

Since it was my first time visiting, María took her time explaining all the dishes—con paciencia y corazón. Everything felt so warm and homely,

A really special spot by Capitol Hill, run by very sweet and good hearted ladies. Try to find the entry, the door is tucked away on the right hand side and a little hard to find. Once you enter in, it's a cozy little spot. Delicious food and large portions, served by generous hands and hearts. Pleas

Honestly………..Best Soft Taco I Have Ever Tasted It!!! If you love tacos or burritos, you should definitely check out this place. Everything here is made fresh. The customer service here is phenomenal. The staffs are very friendly and they give very good recommendations. It might get little bit crowde

I’ve been to Burrito Bros several times after becoming aware of it last year. For a transplanted native Angeleno from SoCal, this is a wonderful spot. Unfortunately, today my experience was disappointing. After paying $10 for a burrito with all refried beans & no rice, got back to my office to find
Best breakfast burritos and pancakes! It was my first time at Burrito Brothers and I was impressed by how quick and efficient the stuff was. Food was amazing!!!

I've been coming here since I was a kid and I've always loved the subs here. I'm 51 years old and the subs are still amazing 🤩🤩🤩!!! This shrimp 🦐 salad sub, on a soft roll hit the spot. Outstanding oatmeal cookies not shown but, delicious as well.
Sandwiches here never fail, smoked turkey was fire 🔥🔥 highly recommend
Awesome little deli right across from competition in Eastern Market. Got the #1 and it was gigantic with nice soft bread.
Great hidden gem. Delicious sandwiches!
There is NOOOOO crab in the crab soup... I paid $11.00 for a seasoned cup of water or what seems like Cambells vegetable soup with Old Bay seasoning in it. 🤦🏾‍♀️
A really good corner cafe. Cold brew is good. The strawberry banana smoothie is great!

The food here is fine. It’s good for what it is and I enjoy their sandwiches. I do not enjoy however that every time I go and ask for my blt with turkey they ask if I want a turkey club and when I explain to them that I want a blt with turkey they get annoyed with me. I understand that they might be
