Located in a beautiful neighborhood, this was a good spot to grab a bite to eat. We had paninis off the lunch menu and was very impressed. Good flavor, good portions, and with Boar's Head meats and cheeses! Staff was nice and there was a relaxing atmosphere. Breakfast menu looks good too.

Stayed at an Airbnb nearby so we went here three days in a row for breakfast before heading out for the days adventures. Small but has some seating for dine in. Local cops, remote workers, families and middle school students stop by for quick snack, breakfast, lunch or to work. Had so many juice opt

A fun little place for breakfast and lunch. Service was quick and the food delicious. We were greeted with a smile and it seemed like they offered a little something for everyone. Everything we had was great. The neighborhood where they are located is very walkable and friendly and during October th

Really beautiful environment. The food is overall good. Would recommend coming here with another individual if you want to try out different food. They have AYCE and the price is reasonable. May get busy at times, but we were seated right away. Definitely would recommend the purple gold yolk bun!

Came for the bottomless drinks, left full as hell! I’ll start by saying this place is super small on the inside so large groups aren’t ideal. I have three stars because upon arriving, 3 different workers came up to us to ask if we were dining in and how many we had. We had 6 people and once they hea

This all-you-can-eat Chinese spot did not disappoint. The food was hot, fresh, and full of flavor—everything from the dumplings to the lo mein hit the spot. The bottomless lemon drops? Dangerous in the best way—sweet, smooth, and just strong enough to keep the good vibes flowing.

The ambience and a

Food comes out so fast !! But believe that takes away from quality of fried food.  The springs rolls &eggplant were very greasy every bite dripping with oil. The seafood fried rich was amazing would recommend!!

Terrible dining experience. The beef was not fresh at all and had a strange, unpleasant taste. The overall cleanliness of the restaurant is questionable. When I raised my concern to the server, the only response I got was a cold “noted,” with no attemp

What a wonderful little gem of a place!  We were staying in the area on vacation and trying out all the different restaurants and made it here for one of our lunches.  When you walk in it’s so unassuming, low key, wonderful scents, and friendly.  We initially didn’t have any expectations of the food

Bombay street food is a gem. The naan is perfectly soft and the veg Kolhapuri is rich, flavorful, and has the right amount of spice. The customer service is top notch, friendly, attentive, and very accommodating. Highly recommended for a comforting and delicious Indian meal.

Excellent food and amazing service! HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

This place was highly recommended by my host who lives nearby. I had the chicken saag, with garlic naan, and a mango lassi. The chicken was so soft and juicy, the naan was crispy and tasty, and the mango lassi was sweet and creamy. Everything ex

5🌟
I am proud to get this this review
The taste was so authentic and genuine, literally the Pillsbury of Nan....OMG 😲
Meat fall off the fork, What can I Say OMG

And you can actually here foreigners in the back grounds speaking loudly.
Bombay Street Food #2
Eastern Market DC

I love this place -- I was getting dinner in between activities on a Friday night, and it was perfect. The saag paneer rules, and came out really fast. The portions are SO BIG! I'll have breakfast for tomorrow. Also, this isn't the restaurant's doing, but I had a lovely convo with other patrons. It
Love this place and we'll definitely be back for more steak! We ordered two of the butter steak combos and it was so worth it. Make a reservation if you ever can.

Steak Frites DC is baaaaaaackkk! 👏🏿👏🏿👏🏿 The whole concept is amazing and the cut of steak in their  delicious Cafe de Paris butter is indeed top tier! Please try the Chai Latte Martini. I love all of their drinks, but that one right there has a special place in my heart. Lol! Everything is delicious

Stable DC is a standout spot with seriously impressive food. Every dish is full of bold, comforting flavors, and you can tell there’s real skill behind the cooking. The textures, seasoning, and presentation all hit the mark. The vibe is warm and relaxed, and the staff was friendly and on point throu

Came here with my friend on a Thursday night. I definitely recommend getting reservations - especially if you want the chalet experience! Having a small private space was nice. We got the spatzl and the cheese fondue to share. Everything was so delicious!! Only off part was the amount of times wait

We came here for a friend's 50th, as she lived in Geneva for 10 years during her childhood, so she was thrilled to see a Swiss restaurant in our area. We were a party of 11, and we were seated at a long table close to the window at the front of the house.

Five of us reserved the Raclette Experience

I have dined at Taco City many times and always have a great experience. Food is amazing and ready fast enough to eat on a quick lunch break. Whether it’s take out or dine in it’s amazing but dine in will always be my favorite. The service is top tier it’s a family owned restaurant and you can tell

Let me just say that this place became one of my bf and I favorite go to place from the very first time we visited back in august! The food is just AMAZING! The place is beautiful and the staff is just beyond admirable!! My bf and I even got a chance to talk to the owner and he was just as amazing,

I happened to be in the area and looking for somewhere to grab a quick bite to eat before catching a show at the Capital Turnaround, and I am SO glad I found Taco City 🌮!!

Yum yum yummmmm… Everything was so incredibly delicious from the cocktails to the quesadillas and tacos!! They have a huge rang

Me and my mom went in to try their tacos for the first time. We see that it is only one worker but seems that she barely wanted to greet us. However, she had seated another party who came in briefly before us. I attempted to catch her attention and she constantly told me to hold on, which didn’t bot

Stopped in for lunch and got the 3 tacos 🌮 for $15. I had the mushroom, chicken, and braised beef tacos. My favorite was the braised beef! The strawberry limeade and salsa w/chips were solid as well. Next time, I'll try the queso.

info.name: Capitol Square Bar & Grill
info.address: 1500 East Capitol St NE, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text:
We made a reservation for 12:30 on a Sunday and the table was ready with menu opens as soon as we arrived.

We ate and had paid our checks by 1:40, just illustrating the quick and efficient service Freddie provided.

We had French toast, catfish, oxtail, wings, salad and other items.   Everything wa

Absolutely LOVE this place! Have driven by for years and finally stopped in for a Friday night date night during happy hour. My husband and I love Washington, D.C. happy hour options and theirs were pretty good either way gluten free and vegetarian options.

Started our dining experience with a vodk

We had a wonderful experience at DC Capitol Square Bar & Grill.
The service was outstanding and Chef Fredy personally made sure everything was perfect, which truly elevated our visit. The food was exceptional, started with the creamiest, most flavorful cream crab that was chef’s kiss!

The lamb chop

This bar and grill is a very nice spot in Capital Hill, adding good food and good vibes alike. The food is something to write home to mom about. It serves African and Latin fusion flavors, full of spices balanced just right.  I had the Capital Square chicken and it was delicious. It turns into a lou

Great atmosphere, very instagramable. We tried the African Mama cocktail (frozen), for apps we had the Oxtail spring rolls and the cream of crab—both super tasty. For my entrée I ordered the lamb chops, absolutely delicious . Chef Fredy made the overall experience delightful.

I went on a date at Kaiju Ramen recently because I was craving ramen, and my date recommended it as the place to go, especially in the area. It was my first time having ramen in DC, and I found it really delicious and enjoyable. I didn’t finish it all because I got full, but it’s definitely a low ke

Got the veggie ramen and tasted like play dough so be prepared to try to ask for flavoring. I was unable to get servers attention for anything so just had to deal with it. Drinks were expensive and weren’t spectacular. Gratuity already included at 22%!!!! The bar below seemed cool, I think later the

Went in for a quick afternoon lunch. I went with the fries as an appetizer, tonkatsu ramen with a soft boiled egg, and to wash it down a milk-tea.

The fries were hot, fresh and crispy. The sauce for the fries was really good! The ramen as the main dish was good, the broth leaves a bit to be desired

I’ve been here a dozen times or so, and every time the food just hits so hard. The gyoza are incredible and all the ramen dishes are just amazing. I love the kaiju chicken, but their kaiju tonkotsu is pretty hard to beat.
Stephen helped us recently, and he was fantastic—great service, great suggesti

This was a great option for vegan ramen. I got the creamy ramen option and I substituted the corn out with bamboo shoots and no extra cost. Luis, the server was nice and friendly. I also got the Asahi non-alcoholic beer which was a great non-alcoholic option for me. I would come back.

The unlimited brunch and bottomless mimosas was really nice. Loved the mix your own mimosas by bringing a bottle to the table. The tapas were lovely. I wish the portions were a tad smaller so we could try more - especially the Benedicts. Overall a great experience and would recommend for groups.

This is a fabulous new Spanish restaurant by the owners of Bodega in Georgetown. Warm welcoming ambiance. Delicious food with a couple of American classics on the brunch menu. Try the French toast -- scrumptious! And to top it off enjoy a special mimosa and the flamenco music and dance during brunch

Quaint ambiance! Lots of tapas to choose from. I was in the mood for Paella. My service started with fresh bread & extra virgin olive oil for dipping. I had a salad featuring field greens, pears, walnuts, goat cheese in a honey vinaigrette. I settled with the Arroz a Banda Paella made featuring shri

Came for Saturday brunch for the first time and everything was great! My wife and I split a cheese board, fried peppers, and patatas bravas. They also served bread for the table. We also got a mimosa each which was tasty and strong (and affordable!) Altogether we had a delicious meal, great service,

The flavors!!! Order 5-6 plates for two people.
Great service, beautiful atmosphere, and the food was incredible. We had grilled octopus, potato, meatballs, sautéed shrimp, green beans and steamed muscles and we were very happy.

info.name: Ama
info.address: 885 New Jersey Ave SE, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text: The food was so good it may have convinced me to relocate to DC just so I can eat here every day. I had the Spaghetti al Pomodoro and the Buffalo Mozzarella Focaccia — both were absolutely incredible. Simple dishes, but done perfectly. My vanilla latte was smooth, creamy, and the perfect way to roun

Ama is all the new craze in DC on social media and the streets. I happened to be in the area and decided to check out the breakfast window. I'll say they are still working out some kinks because things took extremely long. However the pastries were decent and my chai wasn't bad either. I wouldn't sa

Intentional, delicious, and feel good food. Ate at Ama for the first time yesterday and truly blown away. Because I attended for a private dinner, I’m not sure the names of what I ate but everything was so flavorful. Standouts: White fish was so buttery and perfectly cooked. The pasta was so creamy,

I’m not going to go on and on about how this restaurant is a rare breed and there’s nothing quite like it. The truth is, there absolutely is, but not in D.C.

The refreshingly authentic take on elevated Italian food is welcomed to these parts. Why reinvent the wheel when you already have such a soli

We had an incredible experience at Ama! Our server, Filippo, made the evening unforgettable. He was very attentive, warm, and full of knowledge about the menu. You can truly feel the authenticity here; it’s like being transported straight to Italy.

The food was absolutely outstanding, being organic

My first time here, visiting after work. The restaurant is very nice and centrally located. It has various types of seating and it was that the staff were used to a fast pace setting. I sat at the bar and was immediately met by the bartender. The drinks were made to order and were not made lightly …

Excellent restaurant! Good food and great service! Our party was in a hurry and our server was very accommodating. We appreciated the use of the inkind app to pay and receive rewards on our purchase.
Circa does charge an additional service fee but they have a sign posted prominently out front!

Finally made it to this place and it didn't disappoint! The calamari was really good, I didn't care for the sauce though. The smash burger was really good as well as the fries. I also ordered a Hennessey side car for 19 and it was delicious
The fixed menu for Restaurant Week was very good. I had the shrimp bisque, salmon and bread pudding. The pasta was also good. The dessert was worth every bite!
I come here often and it’s always a pleasure. The food is wonderful and so is the service, whether for lunch or dinner. Great for date night, solo lunch, and even sitting at the bar for the game.

Great selection of oysters. Solid service, fantastic views of the river. They have outdoor seating to enjoy the river or a covered patio that's heated and insulated. Dinning room inside was also nice. The restaurant was decorated in simple nautical theme and good wine selection. We had small bites f

We had a lovely dinner at Salt Line. Maria provided excellent service and let us take our time. The oysters were very good, as was the pimento crab dip. My husband got the smash burger, which was tasty. I got the grilled corvina. The flavors were great but the green beans were slightly overcooked. I

Drinks, dinner, and dessert were great. Starting with crab dip and clam chowder were delicious. Trying the two different lobster rolls was a great idea as each one was delicious in its own right and the lobster was cooked perfectly. We upgraded our sides to the brussel sprouts and crispy potatoes wh

The food was nice but the best part were the oysters.  There isn’t parking close but could be dropped off easy.  The drinks weren’t overly expensive and the food came out very quickly.  I would say with appetizer, oysters, meals and drinks we were there less than a hour.  It would be a great place o

I came here on a date and we sat outside on the corner couch, which was a nice vibe—especially with the string lights overhead. I ordered the Brussels sprouts, and they were absolutely incredible. I can’t wait to get them again. I also had the shrimp Caesar salad, which came with four shrimp. For $2

I just had Andrea's Everything Croissant & Salmon Sandwich and it was phenomenal. I pretty much inhaled it. I don't even know what I'm going to do now. I've been fighting every urge to come here just for their delicious baked goods, but now that I've discovered this sandwich... I am ruined... in the

Love this Maman! The cafe is super cute. Really nice music. The staff are all friendly. I love the seasonal drinks! So good I came back twice in one week. Also the food is really delicious. I’ve had a few things already and everything has been solid. Made fresh, always warm, always so yummy! Stop by

I had a prosecco and the “papas breakfast bowl” with flank steak substituting the bacon. Everything was seasoned well, full of flavor, and presentation of the food was very pretty. Service was efficient and friendly. I would definitely come back. Thank you!

I had breakfast at Maman, and the Google reviews were absolutely right — everything was fresh, the roasted coffee was excellent, and the atmosphere was amazing. You’ve officially earned the title of my favorite breakfast spot in DC! Whenever I’m in town, I’ll definitely be coming back.
Highly recomm

I was expecting “stellar” in terms of experience based on the reviews and I was kind of surprised by how (unfortunately) mid everything I tried was - especially with how much they charge. The run down:

1. I ordered a breakfast bowl, asked to swap the bacon for the flank steak. I don’t eat pork and

Let me tell you, Chloe completely floored me. The food wasn’t just delicious… it was an experience. Every dish felt like it had its own story, with flavors that worked together so perfectly I kept going back for more. I sampled a bit of everything, and even when I was full, I found myself unable to

This was one of my all time favorite dining experiences!!! Tapas style so expect to order 2-3 dishes per person. Each dish was better than the last! The burger was the last thing we tried and weren’t sure what to expect based on the presentation… my goodness it was one of the most flavorful burgers

Chloe is a must-visit in DC! The food is fresh, creative, and absolutely delicious every dish is packed with global flavors. The service is truly exceptional friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable. Great atmosphere for a date night or dinner with friends. Highly recommend!

This was our first time to dine at Chloe. The little gem salad and Norwegian salmon were very good. The chocolate hazelnut cake was delicious!  However, the Berkshire pork entree was overcooked, both the meat and vegetables. We also tried the famous caramelized cauliflower, which was very good too.

A memorable meal for 3 that was well timed and packed full of freshness and flavor. We had a vegetarian in the group, and aside from one oyster dish, accommodated him with our choices- and don’t feel like we missed out at all. The tofu with mushrooms and broccolini (pictured) was to die for- (and I

Not my usual stomping grounds, but I made my way to Solace Outpost in Navy Yard for a networking Happy Hour. The atmosphere was lively, and the drink selection didn’t disappoint — plenty of craft beers and other creative libations to choose from. I didn’t get a chance to try the food myself, but eve

Great vibes. Food is always delicious, though I highly suggest you order from the bartender versus using their online ordering system as it only works about 50% of the time. They have a great selection of beer. There are plenty of tvs for catching a game. Indoor outdoor seating. It can get rather cr

Really enjoyed this place. Perfect place to end our father / son trip from the west coast on my birthday. The atmosphere, food, drinks and service were great. Had the chicken thighs, a brat and corn watermelon salad along with a couple of their really good beers. Our server, Ryan, was very knowledge

Solid establishment.

Beers are nothing crazy, but get the job done. Recommend the pilsner.

The food on the other hand was delicious. Crispy chicken thighs and pretzel were some of the best I’ve had anywhere. Ordered the Bavaria Dog as well. Can’t beat that combo of flavors.

Placed was packed for

Just had beer on a random overcast spring Tuesday evening. The pilsner and red were both good. Food looked and smelled amazing based on nearby patrons. View and patio seemed like they'd be nice on a clearer day. No stickers, though, or even coasters. Will have to hit a non-outpost spot to find those

Definitely enjoyable! Went here October 6, during the Chris Brown concert. At first it was iffy as we were sat but not attended to. I went up to the hostess stand to address it and possibly move. Two servers were up there talking and the hostess was on the phone handling a customer. Stood there pati

First of all, shout out to Evan. He was an amazing waiter and he was very considerate of our time (here for the CB concert). He also is receptive to feedback. Case and point, My friend and I ordered smoky getaways — the first round was a little “juicy” and when we told Evan that we wanted to taste t

Silver Social is a great place to grab food & drinks after watching a game at Nationals Park ! The vibe on the roof deck is great with picturesque views of the stadium. The lemon drops were great and a special game day price of 7$ you can’t beat. The grilled shrimp flatbread was prepared freshly and
Chloe was amazing and totally responsive. Appreciated her recommendations and absolutely enjoyed my brunch overlooking the Nationals stadium.

I sat at the bar, and Darryl was very kind, explaining that this establishment had a different menu from downstairs. I enjoyed the excellent meal and a drink. Daryl is truly the ambassador of Silver Diner. Darryl has excellent customer service.

Dinner was delicious. We tried the Gnocchi and the Tortellini with the brussel sprouts. Everything was very flavorful and cooked perfectly. We finished with a decadent chocolate cake. Drinks were equally as good. Look forward to a return visit to try other menu items.

Great restaurant week dinner last night. Lots of choices for a $40 meal-great value. Restaurant was packed which slowed seating and service. But sat outside on a lovely evening so the wait was OK. Staff were wonderful and understanding. Desserts were the weakest link but still good. Be adventurous w

My husband and I were walking around Navy Yards and are soooo beyond happy that we were able to land at Osteria Morini! This was one of THE best Italian Food restaurants we’ve been to (and I’ve been to Italy and lived in NYC) and this is just spectacular.  The wine pairing to the meals, to the wonde

Could not have been better. 3 appetizers were amazing. My dinner was outstanding. All 5 of us enjoyed everything we had. Service was as good as it gets. Juliette (?) from Columbia was the sweetest and proficient server. Loved everything!!

The only reason im giving 4 out 5 stars is because of the price of the meal for my wife and I. Other than that, the food was out of this world good!! Every bite was better than the first! It's a little hard to find parking, then it was 20 dollars an hour to park. We went on a weeknight around 6ish,

info.name: GATSBY
info.address: 1205 Half St SE Suite #105, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text: What a terrible restaurant! Arrived and the music was so loud, that I asked if they could lower it & the hostess firmly said NO without even giving it thought. Then, we sit down for BRUNCH, and i’m expecting good coffee. Turns out, they don’t have a coffee menu, no latte options and NO oat milk to c

Great brunch experience at Gatsby. The food, service, and ambiance were all amazing. I love the variety of options for the bottomless drinks, and the food was incredible. The biscuits, chicken and waffles, and shrimp and grits are a must try.

I’ve visited Gatsby twice this month and I want to shout out my servers, Demoyea & Emily. They were both great and very accommodating.

Before you go, please note that even with a reservation, your entire party must be in the building before you can be seated. Not parking, not on the way.. in the bu

•Food 10/10 •Atmosphere 10/10 •Mimosas 10/10 •Vibes 10/10

Went on a Saturday afternoon with no reservation and had our drinks & entrees within 20 minutes. The Dj kept the vibes going the entire time we were there. Our waiter Arnold was amazing and the views of the National Park across the street we

Great brunch spot with perfect vibes!! The service was amazing and I loved how they had different options for bottomless not only mimosas. Ut several other drinks which were all great. The server also didn’t stall in between refills and kept the drinks flowing 10/10! Food was tasty and the DJ was gr

Came here for Thanksgiving last night and loved it! The restaurant is warm and cozy (Christmas decor was so cute). The Thanksgiving menu was excellent and included a variety of food. The pumpkin soup, ravioli and turkey dinner was delicious. I didn’t think I’d be impressed with the dessert but I rea

I recently worked with Jackie in Navy Yard to plan a surprise 30th birthday for my wife, and everything turned out amazing.

From the start, Anya Gellerman, the event manager, made the whole process easy. She was patient, super responsive over phone and email, and helped with every question or reque

Jackie has become one of my go-to spots for a nice sit-down dinner or date night in the Navy Yard. I feel like this place doesn’t get as much attention as it deserves. I’ve been a few times and the food and service is consistently excellent.

They always have a few specials that change frequently, w

Had a nice dinner here.

Cesar Salad was simple but enjoyable.

The scallops were fabulous. Cooked very well. I usually don’t like cauliflower but they it well here.

The dessert was super. Hit the spot for sure.

Would happily come again and the service was excellent.

What a find! It was our anniversary and we decided to try Jackie Restaurant and we were so pleased we did! Fabulous, friendly staff, especially Tory who made our evening very special with his fun nature and attention to detail. We had the most delicious meal - the best meal we had in our 6 day stay

Took my family here to celebrate a birthday. We had cheese curds, nashville hot tenders w/fries, prime rib dip sandwich w/fries, and the carne asada tacos w/chips and salsa. All was delicious. The birthday girl also got a slice of cheesecake w/chocolate sauce.

Our waitress Jasmine was friendly, alw

Tom's Watch Bar is what a sports bar should be. There are tvs everywhere. Thet even have an outdoor area with tvs. The staff was super accommodating and friendly. Gray went above snd beyond for us. The food and drinks were good as well.

Everyone was very friendly, I want to start with that. As someone with restaurant experience the first thing that I noticed was the menu appeared to have never been wiped down or lately. The bar was dirty, the surface, the caddies, as well as the bar menus. I was always trained to wipe them all down

Tom’s Watch Bar is clearly a go-to spot for fans before and after games, and I recently visited for the first time with friends—grabbing drinks both pre- and post-game.

Before the game, a friend and I grabbed a table, which meant we were assigned a server. The place was packed, and service was unde

This the spot to go to in DC if you want to watch any game, they have multiple games playing at the same time and the bartender are great especially Dani she really took the time to cater us and  to show us what type of cocktail is the best and showed us the best item in the menu.

We held an after-party at Mission and the staff there, Charlie, in particular, were all extremely helpful. They were great about communicating via email and greeted us as we arrived & then escorted us to our reserved space. The food and drinks are great and the relaxed and fun atmosphere was just wh

I recently visited Mission Navy Yard and had an enjoyable experience. The restaurant has a lively, energetic vibe. Great for groups too, as the upstairs is huge. They also have a balcony seating

The staff were courteous, friendly, and helpful and attentive. Loved the Tex-Mex: tacos, enchiladas, and

Ashley and Mia were wonderful! I'm vegan and not too many places by the ballpark have good food that can meet my dietary restrictions.   Mission served it up!
Delicious food! Margaritas were absolutely refreshing with a bit of attitude! Don't worry,  they tailor the attitude to suit your needs 😉

Wo

I recently hosted a group of about 70 people at Mission Navy Yard, and everything went perfectly! The space was ideal; we were on the second floor, and our group was spread across three different areas, which worked wonderfully for the working session we had. The layout really helped keep the noise

Mission: A Lively DC Spot with a Nightlife Vibe
Mission Mexican restaurant in Washington DC offers a truly unique experience that's worth checking out, especially if you're looking for a fun and festive atmosphere. As the evening progresses, this place really comes alive, transforming into a vibrant

Love this place! Yes, I should have made reservations so I do recommend that but they were able to get us in and seated really quickly. The service was amazing, our server kicking butt every step of the way. I was just impressed! The food was amazing and the atmosphere was lovely.

The slogan on the

If I could leave more than 5 starts I would! Mia was our server and she was absolutely AMAZING! Her energy is contagios and you can tell she loves her job! The food was delicious and the Out of the office forever drink was soooo good! We were looking for a place close to the hotel before heading to

We came here for restraunt week. Service was slow to start, but quickly picked up. The Nashville chicken tenders were a great starter, super tender and moist. The Steak & Fries were phenomenal. Perfectly cooked and seasoned. The Chimichurri from the steak and Parmesan fries paired soo well together.

Really nice staff, we were greeted immediately by the host who was very nice and energetic, waitress was also very nice, the atmosphere was also nice to be in with decor and lightning, cool neon signs around.
* Food was really good, we had spinach dip which we all loved due to the cheese they use, i

I had the chicken sandwich and it was delicious as always. My wife had the short rib and it was phenomenal. I love visiting my local Makers Union because everyone treats you like family. I greet the staff and they greet me. Everything is so welcoming and I try to visit once a week. If you visit go s

info.name: Chicken + Whiskey
info.address: 70 N St SE Suite 119, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text: Visited the Valentine's pop-up bar and it definitely did not disappoint! Their cocktail selection really shines - every drink was expertly crafted and absolutely delicious. The food menu, though selective, hits all the right notes. The mac and cheese was pure comfort food perfection, and the empanad

The chicken had decent flavor but was really dry. Also, the rice had a similar problem, good seasoning but very dry. They were low on wedges, so I waited for some fresh ones. They were the star of the plate.

The staff were friendly and helpful. I was greeted right away, and my order was taken promp

I visited Chicken & Whiskey for the first time before heading to a DC Defenders football game, and I have to say, I was a bit disappointed.

First off, they charge a service fee, which was not clearly disclosed. I really dislike service fees — if you're going to charge them, just build it into your

Cluckin' Delicious
The chicken? Absolute smoky, tender perfection—like it had been kissed by fire and blessed by flavor gods. Pair it with the green sauce and you’re in poultry paradise.
Now, about that “served with basmati rice” claim... Let’s just say if the rice were any more modest, it’d be a ga

I come here once a week a cheeky meal so I only have good things to say. The chickens always scintillating, moist and flavorful, just how you want.

Love the arroz and frijoles. The arroz chaufa has bacon bits which is crazy. The picante sauce will knock the jocks off you ya.

The bar in the backs g

I went here before the Breezy Bowl concert, and it was awesome! The rooftop was a bit small, but we snagged a table before it got packed. Their frozen margaritas were amazing. I can't wait to go back.

I stopped in at this spot at the very start of Halloween night and it honestly set the tone for the entire evening. The energy was already great, the vibe was festive, and the drinks were on point — but the real star of the night was Diana behind the bar.

From the moment I sat down, she made the ex

Great location, they have two floors and the top one is a rooftop. This bar is great for happy hour or catching the game.
They are within a 5 minute walk from the Nationals Park.

They have a small simple menu of bites like loaded fries, boneless chicken wings, fried pickles and tater tots. They als

Unfortunately, my friend and I did not enjoy Takoda Navy Yard. The views were nice, but the rooftop bar service was seriously lacking. We were told the food would take a while and were advised not to order, which was disappointing since we came for both drinks and food. The drink I had was tasty, th

If you want a beautiful rooftop bar with classic drinks and an immaculate view, takoda is it! Our bartender Diana and the heaters kept us cozy. Wether it’s off season from baseball or an event going on takoda is always a good time.

info.name: Bammy's Modern Caribbean
info.address: 301 Water St SE Suite 115, Washington, DC 20003

reviews.text: I was very pleasantly surprised by the food here. I promise nothing missed! Especially if you like a little spice. Zee was such an accommodating hostess. She handled a large party with ease and patience. Bonus points because she got my baby to smile. Overall 10/10 experience ❤️

Zee was an amazing waitress!! If you go ask for ZEE!! Her energy was amazing and she made the experience 10 times better, she let us know about the Halloween event and their happy hour specials, we found this place on tik tok and they did not disappoint!! Also the manager, Dre was very attentive and

Tonight we came to this great restaurant for my birthday dinner and when I tell you the food was Fyah!! Oh my goodness. I wanted to try everything... but this just means we'll be back. Our hostess Z was so so amazing. This place is a 20 out of 10. To the chef... thank you!! Great birthday dinner.

I don't eat a lot of Caribbean food so everything is new to me. I tried the curry chicken patty and the beef patty. They were very good to me, but I don't have anything to compare them to because I've only had them at this restaurant. I like theirs and that's good enough for me. I also had the oxtai

Yeah man! Dropped in for a cold Red Stripe and some ‘yard food! The food is delicious! The service is great! And the atmosphere is purely Caribbean! 100% The jerk pork & Jerk Chicken sandwich's were deliciousness. The BAMMY - marvelous! For a YARDIE? Fantastic! CLEANED our plates! Rhatid!

OK, so basically this just taste like a Costco pizza and like I guess Americans really like that but I don’t for an $18 pizza…

Don’t waste your time go to Grazzie Nona that’s a real pizza place. I truly think that place has spoiled our pallet so unfortunately, this place gets two stars. Also just l
Great pizza and arancini balls, super fresh and crispy. The pizza is filling and not too heavy. Great spot for after a nats game and a reservation is a good idea when the weather is nice out.

Great family place for comfortable atmosphere and tasty pie.  We tried a number of pizzas including the mushroom and supreme.  Nothing went to waste.  Service was friendly.  The room is comfortable.  Not fancy.  Great for a casual date or family visit.  We will return.

Got a delicious Frozie (lemon juice, OJ, vodka slushie) and spouse got a Weissbier, after Opera in the Outfield (Porgy & Bess) at Nationals Park last night (8/23/25). Enjoyed the beautiful view, the quiet (every other venue was hopping, too noisy) and the decent prices. Would go again for a meal wit

Always a wonderful spot for an afternoon drink or dinner.  The patio and roof patio are both great views. Food is solid, reliable, and they have good drink specials. Have been here more times than I can count with my mother, siblings, partner, and friends.  It's a good fit for almost all.

Also grea

I’ve been here twice and experienced both bar seating and a tasting by the kitchen. Both experiences are worth it. The staff is very kind and can make thoughtful drink pairing suggestions on any dish. Really delicious, interesting modern takes on Palestinian and Middle Eastern cuisine. The spreads f

Albi was, unfortunately, the worst Michelin-starred restaurant I have ever tried. The food was overwhelmingly salty — so salty that it genuinely made me question what the kitchen was aiming for. The tasting menu was also poorly structured. After serving an extremely salty lamb dish, they followed it

wow wow wow. such a phenomenal experience. the ambiance was top notch along with the food and service. our favorite dishes were the manti dumplings and sfeeha. we also ordered the fattoush and labne tabat to break up the heaviness of our meaty plates. dessert was concord soft serve which i would per

Albi is one of our top 2 dining experiences ever. The restaurant is stunning and to see the calm kitchen working perfectly in harmony was a treat. The food was insane - we loved every bit. The flavors were incredible. We truly savored every dish. The chefs coursing is worth it, and the drinks they p

Albi was outstanding. We ordered a la carte and everything was absolutely delicious. Loved the open kitchen and the whole atmosphere. Service was top tier - servers and sommelier were helpful, knowledgeable, attentive and friendly. Food highlights: arayes, smoked tomato kibbeh naya, smoked urfa labn

My first time dined at this restaurant and I am very pleased with the experience. The night manager and the waiter were every very nice and informative. My food was excellent and the steak was perfectly cooked. I normally don't get dessert but since I enjoyed my main course, I had to get me a slice

Late late night stop to the Silver Diner. Service was on point as our server was very attentive all night. Food came out promptly and was hot and very good. Manager made his rounds too. The crabcake melt was actually very good so that too was a plus.

Had a great experience at Silver Social Club (I think it was the upstairs portion of the restaurant) for brunch when I was staying in the area. All of the food was super tasty. Portion sizes are a little smaller than what you get downstairs but didn’t bother me at all. Who knew putting pomegranate o

This location is by far the best option! The chef did something no other silver dinner has ever done. They took off the tail and butterfly my friend shrimp. It took the experience to the next level. Thank you for for those small details that makes a huge difference. I also forgot to mention that it

I've been here twice enjoyed both times that I was here. The food and atmosphere was nice it wasn't crowded both times. The food and drinks were pretty good, kind of on the expensive side to me but worth it in my opinion. I enjoyed there version of the chicken pot pie! Next time I'll have to try ter

We came here on a Saturday evening a little after the spirt Semifinals. I love their U st location it’s cool to see another location. There was plenty of room! We got a table. I ordered the shrimp and cod tacos. The shrimps tacos were amazing! The cod tacos were good but maybe needs a little extra s

Tried El Ray's navy yard location because I enjoy their U St location and it's sort of a let down. The menu is limited, if you're going for happy hour only the nachos are on their menu. I did enjoy the drinks. The service was quick and the people were nice. Overall if you're looking for food I'd go

Came here after the DC United soccer game! It was around 10:30pm and it was still open and I decided to give it a try and I’m glad I did.

The tacos were absolutely delicious. I tried the spicy margarita and if you like spice that’s a go to!

Omg the absolute best tacos I've ever had!! Super fun atmosphere.  Friendly staff.  Amazing food.  Menu is small but the food is delicious.  They even have this sweet potato taco that is OH EM GEE.  I love meat but darn that was so good!!

Came in here to have a cocktail after friends couldn’t decided where to go. Classic Wednesday drama!  Ended up getting the frozen seasonal cocktails and they didn’t disappoint. The service was even better. Please ask for Greg if you come in.

Our group went there prior to a Nationals game. We had a couple margaritas and some appetizers. The apps were very good and the Margaritas were awesome. Outstanding service. I will go definitely go there again for pre-gaming!

I had an incredible lunch at El Bebe during DC Restaurant Week! The special menu was superb. Every dish was fresh, flavorful, and perfectly portioned. The quesadillas were especially outstanding, and the variety made it easy to try a little bit of everything.

What really made the experience memorab

We visited ÉL BEBE this past Saturday for brunch, and it was an absolute treat! From the moment we sat down, the vibe was lively and welcoming. Gaby, our server, was fantastic, super attentive and friendly, making sure we had everything we needed.

My husband ordered the skillet, which was hearty an

I've ordered takeout from here several times. The food is always tasty, but the portions are on the small side particularly given the prices. Also, when ordering ahead during busy times, the wait can be quite long, so make sure to order well before you anticipate eating.

I'm a vegetarian and came for Restaurant Week. The Restaurant Week menu was not vegetarian, but the host was happy to check to see if they could do mushroom fajitas instead. He confirmed they could and seated me. The waitress came and took my order: nachos, mushroom fajitas, and churro fries. The na

No complaints about Any Day Now....awesome food and coffee! Customer service is great. Decor and atmosphere is a plus! Nice location. Vegetarian options available. Recommend the vegetarian kimchi scallion sandwich. Prices are reasonable. Plenty of seating.

Any Day Now is one of those spots that just feels good the moment you walk in — full of natural light, lush plants, and plenty of cozy seating that makes you want to stay awhile. It’s the perfect place to relax, catch up with friends, or just enjoy a great meal and coffee.

The Kimchi pancake is a m

LOVED this stop. This breakfast sandwich was a brand new flavor profile and I thought the kimchi was so delicious! It came with a side of chili oil too which was tasty. The ube latte was so yummy it was nutty and a little sweet and obviously so beautiful too! Awesome stop

Beautiful space and lovely staff, but the food is horrible. My breakfast sandwich came out drenched in mayo and what tastes like kraft cheese. The hash browns  were even sadder - they look just like the Trader Joe’s microwaveable patties. Everything is served in plastic (why???). Huge waste of money

A local neighborhood gem and officially my favorite cafe! It's such a comfortable co-working space to settle in and get work done - plus the food is amazing!

It's clean and inviting with a variety of food options that cover the globe. I opted for an Iced Masala Chai Latte which was perfect along wi

Walter’s is a perfect place to grab a bite before or after a Washington Spirit game at Audi Field. The food was good, the menu appropriately varied, service was fine (a little slow given how empty it was), and the atmosphere was classic sports bar but there’s plenty of outdoor seating and only a 10

Stopped here on my way home from D.C. and the food was delicious! The steak in the steak salad was seasoned so well and my burger was cooked perfectly. The old bay on the spinach and artichoke dip was the best. Can’t wait to go back.
A father's day gathering.  Nice sports bar across from the natz stadium. The food and drinks was pretty good and got great service.  Definitely a good spot to catch a game.

The location is perfect for pre-game or post-game gatherings at Nationals Park, or catching other sports with good company. Lively but not overwhelming; perfect for group banter without shouting. The outdoor patio offers a relaxed vibe for all ages. Our server was wonderful, she was very attentive a

I love everything about Walters! Great dinner options! Wonderful staff! And tons of TVs!

The bartenders are amazing everyone is so attentive and friendly.

It’s great for a family dinner too.

Me and a friend stopped by Royal Sands Social Club for happy hour during the week and had an overall great time. Since we went early it was surprisingly quiet and we pretty much had the place to ourselves. Their happy hour runs from 4pm to 7pm with some solid specials that we wanted to take try out.

Hosted a number of events here for my college’s alumni group, and they always welcome us with exceptional hospitality. Everyone speaks highly of the food, cocktails, and atmosphere! Thank you for hosting the Florida Atlantic alumni association time after time.

Had an amazing time at Royal Sands in DC! The vibe was great, and the service made the experience even better. Our server and bartender Mekhi was absolutely awesome—super friendly, attentive, and made sure our drinks were perfect the whole time. The cocktails were strong, well-crafted, and came out

A Tropical Oasis in the Heart of DC: Royal Sands Exceeds All Expectations!
Royal Sands is, quite simply, an amazing venue. From the moment you step inside, it's incredibly inviting, transporting you to a vibrant, sun-drenched paradise. It truly feels like a stunning piece of Florida, meticulously tr

We hosted a DC Graduate student mixer on Friday and the Royal Sands team made it so easy to reserve the entire second floor! They were very easy to work with and even offered to make themed cocktails for each graduate school in attendance! It truly was an unforgettable event and would recommend this

Was a guest at the hotel for a concert at Nationals Park the night before. This is a Hotel restaurant so my expectations are not that high. That being said it checked all the boxes. Honestly if the prices were better this would be a 5 star breakfast but at $92.00 for 2 people with no alcohol seems a

Had two breakfasts here and my wife and I and we were absolutely thrilled with the meals. Her waffle and French toast were perfectly prepared with huge amounts of fresh fruit and real syrup. My egg breakfasts were perfectly cooked, home fries were loaded with tender and sweet peppers and onions and

Food was good, service was slow, wait for table was very long, decided to make a reservation and came back at stated time, still waited some to get seated. Around 30 minute wait even with a reservation and the restaurant was approx 1/2 full. 1/2 the tables and the entire bar were not being used for

We dined here with the free breakfast credit that included in our stay at Thompson. The breakfast menu was great, with vegetarian option ( Shroom and Green powerbowl were my favorite!).

Service charge/tips are included in the bill when you charged to your room, double check the bill before signing

Food was decent, but service was atrocious, echoing most of the other reviews here.

I stayed at the hotel for three days, and as a World of Hyatt Globalist member, I got to try most of the entrées (complimentary one entrée and one drink for Globalists). My favorite was Shrooms. I was initially a li

Trouble Bird has such a great vibe especially by the fire pit outside. The atmosphere is cozy but still lively, perfect for a chill evening drink. I ordered the Midori Sour that was perfectly balanced and beautifully presented and the service was friendly. The space feels tucked away but still right

I rediscovered Trouble Bird about a year ago, I knew it as Maxwells, and if you notice that name is still on credit card statements. Anyway, all the mixologists are amazing humans. Justin, Chris, Drew Ian have come together to form an amazing team…even the shy bar-back is always working overtime to

Highly recommend this fun cocktail bar! We held a private event at Trouble Bird a couple of weeks ago, and it went so well! The location is perfect for a buy-out with a small group. Intimate enough while not feeling too small, and comfortable enough for everyone to sit and mingle.

Justin and Chris

Speakeasy atmosphere and pleasant attentive staff -- my bestie's fav hangout -- killer cocktails! Spent WAY too much $ at birthday celebration, but worth it!  Snack selection only for food - fish dip is spectacular.

I have loved this bar every time I've visited. The staff are super chill, the vibe is nice. It's relaxed and artsy without being too in your face about it. Their drinks are great, with good selection. I'm a big fan of their painkiller. They do have a happy hour too. My favorite part though is that t

Had the best time experiencing authentic Ukrainian cuisine at Ruta! We tried a variety of dishes and everything was unique and delicious.

Definitely recommended the Tsvikli beet salad, the Varenyky with an assortment of fillings, and the Bigos!

My personal favorite had to be the Meat Holubtsi (stu

Just in town for a concert. Looked up this place ahead of time. Booked reservation for 1 at 12 PM. Hostess seated me immediately and server Michael was attentive and answered any questions I had about menu. Atmosphere is very laid back and casual, loved the authentic vibes they tried to create. The

Tried Ruta recently and had mixed feelings. The food portions were on the smaller side, and overall the flavor was a bit bland—though that might just be authentic Ukrainian style.

That said, the cabbage roll was absolutely fantastic and easily the highlight of the meal. If you’re going, definitely

Wonderful service, borscht that warmed my heart, and lokshyna that absolutely melted it.  Do not miss the cherry varenyky for dessert!  Plenty of Ukrainian wine, beers, and spirits as well.  We feel so lucky that this restaurant is only a 10 minute walk from our house 💛💙

The restaurant was decorated with bright colors and Ukraine paintings, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere.

Service was friendly and attentive.

Lunch prices were reasonable and affordable, offering good value for the quality.

The dishes were freshly prepared, the portions were decent, though

This place has a pretty nice vibe, a full bar, and a big beer selection. Do know though the whole place is open air and only some of it is covered, so be ready for that. They have tons of seating but their is only street parking. Biggest down side for me is last time I was there I got a bunch of mos
QR code menu, pretzel, and cheese sticks were good. Great beer. There are plenty of tv's to watch sporting events

Met our oldest daughter and fiance for a visit and pre dinner snacks as we were passing through moving our youngest from NYC to VA Beach for a new job, partly bc it's pet friendly and we had our dog with us. They love this place and I can see why. Great atmosphere!! So fun

Mostly outdoor bar with make shift roofs and walls. Great atmosphere. Good location, near metro stops.

I was here in the rain and stayed dry. Good place to meet up with friends and coworkers and hang out.

The sliders are pretty tasty and will generally fill an adult human.

This is by far my favorite neighborhood bar. Friendly staff, excellent food, good prices. Even at their busiest I feel taken care of - they play the games I want to watch and make sure my glass is never empty. If you’re looking for a friendly, neighborhood bar, this is the one

I went to this place because it was nearby where I was and the fusion was interesting. The girl who helped us was so nice! We told her it was our first time there and she proactively gave us some suggestions. We got the avocado chicken bowl and it was delicious and healthy. Full of flavor. We tried

Ordered the bowl with brown rice and pickled cabbage/kimchi and steak. Also ended up going for a pulled pork taco to give one of those a try.

Overall I would give this meal a 4.5/5
Inside decore was nice. The best part was the staff, the guy behind the counter was more than helpful as this was my f

One of my must-visits when I'm in the area. I've always gotten the taco trio "house style" - based on a recommendation from a staff member my first visit - and have never been disappointed. You'll definitely want a fork but the blend of flavors within each taco are very complementary.

Takorean was given a high endorsement from an associate of mine to try while in Washington DC. They were not wrong.
Cleanliness. 4.5 of 5. The restaurant was well maintained and appeared very clean.
Service: 3.5 of 5. Staff was professional but not talkative to the customers. A little more interacti

Ordered a Bowl with half steak and chicken.

I wish they had noodles to go with the meal like some other local options.

It was good except for the salad portion which I did not like as much (-1 star).

I went there for my Birthday during a non busy time for was me and a hand full of people in the place. Seems like it would be busier in later hours. I ordered the seasonal food items the Meatiash and the watermelon burrata salad. They were both good for the most part the items had different spin on

Had an impromptu dinner out with the family and stopped at Emmy’s. It was our first time here but had drive past many times. We were greeted immediately after entering. We sat down and were told about the special by a very kind hostess/waitress/bartender named Paris. She gave us great recommendation

We were in the DC area for a short visit and decided to try Emmy Squared. It was a good choice. The food came out hot and didn’t take long at all. We plan to stop by again the next time we’re in town.

It’s exactly what you’d expect from Emmy squared.  Everything is consistent in flavor and texture and comes out as you’re used too.

We did a pepperoni and mushroom and their signature honey, pepperoni and Calabrian chili pizzas this time with an order of wings.

Always a great choice for delivery o

Was in town for work; stopped by chance, and the food was great! Josh recommended the Zia fries. He was very knowledgeable and was so attentive and witty! The pizza was good and had leftovers for lunch the next day. Will definitely be back when I come in town again!

I had the most delightful experience at Toastique today! From the moment I walked in, the atmosphere was fresh, vibrant, and welcoming. The food? Absolutely delicious—every bite felt like a perfect balance of flavor and nourishment. I do recommend trying Smoked Salmon toast, Whether you’re craving s

I try to come here at least once a month, and it always leaves me happy. I usually order the avocado smash and PB&B bow

Absolutely fantastic! I got the a juice and toast that far exceeded my expectations for grabbing a quick lunch. I was greeted as soon as I walked in and was met every step of the way by a different team member who elevated my experience. Jacob was a friendly face at the front, Kelsey quickly brought

So fresh, flavorful, and worth the hype!
I had lunch at Toastique today while in town for work, and I’m already wishing I lived nearby just so I could come here all the time! I ordered the salmon toast, the Defender juice, and a cold brew smoothie - and every single thing was absolutely delicious. T

Visiting toastique for the first time. I loved the environment, aesthetic food. The only thing i will check is for the avocado toast it had alot of vinegar, very acid to be an avocado toast, it has tomatoes which are already acid. So tiny vinegar will be better.

Weird that you can't sit at a table during happy hour when the place is empty. My Frozen drink was woefully small even for happy hour. It looked more like an after-dinner drink.

Very friendly host and enthusiastic wait staff.
The food was hit and miss for sure. It seemed like there are Cooks in the
Such a cute space with seating in the back area and a cute outdoor space as well! The cocktails were delicious!

Went to Orchard townhouse on a Monday with my bestie she got a glass of cab sauv and I got chamomile fields, which I loved. For appetizer we got the prosciutto & stracciatella, which was fantastic! Lastly, we split the burger and the kale Caesar. They were nothing to write home about but good noneth

Great spot to go for weekend brunch with refreshing takes on brunch classics. We ordered the potato latke with smoked salmon and the fried egg sandwich. Both were filling and simple while being memorable. Looking forward to returning!

This place was a fantastic little lunch find! 3 of us shared the kale salad with breaded chicken and the prosciutto dish, and it was perfect. The orange wine was refreshing and crisp in the perfect glasses.

The inside decor is cute and calming. Would recommend for a lunch stop along your High Line

If you want a place with a good beer selection and fun vibes, then this is the spot.  If you’re hungry, then maybe try another place first then come here for drinks….

We ordered the Mac and cheese bites but they did not have any Mac.. it was just fried cut up mozzarella sticks.  Which is great.. if
My boyfriend and I stopped here for a bite before a Nats game while we were in DC for Warped Tour 2025. The game got rained out, but the food was delicious and lots of options on tap!

First and foremost, be prepared to spend money if you come here. My bill was nearly $90 for just me. But, I had the best fried pickles I've ever had, a delicious chicken cordon blue grilled cheese sandwich, and many different craft brews which were all fantastic. The fruit beer in my pic is one of t

My best friend and I stumbled upon Tap 99 and loved what we saw regarding the drink wall. The staff was great in explaining how it worked, gave excellent recommendations, and the food was off the charts! Lots of TVs with sports games. Indoor and outdoor seating options. Highly recommend!

A very unique sports bar to have a few steps away from the stadium. There is a decent amount of indoor and outdoor seating. We got there a couple hours before the game and it was pretty empty but all the seating was filled within the hour. That gave us enough time to order food and get it fairly qui

🥗 CAVA – M Street, Washington D.C.

Date Visited: July 2025

Ambiance: 3/5
The space itself was fine—clean, modern, what you’d expect from CAVA. But the vibe at the counter was terrible.

This is nowhere near an inexpensive meal!
