This restaurant has a spacious interior, making it a comfortable place to dine and have conversations.

The portions are quite large, so it's best to order accordingly. The calamari had a slightly thick batter, but it was still tasty, especially with the accompanying sauce. The pasta had a well-bala

Pretty decent restaurant if you are craving for Italian cuisine
We tried the Arancini in appetizer.
In entree we highly recommend the Grilled Branzino and the Trottole chicken Pesto
Specially the Branzino had so much flavor and the sauce was awesome
Update 8/18
Visited north Italia for the second ti

info.name: Andy's Pizza Foggy Bottom
info.address: 2000 Pennsylvania Ave NW LBY# 014, Washington, DC 20006

reviews.text: I came here during my lunch break on a weekday. All the pizza options were available and I got the buffalo chicken slice. I don't make that much $, but the pricing was totally worth it. ($6 I believe) The pictures don't do it justice, but if you like NY style thin crust with that grease drip, you'll

Across the street from The Lombardy. Pizza was not cheap, but well worth the price. It is cheaper to mix and match enough slices for a whole pie. Secret Service Police eat there and maybe you should also. There were plenty of seats and tables right outside of Andy's door. This is a great place to si
Jaime made us really awesome margaritas and the slices were so so so good. The crust was perfect! The sauce was yumm!! I love this place!

Delicious pizza with a variety of unique and classic options. Even though it’s in a food court setting, the vibe was fun and casual. Great value for the quality and flavor. A solid spot to grab a bite if you’re in the area—definitely coming back! 🍕

I orders the margarita pizza with sausage.  Used Uber eats to have it delivered. It was pretty good but needed more cheese. Im used to big slices of mozzarella cheese all over my margarita pizza. I was disappointed.

info.name: Sixty Vines Foggy Bottom
info.address: 2200 Pennsylvania Ave NW Suite # 300R, Washington, DC 20052

reviews.text:
Pleasant surprise to find on Saturday night after a show at Kennedy Center. My wife and I were hungry after skipping dinner and found this place to grab a glass of wine and chacuterie board.

We were greeted by our amazing server, Janderson. He walked us through various wine selections, recommended

My new favorite restaurant.   A bright, beautifully-decorated space to enjoy a large selection of food and drinks at affordable prices.  My excellent server, Johnny, helped me decide on Creste di Gallo ($22), a rich, creamy pasta loaded with flavor.  Perfect for special occasions or any time.  Close

Had such a great time at dinner last night! I have been a handful of times, but last night was the best yet. Food was great, wine was tasty and fun to try, but the best part was how great Nijann’s service was! As a server myself, I really appreciate genuine suggestions and every single one was perfe

This is a great place on Pennsylvania Ave close to the Foggy Bottom Metro. Their ambience is extraordinary, menu selection quite expansive and great service.

We ordered the appetizers with the expectation that we will decide on the main course later. However their appetizers servings were so genero

UPDATE TO REVIEW FROM 7 MONTHS AHO
We've returned several times and enjoyed every visit. Favorite dishes (we try to avoid meat though they have many options if that's what you want)
wood fired cauliflower with swhipped eggplant
Roasted smashed fingerling potatoes
Beet salad with whipped feta, pistac

There are a lot of good options in this area, but every time I’m in the neighborhood I ALWAYS make a trip to Bandoola bowl.

I can’t recommend this spot enough; the food is delicious, refreshing, and filling and the staff are always friendly and incredibly helpful.

I usually get a tofu bowl with th

I had a chickpea curry bowl over salad and shredded cabbage. This was so fresh and light, great for a summer day. I think there were about 20 total chickpeas, so not enough protein. But it was really good, great flavors and textures. I like their allergen/vegan-friendly labeling. There was a long li

Very friendly and pleasant staff, always upbeat and welcoming. Have tried their noodles and brown rice with shrimp/tofu/chick pea curry, would definitely recommend the shrimp. The sauces are amazing, very healthy portion of vegetables and overall feel-good meal. Would definitely recommend. Would be
The food here is so good, so fresh and I was very impressed! I got a tofu bowl with spicy wheat noodles and enjoyed it so much!

Bandoola Bowl at Western Market,  is a gem for quick and flavorful meals. I frequent the place whenever I run errands nearby and am always impressed. My go-to is the pork spicy noodle bowl, which never disappoints. The roasted pork pairs beautifully with fresh, crunchy cabbage, romaine, onions, toma

I had a terrible experience at this business and I do not recommend you spend your money here. This restaurant is deceptive as it appears to be an elevated cafe experience but it operates like a greasy spoon diner.

A nagging desire for capuccino and a sweet pastry led me to Tatte. The cashier was p

I’m torn about the review. I’m not personally too impressed here but the food is not bad. There’s no clear indication of where the line starts or end. When it gets busy, the customers are basically on their own. The staff have very limited care. Duck hash meat was a little overcooked to me, husband

I visited The Tatte Bakery in Washington, DC, and had an amazing breakfast. The food was absolutely delicious, and the service was excellent. Everyone was friendly, attentive, and made the experience truly enjoyable. Thank you so much for a wonderful visit — I’ll definitely be coming back!

Stopped by Tatte Bakery and tried their special Honey Baklava Latte, breakfast, and the Pistachio Croissant. The croissant was absolutely amazing — buttery, flaky, and full of pistachio flavor! The latte was nice and unique, though I wish it had just a bit more of that baklava sweetness. Overall, a

Such a lovely, consistent coffee house and bakery experience. The environment and aesthetics are nice and relaxing, the food selection for pastries, sweets and meals are great. Love the new summer tea choices along with their tried and true coffee choices. Prices for drinks are similar to Starbucks,

Very convenient and nice location to get a bite by the Kennedy Center. Delicious food and friendly helpful staff! Food arrived hot and delicious in a really quick turnaround. Lots of seating available both indoor and outdoor. Would highly recommend if your hungry before a show or just in the area.

We had just one experience so far, but I really enjoyed it. Tazza is an amazing little casual eatery in the shadow of the Watergate in DC with indoor and outdoor seating.

Many Mediterranean dishes and artisan pizzas await the more developed palettes. Meanwhile, fresh, simple pizzas are available fo

This might be the best pizza I have ever had! The owner Mohamed is hospitable and kind and is really passionate about his food and his restaurant in general. Great atmosphere always bustling and great great food!

This place was perfect for what we needed prior to seeing a show at the Kennedy Center! It is super convenient and right across the street. You order at a counter and they bring the food to your table. Many choices and everything we got was great! The staff was so friendly as well.

Tazza: A Tried-and-True Favorite for Delicious Meals and Sweet Treats! 🍕🍰

Tazza has been my go-to spot for years, and it’s never let me down! Whether I’m craving breakfast, lunch, or dinner, I know I can count on them for a delicious meal every time. From the comfort of a casual lunch to a cozy din

What a great breakfast! Food was delish! I got a double egg, provolone, and tomato on asiago bagel. The line was out the door but they got us out within 15-20 minutes. Price is great and so good. We will be back multiple times on this trip!

Stopped in at Leo’s GW Delicatessen and tried the steak and cheese sub. Really tasty and very reasonably priced. The bread was fresh, the steak was flavorful, and the portion size hit the spot. There was a bit of a line when I went around 11 am, but that just tells me the locals know this is the pla

Holy Crap!! This is hands down the BEST breakfast sandwich I’ve ever had! Decided to try DW Deli so I stopped in and ordered a Bacon, egg, & cheese on a croissant and let me tell you…AMAZING!! The croissant is light and flaky, the egg and cheese are great, but the star of the show is the bacon! They

This place has all the bodega vibes and the food was great! Portions were huge so it more than justified the prices. Service was quick and staff were friendly even for it being 6am! Wish I worked in DC more often I would definitely make this place a staple!

This place is a time machine. Prices look like they were set in the 90's and frozen since then.

For $7, you can get a massive breakfast sandwich that, if you're a normal human being, will fill you up for the entire day and if you're a local college student, at least through your afternoon classes.

What a lovely find. This north Indian restaurant located in Foggy Bottom was a welcome treat after a hot afternoon on the golf course. Please forgive me in advance for not knowing the names of these items, but my descriptions should be helpful. The starters were an A+ we had roasted sweet potatoes (

Bindaas was definitely an interesting experience. At first, our server came off a bit distant—not particularly warm or friendly. But as the meal went on, he seemed to ease up and became noticeably more approachable.
I'll admit, I had some preconceived notions going in. When I heard we were headed to

We stopped by for Dinner. We were seated pretty quickly without waiting. We ordered Mango Pani Puri, Mysore Masala Dosa & Vada Pav.
Mango Pani Puri was interesting, I wouldn’t necessarily try again. Dosa was decent, the accompaniments were just okay. Vada Pav was good & filling.

The Samosas are hot and fresh - you get three.  If you only get one appetizer though, make it the Cheesy Tikka Fries.  They are special to behold across your plate.  Don't be fooled by the Chicken Biryani picture - it is a giant serving and delicious at that.  The Chicken Tikka Masala comes as mild

Spacious place. The food is good. Got Ragusa Pattice, paneer lababdar and loaded fries. All tasted good.
The wait for the check was quite long, it took them 20 mins just to get the check. Other than that the service was decent.

I went to Duke’s Grocery in Foggy Bottom and had an overall great time with friends. The service was decent, though our waitress wasn’t very attentive and we ended up waiting quite a while for the check, which was a little frustrating. That said, the burgers are excellent.

The star of the menu was

Solid visit for a burger and great happy hour deals. We went for dinner and the burgers were great, truffle Mac was excellent, and the bread pudding was lovely. Service was good, drinks were cheap, and atmosphere seemed dive bar meets knights of the round table with a few other oddities. I’d say, st

I placed an online to-do order after exploring the African American Museum, Lincoln Memorial and Washington Monument. Website was easy to use and it took about 20 mins before my order was ready.  My interaction with staff was brief but very pleasant. Burger and fries were delicious.
I hadn't been for a long time and went to the branch in Western Market. It was great, Fish and Chips was like in London, the atmosphere is always good anyway and I definitely recommend their burgers.

My friend wanted to visit here for brunch to get their English breakfast which he thoroughly enjoyed! I ordered the avocado toast which was delicious as well. Servers were attentive and prices were reasonable.

I give this place a 3 star I wasn’t too satisfied about the shrimp tacos I had for the price that I paid the tacos wasn’t what I would expect it didn’t give what it was worth but the fries were good. the service was amazing and the atmosphere was great
Great American style food with friendly service. Big size.

This review is for the Garden Cafe at the State Plaza hotel.

First amd foremost, the staff was a complete joy during my stay. Daniel, Jennifer, and Sharon were friendly, knowledgeable about the area and the foods here, and very responsive.

Morning coffee with them was such a relaxing way to start

This small restaurant offers excellent value for the money if you are looking for a quiet location for a social or business lunch and do not want to be rushed. The food is good quality and consistent.  Don't expect to be bowled over, though.  The coffee has improved noticeably since my last visit a
Very good service and lovely atmosphere. I got the salmon,onion, and cream cheese bagel and the portions were perfect, they did not skimp out on the salmon. The salmon was a bit salty though.

Pizza was super flavorful but it was basically cold when we received it. Service was not great, I think they lost our order or forgot about us which is why it took so long and was cold when it got to us. Every time I saw an employee they were on their phone. They also told us they couldn’t make any

We went for the large BBQ chicken pizza, and it did not disappoint. First of all, the crust was thin, crisp, and perfectly baked—light enough to not feel heavy but still sturdy enough to hold all the toppings without flopping over. Exactly what you want from a thin-crust pizza.

The BBQ sauce base h
I was looking for a local spot on a pub search. Rooftop bar had a great breeze and amazing views of DC life passing below!

Hive Bar is such a cool, vibrant spot with a great energy—you can tell it’s a favorite for both locals and visitors. The atmosphere is lively without being too loud, making it a perfect place to catch up with friends or enjoy a fun night out.The cocktail menu is creative and well-crafted; I tried a

We flew from Florida to DC for a wedding, decided to come her for a roof top bar experience. The staff at the bar didn’t greet us or acknowledged us while we were in front of them for five minutes. We asked if we could order there and the young woman just nodded, we asked a few questions and she kep

Food is great! Bread was a little dry, but nothing too bad. Good seating options! I got a turkey sandwich, and it was super delicious. I also got a cream cheese brownie which wasn’t as good as I expected. A great place to stop and eat casually.

everything looked delicious! grabbed a panini to go and it did not disappoint. you can also try their soups, the tomato and basil was great, chunky and with the perfect amount of salt. will be coming back!
Love the place , sandwiches made freh everyday
The best sandwich and salad place in DC.  The staff at this location are amazing--fast and incredibly friendly.  My favorite lunch spot.
Good chicken quesadilla. Large portion, cooked well.  Salads looked amazing. Yogurt parfait was delicious too.

info.name: a.kitchen+bar - D.C.
info.address: 1010 New Hampshire Ave NW, Washington, DC 20037

reviews.text: Friendly service, excellent cocktails, and nice ambiance. Enjoyed the squid salad, and the rock fish with clams, the lamb was tender but a tad over-salted. The panna cotta was divine. All in all, satisfying though slightly larger portions would have been welcomed. 😊

Very cool spot to hang out outside or have a romantic dinner, especially with candlelight and dim lighting. The food was delicious overLland the drinks (not pictured, but we had non-alcoholic cocktails). It was definitely more leisurely service, so a great date night spot if you want to linger. Soli

Fairly quiet brunch during our visit.  We had the added benefit of good service too. We had the wagyu steak frites, omelet, biscuits and gravy, and house burger. Probably the best biscuit I've had in recent memory.  No issues with any food despite the steak was slightly over medium.  Will try to go

Attended the event-A.BBQ SERIES with Kevin Tien of Moon Rabbit-on a pleasant, cool Wednesday night.  We were greeted immediately by a cheerful, attentive hostess who escorted us to our seating on the outdoor terrace.  Rain didn’t stop the show thanks to the high-tech, retractable canopy that was ins

A friend and I enjoyed a pricey lunch here during Restaurant Week. The chickpea panisse starter was a tasty eye-opener, an item that we had never tried before that tasted nothing like chickpea and came with an inspired sauce and accompanying items that made for an outstanding dish. My deconstructed

An unforgettable evening of Italian brilliance, made all the more special by Amanda whose warmth and attentiveness elevated the entire experience. From the first toasted bruschetta bursting with roasted eggplant, olives, and tomato basil sauce to the last forkful of airy tiramisu, Matera DC delivere

Simply superb. Matera has become my go-to place for a morning coffee, and a gathering spot for friends and colleagues. The food is delicious, and the service is always above and beyond!
I've hosted a couple happy hours and small events there, and they outdo themselves each time: greeting us with flo

A very small and cute restaurant nestled in the lobby of a hotel and just a few minutes from the Kennedy Center. Our visit however, fell short of expectations with the highlight being it's convenient location. The ambiance was great and appealing, the overall experience didn't leave us eager to retu

Matera is a friendly, cozy restaurant that attracts local residents as well as guests staying at the attached hotel.  The tomato basil soup was excellent.
Sakina was an outstanding server and took extra care both at dinner and the following morning at breakfast to ensure our meal enjoyment and comfo

When the woman greeting you speaks Italian, you know you’re in for something great. Very cozy atmosphere. Superb salmon, cooked to perfection at my request. Delicious tiramisu. I’ve lived in Italy and this darling restaurant was a great example of true Italian food. Highly recommend.

I ordered wonton soup, pork dumplings, shrimp egg roll, and chicken drunken noodles for appetizers — they were pretty decent.

Then for the main course, I got Chicken with String Beans and Pork with Garlic Sauce. The chicken dish had very little chicken, and the pork dish was a total disappointment.

We went to Washington, D.C., for the first time and enjoyed this beautiful city. We went to eat at some places, but one of our favorites is this place. A family restaurant with humble and kind attention. The food is so good. We went twice. If we visit this city again, we will come back to this nice

I was looking for a place to eat on independence weekend and they were open. I ordered combination fried rice, green onion pancake and spring rolls. Food had a little too much oil for my taste. I had green onion pancakes before in a restaurant in Los Angeles and they were awesome so I had high expec
Love this place! Good portion for the price and food soooooo gooood❤️ I usually get shrimp with lobster sauce but beef broccoli, sweet sour chicken are also good!

It's hard to beat the $11 lunch special, which includes a nice selection of entrees and a cup of soup.  I had Won Ton Soup and Chicken with Garlic Sauce.  Close to the Foggy Bottom Metro and a great place to stop for lunch on the way to or from the Vietnam Memorial, especially if you're on a budget.

info.name: Arepa Zone
info.address: 2000 Pennsylvania Ave NW Unit 11, Washington, DC 20006

reviews.text: This was my first time experiencing ArepaZone and the food was amazing! The customer service was great and my overall dinning experience was excellent! Thank you so much!

5 stars for 5 reasons

1. The tequenos are the best! They’re fresh, fatty and simply delicious!

The shredded chicken arepa was pretty good! Juicy chicken, arepa shell crispy and flavorful.

2. The green sauce goes well with the arepa and the tequenos! Good sauce!

3. Fast service food was ready for

Absolutely delicious!
I had the most amazing Venezuelan arepa filled with shredded beef, creamy avocado, sweet plantains, and fresh “queso de mano” — and it was a flavor explosion! The arepa was perfectly crisp on the outside and soft inside, and every bite had the perfect balance of savory, sweet,

Gluten free and a large serving for a reasonable price! Husband had a chicken with cheese one and I had a shredded beef one. The flavor was nice, but it was surprisingly greasy. The beef one had a pool of grease and was served so hot that I had a hard time holding it. We don't live where these are a
Yoooo!! Best empanadas Ive ever tried before!! Staff super friendly, they Also have this Little guys that Í used to eat back in Venezuela… ❤️

One of my favorite places for lunch!  While they mainly offer salads, there are choices of warm bowls and grilled wraps too—you can get it as is, or have it customized.  Lots of toppings to pick from.  Good variety of dressings too, and if you need, they can give you a sample of the dressing to try

First time visitor and had the Cajun shrimp salad. It was delicious, great balance of ingredients, and one hundred percent worth the price!
All the workers were kind and efficient. The facility is clean, modern, and easy to navigate.
Would definitely stop in again.
Value for money especially in this

This place was amazing and a great choice to stop into. We wanted something quick and easy to eat while being out exploring the city all morning. I had the chicken tinga which was amazing! Not thinking I would like the Kale, still got it anyways and was presently surprised by how amazing it was. We

Always a great experience with fresh ingredients. Chopt is apart of my ritual every Friday. Nothing like a fresh salad to end the week right. Fairly priced, so many options, and a pleasing atmosphere. You can’t go wrong!!

This Chopt location is fantastic! The staff is incredibly kind and friendly, creating a welcoming atmosphere. There's always ample seating, and the place is incredibly clean. Plus, being just a block away from the White House adds a unique touch to the dining experience.

Absolutely delicious. The lobster pieces were perfect sized. We ordered lobster rolls, old bay fries, clam chowder, and lobster Mac and cheese. I only have a picture of the fries because we weren’t patient enough to wait before digging in. Everything was perfectly seasoned and the flavors all comple

Mason’s Famous Lobster Rolls located in the Western Market food hall right by George Washington University (GW) off of 21st & Pennsylvania Ave. in DC seemed like a quick and easy spot to enjoy a classic Connecticut lobster roll with warm butter and some New England Clam Chowder w/ oyster cracker and

I had such a great experience at the register around 12pm on 7/24, thanks to the incredibly kind gentleman working there. His service was outstanding, so much so that I felt compelled to leave this review. He was genuinely friendly, engaging in real conversation instead of sounding scripted or going
Great lobster roll with large lumps of meat. I found the Classic Roll to be a solid choice. The lobster bisque is also a delicious, warm treat.

The classic lobster roll with lemon, butter, and mayo on warm toast was to DIE for! They stuffed it full of lobster and no fillers. So. Tasty. Highly recommend this place! Only complaint is that I kept wanting more.

I go around the DMV sampling all the taco places in search of one that reminds me of home. This place was not exactly authentic in flavor but the food was just ok. Zero spice but the meat and fish were cooked well. I wouldn't send people here if they wanted legit tacos but it's a good spot to satisf
Incredible food and party atmosphere! Birria tacos came in very clutch at 1 am after lots of reggaeton, salsa and merengue. Great speakeasy in the back unlike anything I’ve seen in DC so far.
Came here for a happy hour this summer and was blown away by the awesome bartending service, the ambience of the speakeasy, and also the HH food was reasonably priced and tasted really good!

We had a great time, the nachos were amazing and the frozen mango margarita is reallly good too. The service was really good, shoutout to Douby who was so nice and great! Would definitely recommend this place for a night out for drinks

As someone who frequents the Miami Beach location of Bodega and absolutely loves it, I was thrilled to see one open in Washington DC. Unfortunately, the experience was incredibly disappointing and nowhere near the standard I've come to expect.

To start, the restroom was completely inaccessible for

Carvings is a small, local deli in Washington, DC, where I recently picked up lunch to-go. It has the feel of a mom-and-pop shop, and with roots going back to 2008, it clearly has staying power. That said, the pricing structure left me scratching my head.
For instance, you can get a sandwich *with f
Good food! Got it togo. Enjoyed the atmosphere while waiting for food. Wasn't too busy for lunch. I'd eat here again.
Had their Rueban sandwich which was delicious! And the Joe's lemonade was really good too (didn't burn my throat nor was it too strong, like lemonade usually does/is)

Went here after doing the memorials. In a nice area, it was clean, staff was helpful. Menu was ok, prices reasonable. Food cooked to order, came out hot and decent portions. Not a lot of seats. Would go back.

Excellent place for a decent breakfast and good coffee.
The staff is super friendly.
Pancakes are a bit oily but extremely fluffy and soft.
Every thing very well priced too.
Overall a staisfying breakfast experience!!
Beautiful little spot with the vibes of a French cafe. Great meals and savory pastries. Good variety of coffee choices. Excellent service.
Get the croissant and you won't be disappointed. Hash browns were also out of this world. Coffee options are good. Prices are reasonable.

This comfy restaurant boasts a spacious seating area and is the perfect spot for a satisfying breakfast or an indulgent all-inclusive brunch on weekends. Located near West End, Washington, DC, it offers an impressive range of desserts, including delectable crepes, waffles, and cakes, alongside a sel

I wanted to love this place. From sourcing to ordering only to arrive and find out it’s a big disappointment.
The server/cashier/attendant/ whatever hat he chooses to wear, is terrible. I have to now sadly point out that I am an African American Black and he’s a black individual as well so my compla

I visited this location to enjoy breakfast with my family of 3 during a trip to DC for spring break.

We had the chocolate banana crepe, strawberry creme french toast and the big breakfast. The crepe and french toast was good and big breakfast was decent although I wouldn't call it a big breakfast (

The staff were friendly and helpful. We shared the chicken wings and chicken strips. I'm from the south. I was not expecting the chicken strips to be grilled. However, it was a happy surprise. Both items were juicy, flavorful and delicious. I did find the wings a bit spicy for me. I'm not a huge fan
Who-Dey!! Visiting here from Maine and  Bengals fans, this was a huge surprise to see this is a Bengals hideout for watching games!! Great food and great staff! Get the Wings!!

Bottom Line is one of those rare finds in DC that immediately feels familiar in the best way. Tucked away below street level, it has that classic basement bar vibe that reminded me of the great hidden spots in Chicago and Boston. The atmosphere is warm, lively, and just a little bit nostalgic, which

You’re clearly not coming for the food, which is pretty awful. You’re not coming for a quiet chat because you can barely hear your own voice. So, you’re probably coming for the atmosphere, which definitely transports you back into the 1990s. The service is friendly, the food is really bad and the am

The Bottom Line is such a fun hidden gem in DC! It has that classic dive bar feel—nothing fancy, but super welcoming and full of personality. If you're looking for a laid-back spot with strong drinks, good vibes, and no pretentiousness, this is it.

The staff was friendly and quick, even with a pret

Good food! You need to book a reservation if you go past 6pm. The whole place had reserved signs, even at the bar top seating which is where we sat. We got there at 5:30 and they told us we had 1 hour to eat, which was fine! The sushi was fresh, I would say a little on the expensive side compared to

We visited Umai Nori on Sat.
and had an absolutely amazing experience🥹

The food was incredibly delicious and the service was outstanding. Among all the sushi spots in D.C., this one truly stands out as the best. The quality of the dishes and the freshness of the fish were simply exceptional—it was

20th Wedding Anniversary, and this place absolutely lived up to its reputation. The reviews are accurate. 10/10. Ordered 4 set temaki hand rolls, followed by several additional individual orders. Also ordered the Donburi beef bowl. Both the bowl and set order came with excellent miso soup and salad.

My husband and I were in the DC area so we decided to give Umai Nori a try. I really like the ambience! Their salad was surprisingly good. It had a taste of peanut in its dressing. Nothing special about the miso soup. California Hand Roll was very meaty! It was a combination of real crab meat and im
I really enjoyed food. And also inside of restaurant is clean. Our server was so kind. I really want to recommend this restaurant if u like sushi or japanese food.

info.name: Saya Salteña
info.address: 1919 Pennsylvania Ave NW Suite GR07, Washington, DC 20006

reviews.text: Amazing tres leches and the sandwich combo was worth it for the price. The monochinchi was really pleasant aswell. Will be back to try the saltenas

Great service and great food. I had never had Bolivian food before and this was my first time having a saltena. The service was quick and when the food was done, I ate outside because the weather was nice. The saltena was very flavorful and it was a lot of food. However it was extremely messy but it

The salteñas from Saya are, without a doubt, the best I’ve tasted—not just in Washington DC, but even compared to some spots in La Paz, Bolivia. The staff is warm and attentive, and every bite of food is bursting with flavor. A true gem for anyone craving authentic Bolivian cuisine.

Discovered that Saya Saltena had finally opened around the corner from my office.  The store decor is amazing, and has a very inviting atmosphere.  The interior design is fabulous!  The staff was helpful, friendly and attentive.  The lunch was amazing. The flavors exploded with great textures and th

I only had mocochinchi, which is a spiced drink with a dehydrated peach.
It was nice and cold. Very refreshing after walking in the heat.
The fruit was a little bit hard. Maybe it was that batch.

OUTSTANDING local neighborhood sports bar. Am here visiting doing the monument/tourist thing with wifey, staying at the Hotel Washington and needed a place close to eat. Stumbled onto this place- advertised as DC's Oldest Sports Bar- and went in immediately. Food was delicious, recommend the Fish n'

The service was amazing.
I recently stopped by The Exchange Saloon at 1719 G St NW and had a fantastic time. A few highlights:
Service & Atmosphere: The staff were notably friendly and attentive—the bartenders chatted with guests, and service felt personal even during a quick stop before a nearby ev
The bartender was kind and attentive. He had some great recommendations. All the drinks were cold and tasty.
Genuine good guys that appreciated us stopping by! Buffalo Ckn sandwich and sliders were both good. Beers were cold and spot on. It’s my kind of place!!

We flew to DC from Texas and just happened on this neighborhood pub a block from the White House. BEST find ever!!! Turns out it’s the oldest sports bar in DC in a great location!
From the moment you walk in, you’re greeted with a friendly welcome, the bar/restaurant is clean with great lighting! I’

Everything was wonderful! We started with gazpacho appetizer -- beautiful presentation and excellent proportion (see photo).  The bream and snapper dishes were really good. The bream was cooked in an "igloo" of salt which imparted a nice flavor and not too salty. Shout-out to our server Antonio who

I tried it as a solo dinner experience during summer restaurant week in DC.
The ambiance and design were lovely. There was even live music.
The food was generally good. I ordered the Croquetas de Jamón Serrano as a hot appetizer. And as a seafood lover, it was absolutely delicious. It tasted a bit l
Fantastic Tuna salad, just like I grew up enjoying it! Mushroom croquettes were delicious, so we ordered twice. Paired w wonderful Garnasha for a great happy hour. Place is nostalgic!

Excellent spot for celebrating a special occasion! 5/5 in every single category. If you love a live performance with great service and food, you cannot miss Alabardero.

We went to celebrate my sister’s birthday - they sat us at a table with a great view to the flamenco performance, greeted us with

I highly recommend this classy restaurant. The food, ambiance and service is excellent!! We got great service from Elmer, and Maria. They were very attentive, excellent service. Kudos to them!
The flamenco performance as part of their scheduled programming is a treat for the eyes. Just beautiful!!

Red Derby is just one of those cool neighborhood bars that never disappoints. Cheap drinks, good food, and a super chill vibe — nothing fancy, just the right kind of comfortable. Red Derby is just the kind of bar we all ask for, cheap beer, good food, and vibes.

(My only complaint I miss when it was a exclusive "cash only" bar. For me, "cash only" keeps that night life vibe going. Dropping $100 - or $200 😆 - has that nostalgia for a Saturday night.).

A great neighborhood dive bar anytime of day or night. Always welcoming, smoking inside upstairs, great drinks, a solid burger, and phenomenal bartenders! You won't be disappointed you decided to hang out at Red Derby.

Super friendly and welcoming bartender. Great atmosphere, some games in the corner (scrabble, trivial pursuit, maybe 10-15 others) and even some books. Nice back room for private events and a rooftop as well. Didn’t try food but drinks were good and vibes were great!

The special jumbo crab asparagus is great. Everything else , the truffle dumplings was not really a dumplings, more like mini salty meatball, the scallops crudo taste a little fishy/funny  not in a good way, the duck drunken noodle was also mediocre disappointing. Overall all not worth the booking,

Fancy, good meal! Some of the best Chinese food I’ve had. We sat at the chefs counter so we could see the action. Small, intimate vibes. Delicious food. Joia definitely proved me I was wrong. Even though there’s only one burger on the menu with no possible extras, their smashed wagyu beef patty (had the double patty version) is a killer.

I was excited to try Joia Burger and Fries because the idea of their unique toppings and sauces sounded promising. However, the execution didn’t quite meet expectations. The sauces, made with diced vegetables, had too much moisture, which made the buns and fries soggy. On top of that, both the burge
Joia Burger is so good! The fried burgers were super tasty, and the ube ice cream with toasted coconut was amazing. Such a fun little spot in Mt. Pleasant, definitely worth stopping by.

Amazing experience. Different bbq than I have had before. Delicious and tasty. Varieties of sauce were also amazing. Dry ribs are the best. My wife and I both grabbed a two step, which is two meats of your choice and two sides. I got the pork

Customer service was okay, and you mostly do everything yourself. Big open

Sampler Plat

The

info.address: 3054 Mt Pleasant St NW, Washington, DC 20009

reviews.text: Bar del Monte is the kind of place that nails it with quality food and service, no glitz or glam needed. Menu appears to change often if not daily. Nice little herb garden in back.

The pizza was absolutely delicious, uniquely thin, and full of flavor. The porcini salad was wonderful.

Nothing we ate fell short of our highest expectations.

Two other unique things we appreciated:

1

Outstanding pizza and wow worth the hype! The dough was super thin, crispy and tasty. The lamb sausage pizza was truly one of the best pizzas I’ve ever had. Toppings were perfectly balanced and top quality. Even better than 2amys! Laid back atmosphere with very attentive service. A DC gem

In SC, I wasn't a big Smash Burger fan, but Allen, India, and Desiree served us the best Burger ever and gave us outstanding service.  We're big fans again, thanks to this crew. If you guys come to SC, we'll eat here every day.  One love. By the way, this crew needs 10 stars
Easy to grab a quick delicious meal with friendly customer service and recommendations for first timers . They don’t just have burgers you can also grab a hot dog or chicken as well .

Loved the Smash Chicken Burger alongside the fries! Extremely flavorful and the staff was equally amazing, helpful and friendly. I think I’ve found my new go-to spot for a quick bite to eat flavorful food.
Service could have been much better but the food was good. Pictured: Limited time Smoked Brisket Bacon Double, Sweet potato waffle fries and Peanut butter cookie shake.

The gentleman there were not friendly nor accommodating nor professional.

My family and I visted shortly after 1am since we got in to town late. The moment we walked in the guy behind the counter said "it's all take out". There was another patron that needed to use the restroom but they refused him

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ (11/10)
90 Second Pizza — 708 7th St NW, Washington, DC 20001

After a wild night (even got kicked out of 7-Eleven for just trying to charge my phone 😅), I ended up at 90 Second Pizza, and let me tell you — this place restored my faith in kindness and customer service.

From t

I popped in here for a late lunch. Ordering is all done with tablets, which were easy to use. By the time that I submitted my order to my pizza being done was just over 2 minutes. The worker had to help a customer so I’m sure it would have been even faster! I got the margherita pizza and I really en

Out new favorite pizza place on China town. As my son loves pizza we always explore new places but this pizza became our favorite place this time around. It’s very thin pizza and very delicious. It’s really is that fast and easy to prepare. Would really recommend this to anyone.
Not a place I’d sit and spend time at but great food, very quick and easy self-service. PERFECT for right before a game or show at capital one arena

Overall really good.
Atmosphere was nice. Reservations ahead of time but there were tables when we walked in as well.

Everything was seasoned well- on the lighter side. Favorites were the soondubu, galbi, and mandu.

wow. best korean food i’ve had thus far in dc. the appetizers were all very well done, especially the pickled radish. surprisingly, the kimchi was probably my least favorite one. i got the chap chae, and the flavors were fresh and subtle. generous portions with speedy serving. worth the price!

Overall, I’d love to come back here for the dumplings and bibimbap, and to try mandutguk next time.

The host, Andy, was very welcoming and friendly!  He recommended several dishes, including bibimbap, mandutguk (dumpling soup), galbi, and bulgogi.  We ordered everything except the mandutguk, and al

The portions are huge, and they give plenty of side dishes—actually, it was a bit too much.
My kid loved the rice cake and mandu soup.
I really enjoyed the yukgaejang—it wasn’t too spicy.
The dessert donut was delicious—a must-try!

Fantastic everything.
1 - Service.  Absolutely on point.
2 - Food was amazing 👏
3 - Felt welcome . Not some Angry hipster place that gets mad at you for patronage of their establishment.  ( looking at you pretentious burger joints )

Regardless,  this has been our best meal since our week in DC star

I ordered Matar Paneer (medium spicy) with one naan and half bowl of rice.
The food was flavorful — paneer was soft, gravy was authentic, and the spice level was just right.
Naan was medium-soft and fresh.
The portion size was decent for one person.
Total bill: around $24.
Overall, a good Indian foo

It’s hard to find a place that sells a decent Naan pizza.  So I was quite excited to get a garlic naan / paneer pizza.  As much as I want to give it a higher rating, the chutney was sort of standard for American Indian food.  The lack of any Indian people dining at, or working at, the establishment
Great spot for great food. Don’t order the pizzas or bowls, get a dosa or uttapam or Vada pav. Great for cheap, fast, good Indian
Delicious food with generous portions! Highly recommend the dosa, and the vada pav was fantastic too.

I’m visiting DC for a week and decided to try Spice 6, around my hotel corner.
The inside is clean, has ample seating, though not for large groups. You pay and pick up your order within 5 minutes.
It was especially cool that the few folks dining in were from other nationalities enjoying the food. I

This Nando’s location is always a favorite of mine in DC! The staff is super friendly, the atmosphere is lively, and the chicken is always fresh, juicy, and packed with flavor. I love the variety of sauces—they keep my taste buds happy every visit. Definitely my go-to spot for a delicious meal in th

Great Vietnamese restaurant - delicious and affordable food with portions larger than average. Convenient location, the line was short and moved quickly. The staff were polite and eager to help. The music was quiet, which was especially nice compared to other places we visited in the area.

The food was delicious and the atmosphere was fun! Such a great variety of flavors and textures on the rainbow bowl!! I’m not a fan of everything that was on there in concept, but once I started eating it, I couldn’t stop myself! Completely cleared my plate!Not really a quiet place to sit and talk,

Great food and great service! The process of placing an order from our phones was a little challenging but worth it. The food was amazing and fresh. They even have a kids menu. The staff was incredibly helpful.

I had the 1/4 chicken breast with a side, and since I can’t handle too much spice, the mango lime level was perfect. The chicken was cooked really well—tender and not at all chewy. My only tip: avoid sitting near the kitchen, because when they were frying with spices, the air made us cough quite a b

Definitely packed on the crab on the crab roll, which was nice, pickle was solid, and the Cape Cod chips are excellent. The clam chowder, solid. The lobster bisque, too watery. Bathroom requires a code. Street parking. On the receipt the address is 1705 H St NW instead of the 800 17th St NW address
What a delicious little spot! Had the seafood trio with a shrimp, crab, and lobster roll. Fantastic! Highly recommend it and it's only a couple blocks from the metro/train.

Luke’s Lobster Farragut is my go-to lunch spot downtown. The lobster rolls are always fresh, buttery, and perfectly seasoned — tastes straight out of Maine. Quick service, friendly folks, and a chill vibe that makes it easy to pop in and out. Pricey, yeah, but totally worth every bite.

First time at Luke's, we had high hopes for this place but it's not worth the money we paid for our lunch, the only good thing about the sandwich was the bread. The poppy seed slaw tasted a lot like vinegar, I only took a bite and had to leave it because of how bad it tasted. Service was only one pe

My experience was okay. The lobster roll was piled high with incredible tasting lobster. However, I had ordered it warm and I could still tell that the inside of the claws and meat was still a tad cold. However, the bread that it's served on is amazing, and the seasoning they put on top is fantastic

10 on 10.
People call it indian chipotle. Quality is fresh and service is quick.
Quick service restaurant, variety of options to pick from plus chef curated plates and bowls.
Definitely recommend !
We got spicy chicken and make your own!  Flavors are bold  and spice is real.

Ordered take out via uber eats. I was looking for something balanced and they had a buy one get one free special which was a win for me. I got the spicy chicken chili bowl and then Tandoori paneer bowl

Tandoori paneer- 4/5 it was my first time trying this protein substitute &  it was surprisingly d

It was my first time visiting this restaurant, and I decided to go because my co-worker highly recommended it. As a big fan of Indian cuisine, l was impressed by how flavorful and delicious the food was. I loved how colorful the interior was the vibrant atmosphere and friendly staff made the experie

This is a great build-your-own-bowl style spot for lunch. They have a variety of proteins, vegetables, toppings, and most notably, lots of free hot sauce for you to add to your taste. They have tasteful premade bowls as well, if you're not feeling creative. Service was fast and there was adequate se

Stopped at this place on a whim after an endless day of walking museums and in the rain. We were greeted  kindly by the staff and treated to some of the best best casual food that felt more like sit down restaurant quality.  We live in a north dallas community called Highland Village / Flower Mound
The wings were pretty good. They were a decent size. They were well cooked. Flavor was typical Buffalo flavor. Staff was very friendly and attentive. The place was clean.

The food at this restaurant is solid! For starters we had their hot honey wings, those were amazing. For our mains we had the Philly Cheese steak and the Triple Double smash burger! The sandwiches were hot, the fries were hot, and of course everything tasted great! This place also had 40 TVs lol gre

We got lucky when we stumbled upon this tavern! We sat upstairs were there was a few less people, a beautiful view, stunning bar top and plenty of tv's to see whatever sport you wanted....yes including the bathroom.  The food was fantastic! Our service was so kind to give his opinion about different

when in DC , especially near the National Mall and museums, your food options are pretty limited. Penn Quarter offered a great outdoor area to grab lunch and people watch!  food was good. ordered wings, Buffalo Chix Wrap, quesadilla and a " Bar-be-Que" burger. had an issue with my burger (spoiled me
If I could rate them a 10 * on the service I would. Every employee that passes your table will help with cleaning dirty dishes, or refill drinks. The Shark Bite Mahi Mahi bites are perfection!

Ammathar Thai Cuisine is a great spot for authentic Thai food with a cozy and lively atmosphere. The flavors are bold and well-balanced across the dishes, and everything feels freshly made. The grilled chicken with sticky rice was a standout — perfectly seasoned, juicy, and paired with the sticky ri

Local go-to Thai spot. I ALWAYS order the Soft Shell Crab, which is perfectly fried and accompanied by a spicy yet tasty sauce. The past few times we have tried the Whole Flounder (pictured here). They tend to fry it a little too deeply, but it still is solid. My wife really enjoys the Thai Iced Tea
Authentic thai restaurant. Super fast service and great food. I had the Tomyum noodle soup and Chicken wings for dinner. Everything was so yum.

My friend and I went to this Thai restaurant for the first time. Service was great, but there were some other not-so-good things.

The table had crumbs on the seats, which implied to me that it hadn’t been cleaned. The food was not so good too. The veggie spring rolls were mostly batter and had very

Solid spot for classic, decently affordable Thai food at a cozy, no-frills spot located on 14th Street and just a few blocks away from Logan Circle. I dropped by Ammathar for dinner with a friend who was visiting from out of town and deeply craving Thai iced tea, and we had a great time here. It's a

Great food, music, atmosphere and service with books and poetry. What a great combination! This place is great!

Can’t say enough about how much we like Busboys & Poets! We love what they have going on here.

We came for breakfast on a Saturday morning. It was not busy so we were able to quickly gra

I visited Busboys and Poets 450K 3 years ago celebrating my birthday in DC and I had an amazing experience. Not sure if Ebonne still works there but she treated me with total kindness. She suggested some of her favorite items on the menu  which made it so easy for me to choose what I wanted to eat.

Busboys and Poets was such a vibe! I came in for brunch and had the catfish and grits with a couple of mimosas. 100% hit the spot. The catfish was perfectly seasoned, crispy on the outside and tender inside, and the grits were creamy and comforting. The food alone would have been enough to win me ov

A very sweet place in D.C. that offers vegan and „classic“ breakfast. We came for a relaxed breakfast and had a great time. Kiki, the super sweet and caring waitress was such a sweetheart and was taking care of us perfectly. I ordered the vegan Hash Dish and it was delicious.
The interior is great a

Review: Fried Chicken & Burger at Busboys and Poets – A Cozy Comfort Food Hit

I visited Busboys and Poets recently—half craving comfort food, half just needing a relaxed space to unwind. As usual, the place had its artsy, welcoming vibe, but this time I was there for the food. I ordered two of thei

We went for the first time. We heard a lot of good things of it and we were looking forward to expectation. As we entered the overall interior was good. I don’t know but there an unpleasant smell in atmosphere. We were dined in by our host and were given menu. We order Pani Puri for appetizers first

Came for an early dinner, the service was basic but efficient and the food came out quickly. The curries could do with more spicing and were a bit bland but were good enough. The pani puri starter was the best and most flavoursome part!

We ordered chicken steam momo, chilly chicken momo, goat sekuwa and chicken chowmein. Except for chicken steam momo everything else tasted average or below. There’s a room for improvement! But the location, and ambience and service were quite good.
The decor was beautiful. The service was prompt and courteous. The food was fresh and delicious. I wholeheartedly recommend the butter chicken and garlic naan.

Very pleasant. I like how quick and straightforward (and at the same time polite) the servers were, our food got in quick plus their momos jhol was delicious! Me and my brother shared all of it together. Overall it's good. A hidden gem, imo.

I visited Tatte Bakery and café recently in my trip to DC, it was a really nice experience overall. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, and had a lively and fresh vibe which makes it a great place to relax or catch up with friends. The location is also very convenient. The coffee was good, however,

Picked up breakfast for everyone during our family trip. All the pastries were pretty good, but the standout was definitely their iconic fluffy croissant—so light and delicious. The chocolate bun was also solid. There was already a line early in the morning on a weekday, which says a lot. I’d defini

Recently visited one of the Tatte Bakery and Café location in Washington, DC (New York Ave and I Street).
For those of you who are not familiar with these modern chain of high-end, fast casual cafes, Tatte's menu blends American, European, and Mediterranean influences, offering a wide array of scrat

Great bakery! Drinks were a bit slow, but the lamb pita was delicious. There was plenty of spiced lamb (actual lamb) meat with a tasty labneh drizzle stuffed in the Fluffiest pita I’ve ever eaten! They even give you the cap to eat…nice touch.

Matcha latte was good but not sweet at all so ask for sw

My Americano was also underwhelming. On the bright side, the staff were genuinely friendly, and the inte

I recently ordered from Sol Mexican Grill for the first time in person to go, and it was an excellent experience from start to finish. I tried the fish taco with yellow rice, black beans, lettuce, avocado, and what I believe was a queso sauce. The flavors were fresh, balanced, and absolutely delicio

I had a very disappointing experience with the food. Neither the fish taco nor the chicken burrito tasted authentic. The fish in the taco was so unappetizing that I had to spit it out. Additionally, the chicken in the burrito was dry with very little of it in the wrap, this a 80% rice, 19.5% vegetab

We were drawn into this restaurant by the $2.75 tacos for taco Tuesday. These were pretty uninspired tacos, but they were fine. We both got two carne asada tacos and they came with two toppings and a salsa. I tried both the spicy and medium salsas. The spicy wasn't very spicy. The medium was better
Good fast food Mexican restaurant near the Washington Convention Center. Quick service, good fish tacos, indoor and patio seating, and reasonable prices compared to most of the local restaurants.
Ummm, YUM! The quesabarria was fresh, flavorful, and simply fantastic. A lot of cheese and the jus with white onion and cilantro was "awesome sauce!"

info.name: Urban Roast
info.address: 916 G St NW # C-2, Washington, DC 20001

reviews.text: Urban Roast has been on my radar forever, and the other day I finally wandered over to peek at the menu… only to realize they were OPEN during the afternoon.  The real surprise was what waited inside. From the street, you’d never guess there’s a full-blown holiday wonderland tucked behind those door

I've been in Urban Roast several times now when I've been in the area. It's a quaint little spot for brunch, cocktails and everything in between. They have creative spirit-forward cocktails and delicious crave-worthy entrées. I had a mango martini that was delicious paired with a BBQ brisket sandwic

I loved everything about this spot! The décor and overall ambiance were gorgeous.I ordered the breakfast board and a marshmallow cappuccino, both of which were so good.

While my boyfriend and I were there a photographer came around taking professional photos. We ended up buying ours and they even c

It's a high price to pay for the vibe. I know this was Christmas themed and they really leaned unto that but for a flight of espresso martinis and the hangover board ended up costing me $100 after tip ($86 pre-tip). The hangover board was delicious and worth the cost but overall the price left me wa
The ambiance was amazing. The staff was friendly. The drinks were superb. The food was good. I've been wanting to visit this place for a minute.

info.name: Sfoglina Downtown
info.address: 1099 New York Ave NW, Washington, DC 20001

An excellent waitress, Maria helped guide us to a Ceasar salad unlike any other! The dressing was truly spectacular! The warm spiced apple butter cake was enough to f

Super sweet staff!! We got to celebrate one of my co-workers for her baby shower and the staff were so sweet. They have delicious bread with this herbaceous butter. 🧈 I got the spicy vodka sauce dish with grilled chicken on the side, absolutely delicious!! They also wrap up your leftovers in a cute

As close to a 10/10 as you can get. Fantastic food, service and atmosphere. YOU HAVE TO COME HERE.

I searched online for “Italian near metro Center dc”, and stumbled upon the trusty Reddit and fellow Google reviews folk’s opinions for “life changing meatballs” and “excellent meatballs”. I can’t go

Sfoglina was absolutely incredible. Oscar R was our waiter and he was truly exceptional. He treated our children with real kindness and genuine care and it made the entire experience feel welcoming and relaxed. Every suggestion he offered was thoughtful and completely on point. The food was outstand

Made a reservation at Sfoglina yesterday evening. The moment we walked in, we were greeted by the kindest man—he literally goes out of his way to make sure your experience is top-notch! Our server was Alejandro, and he was beyond wonderful and kind.

The food? Out of this world delicious. My husband

My visit to Gordon Ramsay Street Burger in Washington, D.C. was a genuinely enjoyable experience from start to finish. The restaurant has a modern and relaxed atmosphere with a casual layout, comfortable seating, and upbeat energy that makes it a great spot for both solo dining and small groups. The

Eric was our server and he was honestly amazing. He made sure everything we ordered fit our preferences, especially making sure there was no bacon or alcohol in any of the dishes. He was patient, respectful, and super attentive the whole time. If I were the owner, I’d definitely keep him and give hi

We celebrated our wedding anniversary here today and couldn’t have asked for a better experience. The server was warm and attentive, kindly honoring our request to have a message written on the waffle and even presenting it with a candle—a beautiful, thoughtful gesture. We also enjoyed burgers, pizz

I’ll start by saying the service here was exceptional. I arrived a few minutes before opening and was standing outside on my phone when the manager (unfortunately forgot his name) kindly invited me in as soon as the doors opened.
He seated me right away, engaged in a bit of friendly small talk, and

Amazing little place! We tried the chicken and beef burgers, and they were delicious! Wish they had more chicken options but the one they have is pretty good. The hotter than hell fries were bleh, can skip them! Servers are polite and attentive. Another highlight was the free arcade games section in

It feels a little harsh to take off two stars from a place that gets so much right, but for me, the food just didn’t quite live up to the rest of the experience.

The atmosphere, service, and energy were fantastic. The bar seating setup was such a fun concept. I loved watching the chefs in action, c

minibar by José Andrés is a restaurant that I've been most eager to experience.

Firstly, I want to say that to describe it as an "experience" is an apt adjective.

This is indeed a "miniature bar" a dining experience shared with 12 people. Obtaining a reservation is a bit difficult (I followed the

An absolutely unforgettable dining experience — far beyond just “dinner.” From the moment we arrived, every detail, both big and small, was flawlessly executed. The ambiance struck the perfect balance between elegance and warmth, setting the tone for an evening that felt extraordinarily special from

I don’t often leave a review but they went so over and above I feel it needs a mention. This is the 4th time I’ve been to the minibar where food meets science meets art is this elaboate food experience.  It was my birthday, I took my two older sons for this special occasion. The first time I went to

The food was excellent. But we felt that the quality-to-price ratio, similar to Jônt, was lower than other Michelin Star restaurants in DC.

We spent $548.21/person (including mocktail pairings, tax, and service fee) for less food that was less delicious and more expensive than Little Pearl or Pinea

Went there for a quick bite because I had been craving for a good ol’ kaathi roll which is quite a task to get in DC/VA. Ordered the chicken puff and the lamb roast kaathi roll and both were delicious. Honestly, the chicken puff was just great— the puff was flaky and the chicken stuffing was just se

I came across this gem of a place while searching for an Indian restaurant. The food was amazing, we tried Samosa, bombay sandwich (which was like Vada Pav), vegetarian kathi roll and the bowl. Everything tasted so good. We also had a chance to talk with the Chef Ajay, who happens to be from where I

The food tasted wonderful. It was mild and easy to enjoy, which makes it perfect for anyone who isn’t really in the mood to eat or prefers something non-spicy. You can tell the chef put real effort into preparing it because every bite was delicious. I genuinely loved the food. It was very, very tast

Glad we chose this place for our afternoon meal.  Ordered Masala Chai, Chicken Kathi Roll, Paneer Biryani, Samosa. Good Ambience, excellent food taste. Chef Ajay has pleasant personality and we enjoyed the conversations.
Close to museums, nice cozy fresh atmosphere, quick service, and tasty food options. Would recommend: bowls, curry puffs, and Indian mango beer.

What’s good:

The best is mango sticky rice.
Massaman curry was decent although abit thick.
Food is freshly made and comes out piping hot.

What needs improvement:
Chicken wings only has drumsticks no “wings”
Pad Thai was covered with tamarind sauce it was too sweet and too salty.
Kra pao with pork

So good! One of the best pad sew's I've had! The portions were huge and the noodles were thick and chewy which I loved! The flavor was on point and seasoned well. The thai iced tea was great too, and my husband enjoyed the khao soi.

The fried tofu was the only dish we felt was average/bland, but en

Tasty standard noodle dishes like pad see ew and pad thai. Quite large portions as well.

Tom yum soup was also good. Service was great. Easy walk from either Gallery Place or Judiciary Sq metro.
DELICIOUS. Pad Thai with chicken and mango sticky rice and Thai tea. Very affordable and enough to take half home for leftovers. Great atmosphere

This was awesome, the best Thai my wife had ever had. I thought it was really great too! As many Thai places (in my experience) the focus is always on the food, and this place was no exception. I had the drunken noodles which were great and my wife had the flaming beef. The appetizer of minced spicy

We attended a wedding reception at The Henri and were absolutely blown away from start to finish. The space was elegant, modern, and perfectly set up for a celebration intimate yet lively, with such thoughtful details in the layout and lighting. The staff were exceptional: attentive, kind, and incre

As a wedding / event photographer, I have the opportunity to work at many venues across the city, but my experience at Tjhe Henri was truly outstanding. From the moment I arrived, the staff was incredibly professional, kind, and accommodating—not just to the couple and guests, but also to vendors li

Overall the good was good not great. At the price point it was not good enough to return. The steak and the chicken tasted ok. The lobster was fine. Nothing blew me away and nothing stood out as a must have of the mains. The apps were better than the mains. All that being said , the service was outs

Belgium (former owner) and French (executive chef) influence can be easily felt throughout the dishes. Each dish, is refined, flavorful and well prepared. The cocktails were original and delicious. As a Frenchman, I was most impressed by the snail croissant. I would have never expected this dish to

The Henri is a nice balance between cozy and modern, creating a comfortable yet stylish atmosphere. Service was on point — our server was attentive and always nearby when we needed something.

Everything we ordered was delicious, from the food to the cocktails.

Today I visited Dos Toros Taqueria in Washington, D.C., and the experience was excellent. Wendy took great care of me — very friendly and attentive — and the food was delicious. I had a bowl with Mexican rice, pico de gallo, and steak that, to me, tasted very similar to arrachera. It was really good

It rivals chipotle. Wished they had plantains tho, I had a bowl it was very good, place was cleaner than expected considering the location. Service was bi lingual too. Amazing Mexican food! The food came out quick, fresh, and full of flavor. Every bite was delicious — you can tell they put love into what they make. Super satisfying, great service, and overall an amazing experience. Definitely coming back!
The food is really good, and the service is great. The place is really clean as well. Id like to thank Abigail a lot and look for her when you come

I visited this restaurant and it exceeded my expectations in terms of food, attention and atmosphere. A peaceful atmosphere, ideal for going with the family to enjoy a good meal!! I only give 5 stars to this restaurant, because you can not give them more, I liked it too, because everything was very

It's clear why this place is a local favorite – the welcoming atmosphere and consistently delicious food speak for themselves! We were impressed with how quickly the amazing staff accommodated the crowd and got us to our table.

Our breakfast was outstanding: a hearty western omelet with wonderfully
