Very nice suprise and change of pace from most downtown places. Dont be detoured by the hustle and bustle. The food is really great, especially for the price. The price is a little higher than what is listed on Google but still reasonable. The service was very friendly and on top of things despite t

This was a little gem across the street from Ford's Theater. Don't expect anything fancy or high-end. I would set ego aside and enjoy. It's delicious, fast, and has great service. I got the scrambled eggs with sausage, home fries, and a waffle. My wife got a BLT. Our waiter was very down-to-earth bu

Do you want a simple and efficient breakfast menu that serves you quickly with home style food and nothing crazy fancy or with a name you can't pronounce? Do you not care about decor or vibe? Then come here! Their food and simplicity is exactly what we needed on a morning out rushing to begin our tr

info.name: Café du Parc
info.address: at Willard InterContinental, 1401 Pennsylvania Ave NW, Washington, DC 20004

reviews.text: We went for Sunday brunch and had the eggs benedict, French onion soup, house salad, and a kids roast salmon. Everything was very tasty and we were particularly impressed with the presentation and quality of the kids meal with the mashed potatoes and green beans. The environment was lovely and class

French food is ooh la la! From escargot to the french croissant and chocolate mousse, everything here has been divine to my taste buds. The coffee is not cheap. It is top quality. You can sit outside on the patio and enjoy the beautiful scenery. Who knows, you may come across someone famous!

We were walking back towards our hotel when we passed by this spot. We were seated right away outside (our choice) and chose to participate in their Restaurant Week menu. Ended up sharing french onion soup/crab cakes + ny strip/scallops + creme brûlée/peach basil tart. It was a great menu deal and a

I hit up Café du Parc at 1401 Pennsylvania Ave NW, Washington, DC, for a bite, and it was a solid experience with some real French vibes right by the White House. This place, tucked into the Willard InterContinental, feels like a Parisian café with a DC twist.
I grabbed a spot on their outdoor terra

I settled on the eggs benedict with smoked salmon. The food was great, the poached eggs were just about 30 seconds under cooked. The experience itself was amazing. The restaurant was gorgeous, but the service could use improvement. There were approximately 5 people serving. We had 3 tables around us

Laos In Town offers a spacious and inviting setting with plenty of seating both indoors and outdoors, making it a comfortable spot for groups or a casual evening out. The overall experience was quite enjoyable, friendly service, a vibrant atmosphere, and a good variety on the menu.

In terms of the

The food exceeded our expectation! Each dish was unique and each one surprised us.
We highly recommend the Main with glassnoodles and mixed seafood on top, it had sweet and sour taste. The chive starter was really tasty, the sausage one starting with M down the menu also really delicious!! Madeline

This is the kind of restaurant that should be IMPOSSIBLE to get into. The food is guaranteed to be unlike anything you’ve had. It really stands out among all other southeast Asian restaurants in the DMV. It is distinctly Laotian, and I love that they don’t try to play in to the Asian fusion gimmick.

Great friendly, airy spot for well crafted food. The decor is eclectic but not cluttered. A feature is adorned fish traps suspended from the ceiling. Open kitchen and the dining area across is lined with birches. The design and operation both seemed thoughtful and efficient, leaving the overall impr

We ate lunch before heading to airport. When you walk in they have all types of product at the door. From things like soaps t-shirts and food products. It looks like a very upscale restaurant. It has a very casual atmosphere and we were able to talk with not much noise. The staff were very welcoming

info.name: Ted's Bulletin - Noma
info.address: 1005 First St NE suite 3, Washington, DC 20002

reviews.text: Ted's was conveniently located a few doors down from the Washington Marriott Capitol Hill.  It offered outdoor seating under a covered awning for shade from the sun & rain.  Ted had an extensive lunch & dinner menu but also an all-day breakfast menu with very generous portions.  They serve everythin

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Ted’s Bulletin in Noma, and I must say, it far exceeded my expectations. Rating it a solid 4.5 out of 5, this spot truly offers a well-rounded and delightful experience for the cost. From the moment I stepped in, I was impressed by the cleanliness and aesthet

My daughter and I were in town for the Cowboy Carter concert and stopped here for brunch before heading home.  We were initially hesitant because it was very crowded and we had less than 2 hours to eat and walk to the Amtrak Station. However, we were seated right away! The food came out quickly and
Great street corner upscale bar and diner! I was alone. I had great service, a fantastic breakfast burrito and finally one of the best negronis I've ever had. Great atmosphere and plenty of traffic.

I recently got the chance to go to Ted’s bulletin in Noma with a close friend and I loved it. We haven’t caught up in a while, so it was a good time catch up over some great food. The big Mark breakfast was very filling and had everything I could see in a breakfast. If it had a pancake that would’ve

One of the best dining experiences I’ve ever had. The atmosphere is so nice at night. Seat yourself, order on the phone. The bartender is an artist!! Delicious food. Some of the best Indian food I’ve ever had. Everything Vegan is clearly labeled. Could not recommend more on a summer night!

This place was absolutely amazing, i’ve been meaning to go here for ages and it did not disappoint. The prices are a bit high, but it’s DC and the food is incredible.
We got the spicy keema curry and the Indigo special, both of which were incredibly flavorful and delicious. Spice level is manageable

Ambient place but food can be much better. They usually make less spicy so everyone can eat. But some dishes were bland and have no taste. I hope they can increase a little spice level and make dishes more flavourful. Overall experience is good.

Excellent food but not the best place ive been. really good portion. I wasn't a fan of having chickpeas with my rice.  It was good but I rather not have them. I can't give a 4 star because prices are still a little too high for me and the side sauces from inside aren't the best
Nice size place that

Went here on a whim with my girlfriend and it was more than lovely. The atmosphere was perfect to match the perfect portion sizes — I couldn’t have shown up more hungry and I was almost able to finish the entire chicken tikka masala meal minus a few bites. You also seat yourself, order off the QR co

Our experience at Marcus DC was outstanding from start to finish. The cocktails were incredible, and the food was both unique and delicious. Chuck B’s Roast Chicken was the standout dish of the night as it was perfectly cooked and full of flavor. We were also pleasantly surprised by the seasonal can

The atmosphere of this restaurant was beautiful, warm and welcoming.

We started our evening with drinks and I decided to try this non-alcoholic drink “Addis Sol” that our waiter “G” said he put his approval stamp on and to my amazement, It was super delicious!

The flavors of the food were pronounc

We had the pleasure of celebrating my birthday at Marcus DC, and it was an unforgettable experience from start to finish. Chef Marcus Samuelsson’s newest restaurant is a masterclass in culinary storytelling—each dish beautifully crafted with depth, heritage, and imagination.

We began with the blue

Feels like home. Tastes like home. Smells like home. Marcus must be home cooking elevated to the Heavens. From the kindest reception and drink recommendations from the homies, even after arriving late for our reservation, to the man G who lived to serve us, our experience was through the roof. Style

Marcus had been on my list for a while after seeing it featured among D.C.’s top new restaurants, so I went in with pretty high expectations. While I wouldn’t call it a 5/5 experience, there were definite highlights: especially the cornbread and both desserts, which were absolute standouts.

That sa

The happy hour menu is a great deal! 1.25$ oysters, 6$ sliders and a 9$ shrimp po boy with fries! The food isn’t amazing, but good enough for the price

I’ve read the reviews about the noise level and poor service. The bar area can be particularly noisy. I would suggest sitting in the dinning area t

I really enjoyed my time at this spot. The drinks were great, I loved the oysters, service was on point, and the pricing was very reasonable. The atmosphere is super cute and makes for a nice night out. The only downside was the parking, which was a bit of a headache. Other than that, definitely wor

Happy Hour is the best time to experience this place. Great selection, great food, great service, and the vibe was perfect for an after-work moment. I could talk with my friend about my day and still enjoy the energy of the space. The oysters and froze were so good. Really solid spot.

Went for their happy hour which was bustling. I didn't care for the hostess who tried to just throw me anywhere inside of a crowded space.  I ended up finding a decent seat on the patio and my server was really nice. The food was pretty good, and I didn't have to wait long even though it was busy. I

Loved this spot!! Must come for happy hour! Salmon slides were delicious, heck even the chicken tenders were amazing! It stays crowded so make reservations if you can. There is a 90 minute per table limit. Highly recommended

Been here a few times over the years. The food truck is great (it is a separate business operated within the brewery) and they have a solid beer selection. A great selection of different seating areas for groups big and small. Would be there a whole lot if I lived in the area. I try to make a point

Such a fun time! Went here as a stop for the metropolitan beer trail and had such a great time. The outdoor seating was lovely, as seen in the videos attached. Definitely a great place to have fun with friends :)

The “wunder” in this beer garden is it’s vibe and experience. There is lots of seating, a solid selection of beers, cocktails, and nonalcoholic options. A must if in the area - I’m sure it’s lively on weekends, but a Wednesday night was perfect for us!

Seems like a pretty chill place to be at any day of the week. We went on Monday and they had trivia night. Lots of people! Looks like they has several areas to get drinks, so that's convenient.  I did see a bunch of reserved signs. Not sure if you need to reserve setting areas, but if so that's dumb
Very laid back atmosphere with lots of seating. Children are allowed and they offer corn hole. There are a couple of food trucks on site, too.

LOVE THIS PLACE!! Staff are so friendly, food is delicious, we sat outside and it was so pleasant, situated in a quiet neighborhood but right around the corner from Union Station.

The Ultimate Brunch Gyro was delicious!!

Can't wait to go back and hit it the one in Baltimore too!

Delicious food and excellent service!
The food was well prepared and everything was delicious. We all wish we could visit again to make we order every dish!
The lady was very nice, although she knows we just tourists, she still offer umbrellas when she found we went outside without umbrellas!
A plac

This Mediterranean spot is a true hidden gem! Tucked away, but absolutely worth finding. The manager was warm, attentive, and made us feel so welcomed from the moment we walked in. The food was outstanding—fresh, flavorful, and beautifully prepared. We had the chicken and salmon plates, and both wer

Amazing food! We had already been in DC 5 days before finding this place. We picked it for its proximity to Union Station but we were completely blown away by the food - best we've eaten on this trip without a shadow of a doubt. Perfectly balanced plates with nearly every color of the rainbow presen

I went to Cafe Fili with a friend on Sunday for lunch. It was my second visit. The restaurant is light and airy. The service was very attentive and efficient. I had a chicken plate that came with rice, hummus, pickled vegetables and other fixings. I thought it was delicious and also an excellent val

Went to St. Anselm for Thanksgiving / Engagement Celebration with a party of 4 and had a great time! The biscuits and pimento cheese are worth the hype for sure. We got a whole array of food and all of it was amazing! We got the pecan pie and chocolate cake for dessert, which was great as well. The

TLDR: overpriced, bad to mediocre food, small portions.

Went to brunch here about six years ago. Ordered a breakfast plate and latte and was very underwhelmed. The portion was small and nothing special. The latte came in a tiny teacup. It was literally about four sips and looked like it had been si

Came for dinner to celebrate our anniversary. Drinks were nice but took forever to arrive (bar was backed up per our server who apologized for the delay). Biscuits were amazing and an absolutely must here. The food (ribeye & butcher's steak), while good, took forever to arrive. One of my sides (crea

Amazing place, took around 10-15 minutes to get seated since it was quite busy. Our waiter was lovely, great guy. I ordered the buttermilk  biscuits and they were great, they were nice and soft and warm on the inside, they came with a cream spread which tasted amazing, it was my first time trying Am

We went for happy hour and had a great experience. Try the blue crab deviled eggs & the biscuits with pimento cheese are not to be missed! Really affordable prices & top notch service. We’ll definitely be back.

The décor and atmosphere were definitely a vibe, and our server stayed attentive throughout the entire meal.

As for the food — was good, just not anything super spectacular. I’d definitely drop in again if I’m in the area. I didn’t get a chance to try a drink, but the bartender offered plenty of gr

stopped here because it was recommended by a friend and it did not disappoint. Our waiter was super nice and attentive, the ambiance was really cool & the drinks were pretty awesome! The food was good but not great (we are from Texas so I think our expectations may be high). Some food was a bit too

We really enjoyed this restaurant a lot. The decor and atmosphere is outstanding and very unique. Really love the generously sized bar and the cocktails, though pricey, are sophisticated and have depth of flavor. The food is also a bit overpriced but you can tell the quality of ingredients is very g

Decent food, but nothing exceptional. Would recommend the huevos rancheros if you're eating here during brunch. Portions are good, big enough to not be filling but satisfied. As with the price, service is phenomenal.

When this place first opened, there was massive hype given the beautiful and quirk

El Presidente, a bar & restaurant caught my eye one day while visiting Union Market. It was happy hour time, and all I could see is good vibes, colorful, ocean-inspired decor, and people enjoying themselves around what looked like an open air, carousel of cool!

I took note of the name and decided t

info.name: The Pub & The People
info.address: 1648 North Capitol St NW, Washington, DC 20002

reviews.text:
Smily woman came out to greet us in such a friendly way - so easy to do yet so few places do it!

$5 fries in happy hour. The woman behind the bar gave us a free whisky because she poured it erroneously...

I was looking for an Irish Pub, while this is a quaint little pub, not irish. The beer is definitely served  perfect, albeit shorter than normal. The burger is tasty, but definitely not cooked to order. The sandwich fell apart half way threw, so much fluid it just clasped. I won't discount it  is a
A quaint little restaurant in town. The burger was absolutely delicious. Hot, fresh veg, well seasoned, cooked perfectly, juicy. They had a unique side choice: Shishito Peppers. Loved them!

Outstanding service and world class pub cuisine! Delicious shishito peppers, charred broccolini, salmon, ahi poke bowl, burger and wings. The decor is warm and inviting. The open kitchen is tiny but the flavors are massive!
I highly recommend The Pub and The People

My go to neighborhood spot. Amazing solid bar food, paired with excellent other options for everyone if you're not in a burger or chicken sandwich vibe. Always fresh, always good. Reasonable prices, and a beloved staff. I love this place. They take care of their regulars and it's always a great neig

I ordered via DoorDash because I wasn’t feeling well and was very disappointed when both of my sandwiches arrived with sauce on them, despite my request for no mayo or aioli due to allergies. I then made the effort to walk 15 minutes to the restaurant expecting the issue to be corrected, but to my s

Came here for the first time and unfortunately, it’ll be the last. We ordered a burger, quesadilla, mozzarella sticks, and a Caesar salad. The burger was incredibly bland, and there was no option to customize the toppings from the tablet. What you get is what you get. The mozzarella sticks came out

This was my first time trying this place and it was really good, the smash burger exceeded my expectations and the plant atmosphere was very pretty. However I wanted to stay and study for a few hours and couldn’t help but leave after so many flies were surrounding me and my food, to the point where

First time eating from here! I kept it simple with a side of Mozerella Sticks and a side Greek Salad. Establishment is clean with a welcoming atmosphere and ordering was easy. 👇🏾

The Mozerella sticks were torch! They were crispy and cheesy! I don't know what the batter is but it is very flavorful!

Let's take a moment to appreciate the Chimichurri steak I just devoured! This meal was absolutely delicious! The steak was perfectly paired with avocado, roasted corn, potatoes, Caesar salad, and the dressing added an extra burst of flavor!

Now that we've covered the main event, let me introduce yo

A really pleasant surprise in Union Station, an alternative to sandwiches, fast food. Very diverse oriental menu. Both my and my spouses dishes were very tasty, served up quickly, and really ample (burp!).  Most tables out in the open of the station so ambient noisy is present. We were in transit an

I was happy with my lunch here.  We got a couple of dishes to share and an appetizer, and it was all good.  My favorite part was the pickled cabbage with the Manila pork BBQ dish.  We also got general Tso chicken and fried lumpia.
Eat in Union Station.  Hot and fast Asian cuisine.  We got dumpling soup and the Hong Kong Soup. Great service. Sweet view. Not too pricey.

I arrived to Union Station hungry and I am reviewing as I inhale my food so it may be biased. But to say the food is good is an understatement. This might be one of my top 15 meals I ever had. I ordered the Curry Luksa Noodle soup. It was delicious and arrived within 5 minutes of ordering. Had veggi

This is one of the better restaurants in Union Station.  Their service is efficient and consistent which is helpful if you want to catch a train.  I find the fried rice particularly tasty.  You can also tell them how much spice to add in the dishes and they are very accommodating.  The basil based d

The Shift Manager (Pre) was phenomenal. Talk about customer service at its finest! I don’t go out to eat often and when I do I love receiving amazing customer service and this spot has it for sure! I will definitely continue to come back to this specific location (1275 1st NE). It’s truly been a ple

Delish!  Needed food after a long day and Roti hit the spot!  Ordered a greens and grain bowl with harissa chicken and steak with added toppings of my choosing.  It was great.  With a drink came to about $20, but chicken AND steak increased the price.  Totally worth it.

Arrived in DC after a long day of travelling, and all I felt like was a nice salad. We went walking down the street in the hopes of finding something, and saw a guy eating outside Roti, so decided to go in. It did not disappoint. We each had the Harissa Chicken Chopped Salad and enjoyed every mouthf
Not bad if you're in one of the nearby hotels and need a less unhealthy food option nearby

Mediterranean chicken bowl was good tasting but the chicken was a bit cold while there was plenty more sitting on the stove. Service was also subpar most likely because there was only a single worker, though I was one of only two customers inside. Most likely will just go to Potbelly if I’m ever in

Unique crepe location in Union Station. I thought the taste was okay, but the quality and the service did not align with the price. Its uniqueness and the health conscious style showed potential for this restaurant. I would say honing the uniqueness (maybe like a unique sauce or unique packaging) an

The crepe tasted great 👍 we ordered a sweet pancake with honey, banana and almonds, as well as a pancake with beef, cheese and vegetables. Both pancakes were delicious. The price was reasonable. The restaurant locates  on the second floor of the train station, and in this sense it was a kind of disa

This place is located near Pratt Street in Baltimore downtown. Crepes were delicious, and they made it right in front of us. We ordered Nutella and strawberry crepe and strawberry and banana crepe. There is not much space to sit and eat. However you can eat outside by the pier.

We went on a Friday afternoon and wanted meatless offerings. We were looking forward to the egg and cheese, but when we arrived the server said that it was a breakfast item and that he didn't make breakfast items in the afternoon. That information wasn't on the menu online or the one posted above th

The crepes were so yummy! If you’re up for eating in the food court at the train station, it’s totally worth it. They have a variety of sweet and savory crepes to choose from. And while the food court atmosphere isn’t the most beautiful, union station itself is worth some time seeing.

The look and overall vibe at this restaurant was really nice and aesthetically pleasing, but it’s unfortunately the only thing going for it as the food is below average and borderline abysmal. Between my boyfriend and I, we had the mushroom arancini, “bruschetta”, [heavily] charred octopus and salmo

Great spot with amazing bartenders and service! We only went for a drink but the whole place was warm and inviting! We even got a free dish the chef was trying out! Would love to come back to try their food menu.

Amazing experience and atmosphere. The food was delicious.... I almost licked my plate. The cocktails were beautiful and tasty. I will definitely be back! Our server, Alicia, was absolutely the best! Attentive, informative, and friendly.

Some friends rented out the bistro for their wedding party and it was the perfect space. The party was so intimate and perfect for the celebration. The food and drinks were fantastic, I’m still dreaming about the sliders that were served. I can’t wait to come back to town and try the restaurant on a

Great food and drinks both time I’ve been here. The first time I got the burger and it was perfection. Super flavorful and worth the price. Second time I came for happy hour and their truffle fries hit the spot. I’ve only sat at the bar, the bartenders are nice and are willing to help you pick the b

info.name: La' Shukran
info.address: Alley Entrance, 417 Morse St NE 2nd Floor, Washington, DC 20002

reviews.text: After multiple days of searching for dinner reservations at La' Shukran (there were plenty of 9:00pm and later available), I was finally able to secure a 5:30pm two days before my desired date.  The time and the day were not ideal, but I took what I could get.  I had read a very complementary snippe

Walked in just to check out the space and ended up having one of the best dining experiences ever. Huge thanks to the host, for honoring his word and for finding us a spot when they were fully booked (I believe his name was David), Junior, for the incredible cocktails- the Mish Mish, margarita and t

I went into this restaurant with high expectations after countless recommendations from friends, but unfortunately, it didn't live up to the hype. I had a 5:30 PM reservation and was looking forward to finally trying this much-talked-about spot.The service was decent overall, though our server was a

AMAZING experience - totally lives up to the hype. Took my parents and we loved every bite. Service was perfect.
Highly recommend:
BBQ Maitake
Sweetbreads (omg amazing)
Haswei
BUT LEAVE ROOM FOR DESSERT -
The Knafeh Nabulsi was INCREDIBLE
Also great wine selection - I don’t drink liquor but my paren

If you’re interested in a late night, romantic, yet thrilling setting, La’ Shukran is the place.  With its discrete, alleyway entrance, La’ Shukran blends nostalgic escape with stylish design.  While inside, take note of the low, intriguing lighting, comfortable seating, sophisticated decor, and top

The best spot in Union Market!  We were warmly greeted by the lovely hostess and seated at the far corner table, which was perfect!  The dining room is cozy, warm, and the ambience convivial. Our server, Isaac, was highly knowledgeable about the menu and made spot-on recommendations for our wine and

Went on a very busy night. We waited half an hour for a table we had a reservation for. Normally I’m fine getting a drink at the bar there’s nowhere really to wait without being in the way and it was approximately one million degrees inside and there was nowhere to put my coat. So waiting to be sat

The moment you walk through the front door you know you are in for an experience. The atmosphere was sophisticated and full of history. The service was truly outstanding start to finish. The cocktails and wine were superb and the food was excellent!

Oddly located in an alley, the only backside facade in a wide industrial alley amidst rows of dumpsters... sorta turned my stomach before entering the front door. If you're on a romantic date, you might wanna blindfold them until after they enter. Inside, it's a very dark, old world Italian Steak Ho

Stopped by Minetta for brunch with friends and had a decent experience. The ambiance was nice and welcoming, with a beautiful space - especially the back dining area, even thought it felt a bit tight and cozy at times. I also really appreciated the full bar and seating along the walls once you walk

TLDR: I highly recommend Aboveground for your fish-and-chips needs (plus good vibes)!

Aboveground is a hidden gem in DC, serving up delicious fish and chips from London, as well as other bites with South/Southeastern Asian influences.  My wife and I had heard about this place, so we ventured to Uni

I was looking forward to trying this out since I’ve been craving some fish and chips! But as someone who grew up in UK, the food was too seasoned (especially the chips!). The fish and mushy peas were delicious though and the portion was not bad although $19 (without tax) was a bit much compared to p

British for in the Union Market ABOVEGROUND. Lots of choices including sausages rolls, shepherds pie, fish and chips etc. There's even British canned goods and sweets. I got fish and chips. The portions are good. It came with mushy peas. The batter was crispy but a bit salty

I recently visited Aboveground at Union Market, and overall, it was a great experience! They serve a variety of British classics like fish and chips, shepherd's pie, and chicken and leek pie. The fish and chips are really tasty, though at $18, the price feels a bit steep for the portion size. The En

Hands down the best fish and chips I’ve ever had!! Above Ground DC ruined me for all others! The batter was impossibly crisp without being greasy and the fish flaked apart like butter. You can tell it’s fresh and cooked with real care. The fries were golden and seasoned just right and that house-mad

A beautiful cozy bright coffee shop with plenty of coffee and tea options including Ethiopian coffee which a favorite of mine. I had an egg sandwich that was beautifully presented and absolutely delicious. The staff is very kind and friendly. There are fresh flowers in every table. Nice soft music p
Outstanding coffee and breakfast/lunch sandwiches! The staff are kind, and the atmosphere is really cozy. The coffee pot service was tasty and a lot of fun too.

You need to stop by here!! Cute local place with Ethiopian flavors and delicious drinks. With a quiet interior and a gorgeous back patio, this place is a perfect relax cafe. The drinks, food, desserts are all delicious! I got the iced tea, a spiced ice and milk delight all blended together 10/10, th

Stopped here this morning for a coffee and it was delicious! Cute little coffee shop with a chill vibe. I got an iced vanilla latte, fairly priced for how big it is! The espresso tasted very high quality and it was very creamy. Would definitely recommend!
Croissant was a little small for the price and there wasn’t much cheese. And the croissant was saggy, like it was microwaved. Chai was good though. Maybe I should try something else next time?

Been scouting this place for about 3 weeks for a birthday dinner.  I called over a week in advance for a party of 7 - 13 people. They were able too accommodate and the food was GOOOOOD! That hotpot was smokin and I thought I choose a milder one but it was excellent in taste for me. Now this was the

This is one of the worst Chinese restaurants I have ever been. Food is plain bad and not authentic. The place is not clean and many bugs. I was attacked by mosqueitos in Nov and you can see the photos how bad my legs were bitten while there. The staff were nice and friendly but the service was barel
Good food, Chinese meal just the way I like it. Not doused in oil but steamed. All options are good but fried vermicelli noodles is my favourite

Food was pretty good. The scallion pancakes were delicious and the beef hotpot was also very good. The portion of hotpot was huge! One person definitely cannot eat this much food. Also, even the minimally spicy option is very spicy.

A few things to mention, 20% tip were mandatory but there is very little service, the whole time waitress was not showing up, only except when they bring up the food, and they charge for the go box. The young lady is not patient and giving you an attitude. The soup it’s ok, but the rice is not fully

This is Thee Atmosphere to step out of the  “hustle” and enjoy time with a loved one and your luggage - all in your happy place while waiting for your train to board.

Your ORDER YOU SELECT…. and the Staff cooks and prepares your selections in perhaps a half an hour because this is so very popular.

🟢 Green for go, go eat delicious, hot, savory goodness while you're running late on the train you have to get on in 5 minutes. 🫩

🍔 This specific location, (Union Station) delivered timeliness, tastyness and friendlniss. The price was a little big to the portion, but it was very deliciously juicy an

Tried their Veggie Shack — it’s a good burger: crunchy, flavorful, and satisfying. However, if you're choosing between the two, I’d always recommend the Shroom Burger. It’s far superior — the crispy portobello filled with molten cheese remains unbeatable in both texture and taste.

The servers were very kind and attentive! They went above and beyond to make the experience nice.

I went with friends and we found the seating area comfortable and clean. We had a good time chatting while we waited for our food.

I got the veggie burger(6.7/10, it was alright taste wise, and it was

Tried the Shake Shack at Union Station and was pleasantly surprised by their new hot dogs — tasty and a great value while on promotion. Ordering online was super convenient, and the food was ready on time. The in-store pickup area could use a bit more organization.

Looking for that small town homey sports bar atmosphere? This is the right place. The Big Board has a friendly staff and community. Feels like everyone here is a local and knows each other. We came in for just for a small snack and some baseball. I got some Mozz sticks and a larger order of fries. T

The Big Board was the first bar I visited in DC, and it set the bar high for my experience in the city. Conveniently located within walking distance from the Capitol Building, this spot offers a welcoming and energetic atmosphere. The staff were exceptionally friendly and attentive, ensuring we were

No food here.  Drab and smelly dive bar.  The bartender had an attitude as if he was doing you a favor by merely being there.  I tried to liven up the place with some humor but the bartender seemed annoyed.  I really don't understand the appeal of this watering hole.  I guess it's because it is a wa
The burgers dont come with fries, but if you get the spicy burger, just spend the money on another beer.
The best burgers I've ever had in DC thus far. Good mimosas and tap beer. I just wished they offered delivery.

a favorite of mine! I love their housemade salsas too. Generous guac and amazing flavors! The crispy mushroom tacos are so good, so different than mushroom tacos at other restaurants. They are lightly fried, but not overly. Perfect! There are always people there and yet food comes out quickly.

If you haven’t been to Apapacho Taqueria, you’re seriously missing out. The food here is next level fresh, flavorful, and made with real care. I grabbed some of their tacos & one of their signature drinks and the layers of flavor were crazy. Everything tastes just as good as it looks. On top of the

Some of the best tacos I’ve had in DC. The suadero and the gringa are stand outs. Flavorful meats, good tortillas and great salsas.

Unlike many taco places in DC that overdress their tacos with unnecessary garnishes, Apapacho clearly trusts the flavor of their meats and tortillas to shine through,

The food is great but our tacos kept falling apart I think they should put 2 tortillas instead of 1 like other taco places. But other than that we love the food and drinks here. Also it would be cool if they had Mexican corn/Elote.The concha’s here are soooo good so soft and perfect.The employees he

Best tacos in DC, hands down. As a Mexican native, I can confidently say this is definitely the best and least pretentious taqueria I’ve found in all of DC (Then is Chicatana in Columbia Heights). Tacos are very good, and they’ve many options. I tried the mushroom one too (for my vegan friends) and
Authentic Venezuelan food.  Delicious and very tasty.  Staff is friendly. You can also find Venezuelan snacks

The food took forever to come out (more than 20 minutes) and when it did, it was room temperature/lukewarm at best. I got the pabellón criollo bowl with beef but noticed a hot dogs/pork flavor, especially when I ate the plantains. It’s clear they are using the same oil for everything which is gross.

Place: Very nice and clean, located inside La Cosecha market.

Customer service: Good.

Food: I ordered a Patacón Trío, tree tostones of fried plantain with beef, chicken and black beans. It was good. The other item was the Pepito, it could be better, the bread wasn't the expected, and beef as well.

Best gluten-free empanadas ever!! And I am a hard sell on gluten-free foods that involve breading & frying. The empanadas quickly became my go-to comfort food when I'm craving something fried, warm, and savory. Always hits the spot. The camaron, queso, and beef are my favorites but all of the option
The food is delicious and the service is good. Veronica was kind and didn't make me wait. I'm not Venezuelan, but Arepazon's food is delicious. 10/10 on their entire menu.

info.name: His & Hers
info.address: 2214 Rhode Island Ave NE, Washington, DC 20018

reviews.text: This restaurant was a 10 out of 10. Our waitress Aniyah (sorry if that’s wrong) was sweet. She gave us shot for my bday. The crab stuffed salmon was delicious. The seafood rice could have been a dish by itself. To top it off, we met a local who is a regular that bought us a drink on our way out..

The service and vibe were fine, but that’s where the positives end. The drinks were disappointing across the board—flat, unbalanced, and not enjoyable. What really threw us off, though, was the water. It tasted awful, like something was seriously wrong with the plumbing or filtration. That alone was

Whenever you are in the DC area make sure you check out his & hers restaurant their food is phenomenal, the atmosphere is a vibe and the server Aniyah was the best so professional and kind I would definitely come again. I had the stuffed salmon with vegetable fried rice and collard greens it tasted

Amazing spot! I was taking class at the Capoeira Spot and found this place nearby during my lunch break. The owner was working the bar with two other individuals and was super kind! The food was delicious. Some of the best grits I’ve had. The atmosphere is so calming. I recommend coming here!

I had 2 dishes - the charred octopus and the pan seared halibut.

I loved

There was a credit card surcharge, so just be mindful of that. We d

Feel like I got lucky stumbling into this resta

Otherwise... it was a lovely experience!
A great atmosp

First time here and hard to believe we've never come before. Every dish was tasty. Servers were friendly. Food came out very quickly. Will definitely be coming back.

My wife got a burrito bowl, said it was great. I got the  chicken enchiladas, they were great chicken was moist, and the presentation/portion s

Silver is a classic spot in the Cathedral Heights area. We love coming here for breakfast or brunch. The juice is always freshly squeezed and the coffee and tea is hot and piping. First time visiting, and we’re from out of town, what a great find! The food was absolutely delicious, with every dish packed full of flavor. You can really tell they care about quality and taste. This restaurant offers great value in good food and well/locally sourced food. Best kept secret of DC. Best lamb kebab (and laffa!), best tabuleh, best kibbeh, best grape leaves, best lentil soup… Best!
May be gotta change the name, it’s a bit hard to understand what to expect .. but it is simply the best lunch each time I came… and indeed fresh, yummy & authentically Mediterr

Awesome place to get shawarma, hummus, and fresh pita. Salim, the owner, was super nice and welcoming and the staff overall were just wonderful. Prices are reasonable for the delicious food you get and portion sizes are large (see pics!). Highly recommend this place if in Cleveland Park!
There’s no place like it. My family and I have been coming here for years. Everything is fresh, authentic, flavorful and hot! Everyone is so nice and welcoming and it’s very clean.

Absolutely phenomenal! Get the rice pudding for dessert, I swear you will love it! Light orange flavor that accents the thick milky rice pudding, definitely not your Grandmother’s rice pudding!
Everything we ordered was amazing but I am going to have dreams of that rice pudding until the day I die i

Our Wonderful Detour to Lillies 🌸

We grabbed a couple of seats at the bar for a quick drink and an appetizer, and left feeling like we discovered a local favorite. We orde

I’m really disappointed, I was debating between georgetown location and this, but this was rated higher so I chose this one. I came from the zoo and wanted to sit down for some lunch. We got the Peking Duck and we’re not disappointed. Order a hot tea, the tea service is beautiful. On top of this they did not include the dippi

I’ve never not given a tip when dining out, but this was the first time.
We waited for almost two hours without anyone informing us about the delay.
I’ve been to other branches and they were fine, but this one was really disappointing ,both the staff and the food.
Absolutely loved this place. Food was phenomenal. Spicy, well cooked, seasoned amazingly. Staff was great as was the place itself too. Would return!

The food was okay. It was pretty bland compared to other Thai places I've tried in the city. Maybe it was just the dish I ordered? I had the Chicken Pad See Ew, and we also got the Pad Thai. Nothing to write home about. But the service was great, and I really liked the restaurant's atmosphere. Plus,
Tasty and affordable! The Red Curry Pumpkin with shrimp was delicious. Lots of indoor seating. Would return!

Absolutely excellent!

Surprised to see few people dining in. There is only one waiter, but he does a fantastic job!

Great atmosphere and good food!

Would never go back here again. So basically I looked for the closest pho spot because i was SO hungry and this spot was the closest. Restaurant looked good, didn’t have to wait for a seat. Exactly what I needed following a late evening out! The apple broth was fantastic in the vegetarian soup, and not sweet like one might expect. Our go-to pho spot! One of the best in DC in our opinion. We always get the #4 and the broth is so rich in flavor.

We had rice noodles, chicken curry, fried rice, beef steak and thai tea. The food was good, but the portion was a bit small.

pros: Delicious food, well ambience

cons: the server was in a rush in a relatively empty restaurant, and he barely let us finish our orders!  Also the facilities were a bit

info.name: CAVA
info.address: 325 Park Ave S, New York, NY 10010

reviews.text: Love Cava! Second time here and really appreciate how fresh the ingredients are. It’s the first time I’ve been able to get both rice and salad as a base at a healthy fast casual place. The protein toppings are super savory too. And the eggplant… dip forget it!

Amazing experience at cava. You can build your own bowl and there are plenty of options for vegans and vegetarians as well. Each option clearly displays the amount of calories and what ingredients are present, so it’s great for people that are cautious about what they are eating and are concerned ab

It was not crowded, til it was, and then the afternoon rush was intense. I witnessed grace under pressure, and everyone worked well together to clear the customers.
Staff is very generous with their servings and this location is super clean with delicious bowl options. Service is fast so coming here between class is always worth it!

I cook Lebanese food well, so this was

Only roo

Loved the food - contemporary Italian style food cooked at a small but check homestyle restaurant. Try their range of pastas with seafood and paired with their house wine. Any visit here is sure to be a delight

Good vibes. Great people. Awesome bartender, David was amazing and very attentive to our party at the bar, drinks were delicious the food was amazing! oh this food was so delicious. the fried artichokes were probably my favorite food I had while in DC. But honestly I don’t think you could go wrong with anything on the menu. The ambiance on their little patio was great too! Would absolutely recommend

Terrible!😣

Was pleasantly surprised at how phenomenal everything was.

We were also lucky enough to be given free appetise

Let me first say, this is a gem of a restaurant and perhaps a new favorite of mine and I am so grateful it’s near my home.

From the moment my friend and I walked into Sofra, we felt it was a warm welcoming atmosphere. It was cozy and felt like you were part of the family.

My friend and I went at a

The atmosphere is eccentric and laid back, metal chairs and basic wood

Food was brought out to our table. They had a spot for us to wash our hands. They had nice silverware. Unlimited sauce. I had a

Our kiddo loved the grilled cheese that was on a Portuguese roll.

We bought the sauce. Will come back.

Snacks were good. Prices are on the high side. Panda cake pops were almost $7 each. Raspberry cake was good. Black and white cookie didn’t have much flavor. Nice place to stop for a special treat before the zoo.

Enjoy! :

The food here is fantastic and reasonably priced. The service is also fantastic. We usually do takeout here but decided to try dining in. The servers were so kind and attentive. It’s a great, casual hole in the wall spot for some yummy Thai food.

We rented the whole restaurant for my daughters 28th birthday.  Miguel and his team were AMAZING!  He put together a 3 course menu that was delicious.  The drinks were great. I'll start by saying delicious! Came by this restaurant twice in a week while my org was having our conference in the area. I was pleasantly surprised by the flavor of all the options. info.name: The Tavern at The Henley Park

reviews.text: Went for the tea time experience. Very readable price compared to others in the area. Tasty selection of scones and desserts. Finger sandwiches were also served but was not my favorite.

This review reflects our experience from March 31, 2024. Despite nearly canceling due to the torrential rain, we’re glad we didn’t. Celebrating Easter with an afternoon tea on a rainy day turned out to be a cozy and relaxing experience. The selection of cute, beautifully crafted pastries was delight

Wonderful afternoon tea experience. I've been to many teas around the world and know what makes a great afternoon tea. The top things were: the variety of sandwiches, the star was the lobster salad cup, not many places offer two full size moist scones with lemon curd and cream!, in my opinion a must

Yes, it is true that the tea is served from teabags, but it was still well worth it for the price point. I would definitely go back.

The Henley Park hotel is a beautiful, historic hotel in downtown DC.
